<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ESMG Combustion and Detonation
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../esmg.gif" ALT="ESMG Logo">
</CENTER>
<BR><BR><P><I>Announcement and Call for Papers</I>

<P><STRONG>28th International Annual Conference of ICT<BR>
June 24 - June 27, 1997</STRONG>

<P>Karlsruhe<BR>
Federal Republic of Germany<BR><BR>

<H2>Combustion and Detonation</H2>


<P><I>28th International Annual Conference of ICT</I>

<P><STRONG>Combustion and Detonation</STRONG>

<P>Investigating combustion and detonation properties of energetic 
materials is the basis for establishing new products. In recent 
years, the technical progress in manufacturing, diagnostics and 
modelling has great influence in various research fields related to 
propellants and explosives.

<P>The spectrum of task comprises qualification and testing of 
energetic materials, non-intrusive combustion and detonation diagnostics, 
influence of mechanical and processing properties, determination 
of performance and sensitivity parameters, safety aspects and 
technology; modelling of reaction and combustion phenomena.

<P>The 28th International ICT Annual conference is aimed at the 
introduction of new strategies, developments and research results 
and technologies with a special emphasis on combustion and detonation 
of energetic materials.


<P><STRONG>Chairman of the Conference</STRONG>

<P>Wilhelm Eckl,<BR>
ICT Pfinztal<BR>



<P><I>Announcement and Call for Papers</I>

<P>The Fraunhofer-Institut f&uuml;r Chemische Technologie (ICT) 
is holding its 28th International Annual Conference on

<P><STRONG>Combustion and Detonation</STRONG>

<P><U>Main topics are:</U>

<UL>
<LI>Qualification and testing of energetic materials
<LI>Modelling and diagnostics
<LI>Performance and sensitivity
<LI>Safety aspects and technology
</UL>

<P><U>Presentation:</U>

<P>Contributions to the conference can be presented as oral presentations 
(presentation time 20 minutes including discussion) or posters.

<P>Please submit an abstract not exceeding 300 words together with the 
exact title and author(s).

<P>The papers will be published in the Conference Proceedings which will 
appear at the beginning of the event. Guidelines on how to prepare the 
text for publication will be sent to the authors.


<P><U>Conference languages: </U>

English, German (Simultaneous Interpretation)

<BR>
<P><U>Deadlines:</U>

<P>
<TABLE WIDTH=400>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD WIDTH=225>Abstracts</TD>
<TD WIDTH=175>November 29, 1996</TD>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD WIDTH=225>Reply to authors</TD>
<TD WIDTH=175>January/February, 1997</TD>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD WIDTH=225>Full papers (camera ready)</TD>
<TD WIDTH=175>March 21, 1997</TD>
</TABLE>

<P>The program will be published in April 1997.<BR>
Further Information e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:ekl@ict.fhg.de">ekl@ict.fhg.de</A>
</BODY>
</HTML>

</DOC>
