<HEAD>

<TITLE>ICT-ES Research Fields</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1>Research Fields of ICT - Department Energetic Systems </H1>

<P>
<EM>*** Achtung Baustelle ***</EM>
<H2>Overview </H2>

<P>
Table of contents for fast access:
<P>
<A HREF="ict_research.html#industrialSafety">Industrial Safety</A>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ict_research.html#substanceHazard">Substances with hazard potential</A>
<LI><A HREF="ict_research.html#chemicalExplosions">Chemical explosions</A>
<LI><A HREF="ict_research.html#gasExplosions">Gas explosions</A>
<LI><A HREF="ict_research.html#expertisingWork">Expertising work</A>

<LI><A HREF="ict_research.html#others" >other research fields</A>
</UL>

<P>
<A HREF="ict_research.html#automotiveSafety">Automotive Safety</A>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><A NAME="industrialSafety">Industrial Safety </A></H2>

<H3><A NAME="substanceHazard">Substances with hazard potential
(pyrophoric and self-heating substances)</A> </H3>

<UL>
<LI>self heating reactions
<LI>critical diameters
<LI>thermal analysis / stability 
<LI>safety problems in production, storage, handling and transport
<LI>pool fires 
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="chemicalExplosions">Chemical explosions</A> </H3>

<UL>
<LI>decomposition of chemicals to gaseous species (caused by heating,
igniter, shear forces, impact)
<LI>rapid oxidation of gases / fine dispersed particles
<LI>thermal runaway explosion (a exothermic reaction out of control)

</UL>

<H3><A NAME="gasExplosions">Gas explosions</A> </H3>

<UL>
<LI>Basic investigations of phenomena associated with gas explosions
(Dispersion, DDT, flammability limits)
<LI>time resolved temperature, radiation emission, velocity of
propagation
<LI>tank rupture/burst/explosion 
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="expertisingWork">Expertising work</A> </H3>

<UL>
<LI>risk analysis
<LI>prevention and protection against explosion detonation
<LI>design of buildings/facilities/plants with respect to explosion/detonation
prevention and protection 
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="others">Other research fields</A> </H3>

<UL>
<LI>liquid explosions
<LI>solids explosions
<LI>dust explosions
<LI>container explosions
<LI>free jet flames
<LI>fires
<LI>dispersion of gases and aerosols
<LI>ignition phenomena
<LI>flammability
<LI>flammability limits
<LI>detonations / gases solids liquids / crtitical diameters /
critical concentrations
<LI>substances with spontaneous combustion/decomposition ability:

<LI>spills and releases 
</UL>

<HR>

<H2><A NAME="automotiveSafety">Automotive Safety </A></H2>

<UL>
<LI>air-bags
<LI>impact 
<LI>fast measuring techniques
<LI>fastening belts
<LI>fire extinguishing by gas generators
<LI>burning / evolved gas <BR>

</UL>

<HR>

