<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ESMG Rectangular air-cushioned explosion door
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../esmg.gif" ALT="ESMG Logo">
<H1>Products</H1>
</CENTER>
<H2>Rectangular air-cushioned explosion door for reduced explosion pressure &lt; 
1.5 barg and large venting areas</H2>


<STRONG>Design features</STRONG>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>SIT rectangular air-cushioned explosion doors are suitable 
for structures with a calculated reduced explosion pressure Pred &lt; 1.5 
barg and for large venting areas. The operating principle is the same 
as with all SIT air-cushioned explosion doors. The kinetic energy of the 
lid is absorbed by building up the air-cushion against the baffle plate, the 
energy transfer from the low mass, aluminium lid into the resilient, heavy baffle 
plate and the spring assembly supporting the baffle plate.

<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>The <STRONG>RLE</STRONG> version is especially suited for large dust 
collectors and electrostatic precipitators, for dryers and for various 
processes, even under harsh environmental conditions. The design allows 
installation for vertical, inclined- and horizontal venting. Due to the 
light sandwich design of the lid, its inertia is very low. Therefore, the 
venting efficiency of the RLE is 85-96% compared against low-mass rupture 
disks. The RLE version further features:
<UL>
<LI>automatic closure
<LI>good insulating properties (1.4 W/mK), therefore no condensation
<LI>heat resistance up to 150&deg; C
<LI>progressive silicone lip seal, no leakage below the pre-set static 
reponse pressure
</UL>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>An optional sentinel switch enables remote signalization of 
each venting action.

<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>The <STRONG>RLE-S</STRONG> series is of an extremely light, all 
aluminium construction. It is suitable for explosion venting of wood 
processing- and storage equipment, dust collectors working at ambient 
temperature, buildings etc. The lid remains tight at various preset pressures, 
due to the progressive silicone seal.</P>

StuvEx GmbH<BR>
Wilhelmstr. 2<BR>
D-59057 Hamm<BR>
Tel.: +49-2381-271480<BR>
Fax: +49-2381-271248<BR>
<BR>
For further information please contact us by e-mail: 
<A HREF=mailto:ober@prosicht.hamtec.de>ober@prosicht.hamtec.de</A>

