<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ESMG Pressure relief stacks
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../esmg.gif" ALT="ESMG Logo">
<H1>Products</H1>
</CENTER>
<H2>Pressure relief stacks with hinged lid
for explosion venting from ducts, minimizing the risk of downstream reignition</H2>

<STRONG>Design</STRONG>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>The hinged lid is, under normal conditions, held by a retaining 
device with an adjustable pre-setting of the static response pressure. The 
pre-setting is done in our works and lead sealed. A heavy, hinged and freely 
movable baffle plate takes the energy impact of the light aluminium lid of 
the stack. The lid has to turn approximately 270&deg; and loses a significant 
part of its kinetic energy thereby, before it hits the baffle plate.<BR>
As in the case of explosion doors, a sentinel switch for remote signalization 
of venting occurrences is available optionally.

<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>Explosion stacks are also available with air-cushioned explosion 
doors instead of the hinged lid shown on this page.</P>

