<TITLE>
THE ARIPAR PROJECT
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511642
Quality valid. date   :1995-12-12
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :THE ARIPAR PROJECT : ANALYSIS OF THE MAJOR ACCIDENT
       RISKS  CONNECTED WITH INDUSTRIAL AND TRANSPORTATION ACTIVITIES IN THE
       RAVENNA AREA
Author                :EGIDI D
       FORABOSCHI F P
       SPADONI G
       AMENDOLA A
Affiliation           :CIVIL PROTECTION OF THE EMILIA-ROMAGNA REGION,
       BOLOGNA (IT)
       UNIVERSITY OF BOLOGNA, DEPARTMENT OF CHEMICAL AND PROCESS ENGINEERING
       (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)

Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: RELIABILITY ENGINEERING AND SYSTEM SAFETY,
       VOL. 49 (1995) PP. 75-89
Abstract              :The paper describes the ARIPAR project aimed at the
       assessment  of  the  major  accident  risks  connected  with storage,
       process  and  transportation  of  dangerous substances in the densely
       populated  Ravenna  area  in Italy, which includes a large complex of
       chemical  and  petrochemical plants and minor industries, essentially
       distributed  around an important commercial port. The project started
       by   making   a   complete   inventory  of  fixed  installations  and
       transportation  activities capable of provoking major fire, explosion
       and  toxic  release  events;  Relevant  accident  scenarios were then
       developed  for the single hazard sources; probabilities were assigned
       to  the  events  and  consequences  were  evaluated. Finally iso-risk
       contours  and F-N diagrams were evaluated both for the single sources
       and for the overall area. The methodological approach and the results
       have  proved  to  be  very  useful  for  the priority-ranking of risk
       mitigating interventions and physical planning in a complex area.
Facet codes           :102 Chemical engineering
       308 Industrial processes
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1995
Publication type      :ART An article in a journal
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13430500
Subject index codes   :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
       TEC (OTHER TECHNOLOGY)
 
