EXPLORING ENVIRONMENTAL EFFECTS OF ACCIDENTS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199510960
Quality valid. date   :1995-08-10
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :EXPLORING ENVIRONMENTAL EFFECTS OF ACCIDENTS DURING
       MARINE  TRANSPORT  OF DANGEROUS GOODS BY USE OF ACCIDENT DESCRIPTIONS
Author                :ROMER H
       HAASTRUP P
       PETERSEN H J S
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       TECHNICAL  UNIVERSITY OF DENMARK, DEPARTMENT OF CHEMICAL ENGINEERING,
       LYNGBY (DK)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT
Abstract              :Based on 1776 descriptions of water transport
       accidents with dangerous goods, the environmental problems associated
       with  releases  of  this  kind  are  discussed. It was shown that the
       volumes  of  crude  oil  releases are approximately five times larger
       than  releases  of  oil  products.  Only  2  %  of the 1776 accidents
       described  contained information on consequences to living organisms,
       and 10 % contained information on consequences to ecosystems.
