<TITLE>
HOW MANY ACCIDENTS HAPPEN WITH HAZARDOUS MATERIALS?
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199510664
Quality valid. date   :1995-07-07
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :HOW MANY ACCIDENTS HAPPEN WITH HAZARDOUS MATERIALS?
Author                :HAASTRUP P
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: HOW MANY ACCIDENTS HAPPEN WITH
       HAZARDOUS  MATERIALS?,  STOCKHOLM (SE), MARCH 23, 1995 AVAILABLE FROM
       EUROPEAN  COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 38930
       ORA
Abstract              :Accidents with hazardous materials are normally
       registered  in  a  number of national and international databases, in
       order  to allow the accident experiences to be shared. An analysis of
       seven  European  databases  showed that the degree of overlap between
       the sources and thus the coverage of a single database varies widely,
       and is generally low, which means that the actual number of accidents
       occurring   is   not  well  known.  The  presentation  describes  the
       comparison  of  accidents from fixed installations, and estimates the
       (unknown) number of industrial accidents with hazardous materials.
