<TITLE>
THE DATABASE OF THE MAJOR ACCIDENT REPORTING SYSTEM
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199510635
Quality valid. date   :1995-07-07
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE DATABASE OF THE MAJOR ACCIDENT REPORTING SYSTEM
Author                :RASMUSSEN K
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: SEMINAR ON ACCIDENT ANALYSIS, ISPRA
       (IT),   OCTOBER  12-14,  1994  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN  COMMISSION,
       DGXIII/D-2,    L-2920    LUXEMBOURG    AS    PAPER   EN   38532   ORA
Abstract              :The EC accident notification scheme MARS is based on
       the requirements in Community Directive no. 82/501/EEC and amendments
        to  set  up  an  accident  database  to collate information on major
       accidents  in  the  industries  covered  by  the  Directive. The data
       supplied  should  be  as  exhaustive  as  possible,  including events
       leading  to the accident and consequences and emergency response. The
       contents of MARS are not public, but a public summary is published.
       It  has  been  chosen  to  build  the  MARS  database as a relational
       database  using  Superbase in a Windows environment. The platform for
       the  program is a PC with DOS operating system. The database reflects
       the  structure  of the notification form and has five main parts: (i)
       report  profile;  (ii)  short  notification; (iii) full report of the
       occurrence;  (iv) full report of the consequences; (v) full report of
       the response.
Facet codes           :007 Safety
       702 Data bases and data banks
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1994
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB133107500
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
       IPS (INFORMATION PROCESSING, INFORMATION SYSTEMS)
 
