<HEAD>
<TITLE>
GENERAL GUIDELINES FOR CONTENT OF INFORMATION TO THE PUBLIC
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199411376
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-07
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :GENERAL GUIDELINES FOR CONTENT OF INFORMATION TO THE
       PUBLIC      :      DIRECTIVE      82/501/EEC      -     ANNEX     VII
Author                :DE MARCHI B
       FUNTOWICZ S (EDITORS)
Affiliation           :ISIG, INSTITUTE OF INTERNATIONAL SOCIOLOGY, GORIZIA
       (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15946 EN (1994) 36 PP., FS, FREE OF CHARGE ISBN
       92-826-9053-9  AVAILABLE  FROM  JOINT  RESEARCH CENTRE, INSTITUTE FOR
       SYSTEMS   ENGINEERING  AND  INFORMATICS,  I-21020  ISPRA  (VA.)  (IT)
Abstract              :The Directive 82/501/EEC on the major accident
       hazards of certain industrial activities requires that members of the
       public  liable  to  be  affected  by  a major accident be informed of
       safety  measures  and  how  they  should  behave  in  the event of an
       accident.  The  public information requirements have been extended by
       the  second  amendment to the Directive (88/610/EEC, Official Journal
       of  the  European  Communities L336, 7 December 1988). The guidelines
       developed  at  the  JRC  Ispra concern the items of information to be
       provided  according  to  Annex  VII  to  the amended Directive. Since
       research indicates that the means of communicating with the public is
       strongly   determined   by   local  cultural  mores,  the  guidelines
       concentrate on the information content that is to be communicated.
Facet codes           :001 Documentation and information science
       005 Science policy
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1994
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13360900
Subject index codes   :POL (POLICIES)
       INF (INFORMATION, MEDIA)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
</PRE>
