<TITLE>
LESSONS LEARNED FROM EMERGENCIES AFTER ACCIDENTS IN
GREECE AND ITALY
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410803
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-06
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :LESSONS LEARNED FROM EMERGENCIES AFTER ACCIDENTS IN
       GREECE    AND   ITALY   INVOLVING   DANGEROUS   CHEMICAL   SUBSTANCES
Author                :ZIOMAS I C
       TZOUMAKA P N
       FIORENTINI C
       ROMANO A
       LOCATELLI M
Affiliation           :ARISTOTELE UNIVERSITY OF THESSALONIKI, PHYSICS
       DEPARTMENT (GR)
       ARISTOTELE UNIVERSITY OF THESSALONIKI, PHYSICS DEPARTMENT (GR)
       TELSA SPA, PERO
       TRR SRL, OSIO SOTTO (BG)
       TRR SRL, OSIO SOTTO (BG)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15767 EN (1994) 106 PP., FS, ECU 15 ISBN
       92-826-8222-6  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The report includes two separate studies on emergency
       planning  and  response  provisions for accidents in Greece and Italy
       involving  dangerous substances either in fixed installations subject
       to the requirements of the Seveso Directive, or during transportation
       of  dangerous chemical substances. The first part of the studies is a
       comprehensive  review  of  the  framework  for emergency planning and
       response.  The  second  part  focuses  on  relevant  accidents. Fixed
       installations  and  transport accidents have been selected to extract
       lessons on emergency preparedness and response.
Facet codes           :538 Safety and health at work
