</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410524
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :EC STUDY - LESSONS LEARNT FROM EMERGENCIES AFTER
       ACCIDENTS   IN   THE   NETHERLANDS   INVOLVING  DANGEROUS  SUBSTANCES
Author                :WIERSMA T
       HEIDEBRINK I
       VAN BEEK P
Affiliation           :TNO, DEPARTMENT OF INDUSTRIAL SAFETY, APELDOORN (NL)
       TNO, DEPARTMENT OF INDUSTRIAL SAFETY, APELDOORN (NL)
       TNO, DEPARTMENT OF INDUSTRIAL SAFETY, APELDOORN (NL)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15563 EN (1994) 100 PP., FS, ECU 11.50 ISBN
       92-826-7513-0  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :This report presents the results of the study carried
       out  for  the  Netherlands  on  lessons learnt from emergencies after
       accidents   involving   dangerous  substances.  An  overview  of  the
       organisation   of  emergency  response  is  provided  which  contains
       descriptions of laws, regulations, tasks and preparatory activities.
       Seven  accidents  involving  fixed  installations  and transportation
       activities   are  described.  Lessons  learnt  by  the  organisations
       involved  are  provided,  and  conclusions  and  recommendations  are
       presented.
