<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410522
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :EC STUDY - LESSONS LEARNT FROM EMERGENCIES AFTER
       ACCIDENTS     IN     IRELAND     INVOLVING    DANGEROUS    SUBSTANCES
Author                :MAXWELL D R
Affiliation           :HINTON AND HIGGS, DUBLIN (IE)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15565 EN (1994) 98 PP., FS, ECU 16.50 ISBN
       92-826-7516-5  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :This report discusses the study to gather information
       on emergency planning and response in Ireland. A comprehensive review
       of  policy,  legislation  and  organisation  is  presented  including
       details  of  statutory  requirements,  central  and  local government
       authorities  and emergency and voluntary services. Relevant accidents
       which have occurred in Ireland at both fixed installations and during
       transportation  are  summarised. An evaluation of the suitability and
       efficiency  of  the  emergency planning and response during and after
       accidents is given and the lessons to be learnt are discussed.
