<TITLE>
EC STANDARD PROBLEM
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410449
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :EC STANDARD PROBLEM : PREDICTION OF EFFECTS CAUSED BY
       A     CABLE    FIRE    EXPERIMENT    WITHIN    THE    HDR    FACILITY
Note                  :FINAL COMPARISON REPORT
Author                :KARWAT H
Affiliation           :TECHNISCHE UNIVERSITT MNCHEN, LEHRSTUHL FR
       REAKTORDYNAMIK           UND           REAKTORISCHRHEIT          (DE)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15648 EN (1994) 175 PP., FS, ECU 18.50 ISBN
       92-826-8180-7  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :With the agreement of the German Federal Ministry of
       Research and Technology (BMFT), the HDR project has offered the cable
       fire  experiment  E42.2  as  a  basis  for  an international standard
       problem  to  be  performed  under  the  sponsorship  of  the European
       Commission.  Within  the specified fire compartment three cable racks
       have  been installed which were loaded with various types of selected
       cables.  Another  three  racks  were installed, vertically fixed to a
       side  wall  of the fire compartment. A gas burner was operated for 60
       seconds  igniting a small cable package close to the burner. With the
       necessary  initial  and  operating conditions given, the participants
       were requested to predict thermal effects caused by the cable fire.
       The  standard  problem exercise demonstrated the limited state of the
       art in the simulation of a cable fire.
Facet codes           :818 Reactor safety
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1994
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB132138500
Subject index codes   :FIS (NUCLEAR FISSION)
       SAF (SAFETY)
 
