COMMUNITY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE ON INDUSTRIAL RISK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199310940
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :COMMUNITY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE ON INDUSTRIAL RISK :
       LESSONS  LEARNED FROM EMERGENCIES AFTER ACCIDENTS IN FRANCE INVOLVING
       DANGEROUS SUBSTANCES
Author                :BRETTE B
       LEQUIME B
       BESNARD J C
Affiliation           :SNPE INGENIERIE/RESEAU EURISYS (FR)
       SNPE INGENIERIE/RESEAU EURISYS (FR)
       SAMEX SECURITE (FR)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15059 EN (1993) 84 PP., FS, ECU 10 ISBN
       92-826-5654-3  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The purpose of this work is to draw on lessons that
       are  of general interest to the Community member states regarding the
       emergency  action  taken in the case of accidents in France involving
       dangerous  substances,  in  both fixed installations and in transport
       activities.   The  first  part  of  the  study  report  outlines  the
       organisation  of  the  people  involved  in  preparing and setting up
       emergency operations and the corresponding regulated provisions.
       Especially  the  case  of  ground  activities has been considered, as
       particular  provisions  apply to underground storage. The second part
       describes eleven accidents which occurred in France which were chosen
       for their instructive character regarding emergency action. The third
       part proposes lessons and makes recommendations derived from analysis
       of  these  accidents and the many contacts made with different public
       organisations, experts and operators within the field of this work.
Facet codes           :001 Documentation and information science
       312 Safety engineering
