<TITLE>
COMPARISON OF ROAD ACCIDENTS DURING TRANSPORT OF
DANGEROUS GOODS IN FRANCE, ITALY AND GERMANY
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210650
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :COMPARISON OF ROAD ACCIDENTS DURING TRANSPORT OF
       DANGEROUS      GOODS     IN     FRANCE,     ITALY     AND     GERMANY
Author                :FACCHINI A
       BROCKHOFF L H
Affiliation           :POLITECNICO DI MILANO, DIPARTIMENTO DI INGEGNERIA
       NUCLEARE (IT)
       TECHNICAL  UNIVERSITY OF DENMARK, DEPARTMENT OF CHEMICAL ENGINEERING,
       LYNGBY (DK)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: TRANSPORTING DANGEROUS GOODS BY
       ROAD:  SAFETY  AND ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION, KARLSTAD (SE), JUNE 2-4,
       1992   AVAILABLE   FROM   EUROPEAN   COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920
       LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 36592 ORA
Abstract              :Two interesting studies related to the transport of
       dangerous  goods  have  been  carried  out  in Italy and Germany. The
       Italian  study  is based on accidents on road and rail occurring from
       1985  -  1988,  and approximately 250 accidents have been included in
       the  analysis.  The German study covers road accidents with dangerous
       goods from 1982 - 1984 and includes approximately 350 accidents.
       Furthermore,  the  French  Ministry for the Environment has published
       very  extensive  accident  lists for the years 1987 - 1990, including
       more  than  2000 accidents with hazardous materials, both in relation
       to  transportation  and fixed installations. The paper analyses these
       studies  in depth and attempts to give an overview of the differences
       and  similarities  between the three countries. Available data on the
       volume  of  material transported are presented. The number of serious
       accidents  in  the  three  countries  is  estimated  and subsequently
       normalised  according  to  kilometres driven with dangerous goods per
       year.  The  differences and similarities are discussed and an attempt
       is made to extrapolate the findings to the entire European Community.
Facet codes           :314 Transportation
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB130122100
