<TITLE>
EXTRACTION OF LESSONS LEARNED FROM ACCIDENT DATA
BASES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210460
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :EXTRACTION OF LESSONS LEARNED FROM ACCIDENT DATA
       BASES
Author                :DROGARIS G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: WORKSHOP ON THE PREVENTION OF
       ACCIDENTS  INVOLVING  HAZARDOUS  SUBSTANCES, TOKYO (JP), APRIL 22-26,
       1991   AVAILABLE   FROM   EUROPEAN   COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920
       LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 36708 ORA
Abstract              :Accidents registered in FACTS, MHIDAS, SONATA, and
       EPA databases are compared by type, by country and by gravity index.
       Many  accidents are included in only one or two of the databases, and
       even  where  an  accident  is  common  to several databases there are
       differences in the reported data, partly caused by the lack of common
       agreement on precise definitions of terms such as injury or cause.
       Environmental damage is often ignored as an important consequence.
       The 98 accidents in the MARS database are also analysed.
