<HEAD>
<TITLE>
BENCHMARK EXERCISE ON MAJOR HAZARD ANALYSIS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210541
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :BENCHMARK EXERCISE ON MAJOR HAZARD ANALYSIS
Note                  :VOL. 2 - PART I AND PART II : SUMMARY CONTRIBUTIONS
       OF PARTICIPANTS
Author                :CONTINI S (EDITOR)
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13597 EN (1992) VOL. 2: PART 1, 405 PP.; PART 2,
       475  PP.,  MF, ECU 36, BLOW-UP COPY ECU 132 (FOR BOTH VOLUMES) OFFICE
       FOR   OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN  COMMUNITIES,  L-2985
       LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The Joint Research Centre of the European Community
       has  organised a benchmark exercise on major hazard analysis with the
       aim  of assessing the state of the art in risk analysis. The exercise
       was  performed by 11 teams representing control authorities, research
       organisations, engineering companies and industry. As reference plant
       for  the  exercise, an existing ammonia storage plant was considered,
       but  located in an hypothetical site. The project was subdivided into
       two  phases.  The  first  phase  was  aimed at comparing the existing
       approaches  to  risk  analysis,  from hazard identification up to the
       calculation  of  the  individual  risk contours. The objective of the
       second  phase,  based  on  the  results  of  the  first phase, was to
       identify the single components contributing to the overall difference
       in  the  results. Volume 2 contains summaries of the contributions of
       each individual team to the benchmark exercise, in two parts.
Facet codes           :538 Safety and health at work
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB130110400
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Reference to project  :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
 
