<TITLE>
THE JRC COMPUTER PACKAGE FOR EMERGENCY PRESSURE RELIEF STUDIES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511627
Quality valid. date   :1995-12-12
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :THE JRC COMPUTER PACKAGE FOR EMERGENCY PRESSURE
       RELIEF STUDIES
Author                :DUFFIELD J S
       BRINKHOF N
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: CHEMPUTERS EUROPE II, NOORDWIJK (NL)
        OCTOBER  10-12, 1995 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2,
       L-2920      LUXEMBOURG      AS      PAPER      EN      39339      ORA
Abstract              :The computer package RELIEF has been developed to
       ease  the  task  of  designing  emergency pressure relief systems for
       batch  type reactors commonly used in the chemical industry. The main
       areas  of  application  are:  (i) for the safety engineer, who has to
       ensure the correct functioning of relief systems; (ii) for the design
       engineer,  who has to design new plant and explore the feasibility of
       different  relief  strategies;  (iii) for consequence analysis, where
       RELIEF  can  furnish  a  realistic  time  dependent  source  term for
       dispersion calculations; (iv) for training and educational purposes.
