<TITLE>
SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS USING LYAPUNOV EXPONENTS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511459
Quality valid. date   :1995-11-03
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS USING LYAPUNOV EXPONENTS :
       APPLICATION TO CHEMICAL REACTORS
Author                :STROZZI F
       CALENBUHR V
       ALOS M A
       ZALDIVAR J M
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS OF MODEL OUTPUT
        BELGIRATE  (IT),  SEPTEMBER  25-27,  1995  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 39288 ORA
Abstract              :It is well known that, for certain values of the
       parameters  in  the  mass and energy balance equations that represent
       the  dynamic  behaviour of chemical reactors, the system becomes very
       sensitive  to  the  values  of the initial conditions. Sensitivity to
       initial  conditions  is  a  well-  known  characteristic  of  chaotic
       phenomena.  Local Lyapunov exponents were used in the definition of a
       generalised  sensitivity criterion in the context of single reactions
       in a batch reactor working under isoperibolic conditions i.e.
       constant jacket temperature. In this work, this criterion is extended
       to  cases  where  two  consecutive  or  two  parallel reactions occur
       simultaneously.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1995
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB1346100
Subject index codes   :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
       SAF (SAFETY)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
