<TITLE>
CONTROL OF BATCH REACTORS USING NEURAL NETWORKS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199211040
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :CONTROL OF BATCH REACTORS USING NEURAL NETWORKS
Author                :ZALDIVAR J M
       HERNANDEZ H
       PANETSOS F
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       UNIVERSIDAD CARLOS III DE MADRID, ESCUELA POLITCNICA SUPERIOR (ES)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: CHEMICAL ENGINEERING AND PROCESSING, VOL. 31
       (1992) NO. 3, PP. 173-180
Abstract              :In this article the use of neural networks for
       adaptive  control  of  temperature  in a jacketed vessel, in which an
       exothermic  reaction  takes  place,  is  discussed.  Different neural
       network  architectures  are  compared  against  a  traditional scheme
       through  simulation.  The  results  indicate  that the neural network
       approach  can  be  used  to  deal  with  the  control of these highly
       non-linear batch and semibatch chemical processes.
