<HEAD>
<TITLE>
SAFETY OF CHEMICAL BATCH REACTORS AND STORAGE TANKS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199110707
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :SAFETY OF CHEMICAL BATCH REACTORS AND STORAGE TANKS
Note                  :EURO COURSES : RELIABILITY AND RISK ANALYSIS - VOLUME
       1
Author                :BENUZZI A
       ZALDIVAR J M (EDITORS)
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13457 EN (1991) 439 PP. ISBN 0-7923-1233-3 KLUWER
       ACADEMIC  PUBLISHERS  GROUP,  P.O.  BOX  322,  3300 AH DORDRECHT (NL)
Abstract              :This volume reviews the safety issues relating to
       batch  reactors and storage tanks, with emphasis on the prevention or
       mitigation  of  dangerous  situations  which could lead to thermal or
       pressure  excursions. The case histories of relevant severe accidents
       which  have  occurred  in  the  past are analysed, and current safety
       criteria   and   guidelines   are   illustrated.   Methods   for  the
       characterisation or simulation of chemical systems are considered.
       Particular  interest  is  focussed on runaway reactions; experimental
       techniques  and  aspects  such as instrumentation and control for the
       investigation  of  the  origins  and  causes  of  such  reactions are
       reviewed in depth.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1991
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB129128200
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
