<TITLE>
EMERGENCY PRESSURE RELIEF OF BATCH REACTORS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199011706
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :EMERGENCY PRESSURE RELIEF OF BATCH REACTORS
Author                :BENUZZI A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: FRIENDLY BATCH CHEMICAL PLANTS,
       BARCELONA (ES), SEPT. 25-28, 1990 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION,
       DGXIII/D-2,    L-2920    LUXEMBOURG    AS    PAPER   EN   35727   ORA
Abstract              :This report concerns the safety of batch reactors
       under  runaway  reaction  or external fire conditions. This topic has
       recently  received  increasing attention from the process industries,
       the  media  and public authorities as a consequence of several severe
       accidents  which  have  occurred  in  the  past.  Design  methods for
       adequate   emergency   relief   systems,   including  two-phase  flow
       conditions,  are reviewed. In particular, experimental and analytical
       procedures   concerning   the   in-vessel/venting-line   fluid   flow
       descriptions are presented and discussed.
