<HEAD>
<TITLE>
REVIEW OF ACCIDENTS INVOLVING CHLORINE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199211242
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :REVIEW OF ACCIDENTS INVOLVING CHLORINE
Author                :DROGARIS G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 14444 EN (1992) 100 PP., FS, ECU 10.50 ISBN
       92-826-4403-0  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :This study comprises a review of accidents involving
       chlorine that can be found in various accident data collections.
       Basic  material  has been obtained by interrogating FACTS, MHIDAS and
       SONATA  databases and reviewing the Strflle Handbuch. Other sources
       such as CDCIR bulletins, the EPA acute hazardous events database, the
       accident  inventory  of  the  French  Ministry  of  Environment,  and
       journals  and  text  books  on  safety-related  issues have also been
       utilised.  This  comparison  shows that none of the existing publicly
       accessible  accident  data  collections  includes  all accidents. The
       probability  of  an  accident  being  recorded  in  an  accident data
       collection  increases with the severity of its consequences, but even
       major  accidents can escape recording. In the absence of a structured
       accident  reporting  system there are many difficulties in collecting
       complete  and  accurate  accident  reports.  Therefore there are many
       limitations  that  must  be seriously considered when using data from
       these  sources  for statistical purposes. On the other hand, accident
       databanks   are  extremely  useful  for  identifying  priorities  and
       diffusing the knowledge for effective accident prevention policies.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13115900
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Reference to project  :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
       IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
</PRE>
