NTERPRETATION OF A CHLORINE RELEASE ACCIDENT
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199111209
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :INTERPRETATION OF A CHLORINE RELEASE ACCIDENT
Author                :BENUZZI A
       GUSTIN J L
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       RHNE POULENC INDUSTRIALISATION, DECINES (FR)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: DIERS USERS GROUP MEETING, TORONTO
       (CA),   SEPT.   25-27,   1991  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN  COMMISSION,
       DGXIII/D-2,    L-2920    LUXEMBOURG    AS    PAPER   EN   36352   ORA
Abstract              :The computer code SAFIRE, developed by DIERS, has
       been  used  for  the  simulation of a chlorine release accident which
       produced the loss of 20,000 kg of material. The data available on the
       accident   were   sufficient   to  define  the  input  for  the  code
       calculations.  The  SAFIRE simulation of the accident was found to be
       adequate   for  a  satisfactory  reproduction  of  all  the  measured
       quantities.
