<TITLE>
THE EUROPEANS TRY THE CONE CALORIMETER FOR EVALUATING THE FIRE SAFETY OF FURNITURE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199512097
Quality valid. date   :1996-01-15
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :THE EUROPEANS TRY THE CONE CALORIMETER FOR EVALUATING
       THE FIRE SAFETY OF FURNITURE
Author                :WICKSTROM U
       SUNDSTROM B
Affiliation           :SP FIRE TECHNOLOGY, BORAAS (SE)
       SP FIRE TECHNOLOGY, BORAAS (SE)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON FIRE
       SAFETY,  ORLANDO  (US),  MARCH  19-22,  1995  AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 39614 ORA
Abstract              :This publication discusses the Commission of the
       European  Community  draft directive on fire behaviour of upholstered
       furniture. To promote the development of a relevant evaluation method
        the  European Commission has funded a research programme called CBUF
       (combustion behaviour of upholstered furniture) with the objective of
       providing   scientific   and   technical   support   for  performance
       requirements.  The  main  objective of the CBUF project is to develop
       means of evaluating upholstered furniture in full scale as well as in
       small  scale.  Eleven laboratories from 8 counties participate in the
       project,  which  is expected to be completed during the first half of
       1995. Principals have been developed to test and evaluate components,
       fabrics  and cushion materials, separately or in combinations thereof
       (composites). The results are presented here.
