<HEAD>
<TITLE>
COMPILER'S GUIDE FOR THE PREPARATION OF INTERNATIONAL
CHEMICAL SAFETY CARDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199311676
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :COMPILER'S GUIDE FOR THE PREPARATION OF INTERNATIONAL
       CHEMICAL SAFETY CARDS
Note                  :FIRST REVISION
Author                :CEC
       IPCS
Affiliation           :CEC LUXEMBOURG (LU)
       IPCS,  DIVISION  OF  ENVIRONMENTAL HEALTH, WORLD HEALTH ORGANISATION,
       GENVE (CH)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 14410/1 EN (1993) 111 PP., FS, ECU 12 ISBN
       92-826-3697-6  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The International Chemical Safety Cards (ICSCs)
       project  is an undertaking of the International Programme on Chemical
       Safety.  ICSCs  summarise  essential health and safety information on
       chemical substances. This publication lists the standard phrases used
       to  prepare  ICSCs  as  well  as  the procedures and criteria used to
       select  them.  The  standard phrases are used to describe the various
       characteristics  of  a  chemical, the hazards associated with its use
       and  the  ways in which it should be packaged and handled in order to
       prevent  problems  to human health and the environment. Each standard
       phrase  is  allocated  a  five-digit  number  which  facilitates  the
       preparation  of  ICSCs  on  computer and simplifies the production of
       cards in different languages.
Facet codes           :530 Industrial health and safety in general
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1993
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13236400
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
 
