       International  Chemical Safety Cards (ICSCs). The ICSCs have no legal
       status,  but  should be seen as an informative tool which can be used
       by interested parties, whether the worker himself or the employer.
       The  ICSCs  have  a special role to play in this respect in small and
       medium  sized enterprises. The ICSCs and the Compiler's guide contain
       the  collective views of the IPCS Peer Review Committee. They may not
       reflect  in  all  cases  all  the  detailed  requirements included in
       national  legislation  on  the  subject.  The user should, therefore,
       verify   compliance   of   the   cards  with  the  relevant  detailed
       requirements in the country of use.
