<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ADREA-HF
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210031
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :ADREA-HF : A THREE-DIMENSIONAL FINITE VOLUME CODE FOR
       VAPOUR       CLOUD       DISPERSION      IN      COMPLEX      TERRAIN
Note                  :FINAL REPORT
Author                :BARTZIS J G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13580 EN (1991) 62 PP., MF, ECU 4, BLOW-UP COPY
       ECU   10.50   OFFICE   FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The computer program ADREA-HF is a special version of
       the  ADREA  code  under  development in NCSR Demokritos (Greece). The
       latter  is specifically designed for buoyant flows in complex domains
       and  has been applied to atmospheric transport and thermal hydraulics
       of   closed  systems.  The  present  version  of  the  ADREA-HF  code
       represents  the first iteration in vapour cloud dispersion prediction
       under  complex  environmental  conditions.  It is based on the finite
       volume concept in a Cartesian coordinate system. Treatment of complex
       domains  is  achieved  by  allowing  a  boundary surface of arbitrary
       irregularity  to  cross  a  calculation  cell.  In  this  report  the
       theoretical  basis  of the code is discussed in detail. A description
       of  the  code  is also given, together with the necessary information
       for the use of the code.
Facet codes           :206 Meteorology and climatology
       523 Atmospheric pollution
       538 Safety and health at work
