<TITLE>
TOWARDS GUIDELINES ON THE EFFECTIVE PROVISION OF
PUBLIC INFORMATION ON MAJOR INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENT HAZARDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199110711
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :TOWARDS GUIDELINES ON THE EFFECTIVE PROVISION OF
       PUBLIC    INFORMATION    ON   MAJOR   INDUSTRIAL   ACCIDENT   HAZARDS
Note                  :AN EXECUTIVE SUMMARY OF A WORKSHOP HELD IN LONDON,
       19-20 MARCH 1990
Author                :PELTU M
       GOW H B F
Affiliation           :INFORMATICS ASSOCIATES, LONDON (GB)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13214 EN (1991) 12 PP., MF, ECU 4, BLOW-UP COPY
       ECU  5  OFFICE FOR OFFICIAL PUBLICATIONS OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES,
       L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :A study has been carried out to provide an empirical
       evaluation of public information on major industrial accident hazards
       in  the  EC,  focussing  particularly on public responses to relevant
       communications. The JRC Ispra organised a workshop to use the study's
       interim  findings  as  a  basis  for  examining  the  feasibility  of
       developing  appropriate guidelines in relation to the Amended Article
       8  of  the Seveso Directive. The main objectives of the workshop were
       to:  -  describe  and analyse the information campaigns which are the
       subject  of  the study; - discuss these results among the researchers
       and  invited  experts,  and  -  use this study's interim findings and
       other  related  research  and  experience  to  consider  the proposed
       European code of good practice.
