<HEAD>
<TITLE>
A TOP DOWN APPROACH TO FAULT TREE ANALYSIS USING BINARY DECISION DIAGRAMS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511315
Quality valid. date   :1995-11-23
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :A TOP DOWN APPROACH TO FAULT TREE ANALYSIS USING
       BINARY DECISION DIAGRAMS
Author                :CONTINI S
       DE COLA G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       INFOCON, LAVAGNA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: EUROPEAN JOURNAL OF DIAGNOSIS AND SAFETY IN
       AUTOMATION (1995)
Abstract              :This paper describes an efficient method for
       determining the significant minimal cut sets of complex fault trees.
       It  is based on a top-down approach applied to a segmented fault tree
       obtained by means of the repeated identification of pseudo modules.
       The  efficiency  of  this  method is largely due to the use of binary
       decision diagrams as data structure. A prototype computer program was
       produced  by  modifying  part  of  Ispra-FTA  in  order  to prove the
       convenience of modifying existing software for fault tree analysis to
       produce   more   powerful   tools.  For  non-monotonic  functions  an
       approximated  solution  is  proposed  that is acceptable in practical
       applications.  The  type of quantitative analysis than can be made is
       briefly  shown  in  graphical  form. Finally, the extraction from the
       graph  of  significant  minimal  cut  sets  by  setting not uncertain
       thresholds is presented.
Facet codes           :720 IT application technologies
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1995
Publication type      :ART An article in a journal
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13413300
Subject index codes   :IPS (INFORMATION PROCESSING, INFORMATION SYSTEMS)
 
