<TITLE>
FIRE ENDURANCE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :198910574
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :FIRE ENDURANCE : ANALYTICAL PREDICTION OF PRESTRESSED
       CONCRETE BEAMS
Author                :FLOREANI F
       INZAGHI A
Affiliation           :UNIVERSIT DI UDINE (IT)
       JRC ISPRA ESTAB. (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: ABAQUS SECOND ANNUAL USERS'
       CONFERENCE,  STRESA  (IT),  MAY  24-26,  1989 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 34709 ORA
Abstract              :As the Italian Building Code does not include fire
       safety  in prestressed beams, the prefabrication industry cannot make
       experimental  tests  on  high load beams in furnaces. A prediction of
       fire  endurance  is needed. A developed analytical model has obtained
       the  approval of the Control Institute, whilst waiting for a preprint
       of the new code for fire resistance developed by Unification National
       Institute, Milan. The model chosen is a thermo-mechanical analysis of
       fire  response.  Prediction of fire endurance of prestressed concrete
       beams in non-linear materials is achieved by a finite element method,
       using ABAQUS.
Facet codes           :303 Construction: equipment- methods and materials
