<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ENQUIRY INTO THE ROLE OF STEEL STRUCTURES IN FIRES IN INDUSTRIAL BUILDINGS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :198910091
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :ENQUIRY INTO THE ROLE OF STEEL STRUCTURES IN FIRES IN
       INDUSTRIAL BUILDINGS
Author                :KRUPPA J
Affiliation           :C.T.I.C.M., PUTEAUX (FR)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 11493 EN (1988) OFFICE FOR OFFICIAL PUBLICATIONS
       OF      THE      EUROPEAN      COMMUNITIES,     L-2985     LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The various fire safety measures may have an
       important  bearing  on  the  building  and  exploitation  costs. This
       especially  holds  if  substantial  requirements  are set to the fire
       resistance  of steel buildings, since such requirements normally will
       call  for  expensive  fire  protection  on  the steel structure. With
       respect  to the ability of the various fire safety measures to reduce
       the loss due to fire, no systematic information is available.
       Nevertheless,  in circles of fire insurance, a trend becomes manifest
       to  emphasize  the  significance  of  the fire resistance of the load
       bearing structure in the premium rate system. Especially for low rise
       industrial  steel  buildings,  which at present are often realized in
       unprotected steel, this will have serious financial consequences.
       Therefore, it has been decided - both in France and The Netherlands -
       to  carry out a field survey on the role of steel structures in fires
       in  low  rise industrial buildings. Although the two surveys have the
       same  scope,  they  are  not identical. This paper describes the main
       results of both studies.
