<TITLE>
THE EUROPEAN COMMISSION'S RESEARCH PROGRAMME ON THE POST IGNITION FIRE BEHAVIOUR
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199310094
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE EUROPEAN COMMISSION'S RESEARCH PROGRAMME ON THE
       POST    IGNITION    FIRE    BEHAVIOUR    OF   UPHOLSTERED   FURNITURE
Author                :GOULD D
       FAIRLEY T
Affiliation           :CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
       CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: 3RD EUROPEAN CONFERENCE ON FURNITURE
       FLAMMABILITY,   BRUXELLES  (BE),  NOV.  24-25,  1992  AVAILABLE  FROM
       EUROPEAN  COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 37275
       ORA
Abstract              :The CEC is undertaking a programme of pre-normative
       research on the post-ignition fire behaviour of upholstered furniture
        in order to develop suitable test methods for a future Directive. In
       particular  the  work  relates  to  the  application  of  the  Second
       Essential Requirement of this Directive. Small scale, large scale and
       room  tests will be carried out on a wide range of different types of
       furniture,  and  the  results  linked  by  fire  modelling. The final
       objective is the capability to predict the results of room tests from
       the  results  of  small  scale  tests  on  furniture  materials.  The
       programme  will  also  provide a series of well documented, validated
       databases against which future fire models can be tested.
