<HEAD>
<TITLE>
INTERCOMPARATIVE TESTS OF CALIBRATION DEVICES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199310751
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :INTERCOMPARATIVE TESTS OF CALIBRATION DEVICES FOR
       RADIANT HEAT FLUX METERS
Author                :OLSSON S
Affiliation           :SP FIRE TECHNOLOGY, BORAS (SE)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 14400 EN (1993) 42 PP., MF, ECU 4 OFFICE FOR
       OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :SP in Sweden and the Fire Research Station (FRS) in
       England  have  performed  an  intercomparative  calibration  on  four
       different radiometers, to investigate the differences between the two
       different calibration methods. The intercomparison was the first step
       in  a  tentative  research  project  with  the goal of establishing a
       common  European  system  for  the  calibration  of thermal radiation
       meters  for fire research purposes. FRS performed the calibrations in
       an  open  configuration  equipment  against  a  reference  thermopile
       radiometer, whilst SP used a semiclosed arrangement with a black body
       cavity  as  radiation  source.  The  calibrations  were  made for two
       radiation  flux  ranges,  20  and  50  kW/m2,  and  with  Gardon  and
       Schmidt-Boelter  type  radiometers.  The  study shows that there is a
       difference  in results of up to nearly 8 % in relative terms. As this
       difference  is  of the same order as the combined error limits of the
       calibrations,  it  could have been explained, had it been of a random
       nature. It seems, however, as if the difference is systematic.
Facet codes           :315 Test facilities and methods
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1993
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB131131800
Subject index codes   :MEA (MEASUREMENT METHODS)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
</PRE>
