<TITLE>
THE ARIPAR PROJECT
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410624
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE ARIPAR PROJECT : ANALYSIS OF THE INDUSTRIAL AND
       TRANSPORTATION    RISK    CONNECTED    WITH    THE    RAVENNA    AREA
Author                :EGIDI D
       FORABOSCHI F P
       SPADONI G
       AMENDOLA A
Affiliation           :CIVIL PROTECTION OF THE EMILIA ROMAGNA REGION,
       BOLOGNA (IT)
       UNIVERSITY OF BOLOGNA, CHEMICAL ENGINEERING DEPARTMENT (IT)
       UNIVERSITY OF BOLOGNA, CHEMICAL ENGINEERING DEPARTMENT (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: PSAM II, SAN DIEGO (US), MARCH 20-24
        1994   AVAILABLE   FROM   EUROPEAN  COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920
       LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 38055 ORA
Abstract              :This paper describes the main results of the ARIPAR
       project  which assessed the major sources of accident risks connected
       with   the   processing,  storage  and  transportation  of  dangerous
       substances on the Ravenna industrial and harbour area. The assessment
       work  was  undertaken in order to plan for urban development, to plan
       for  the  improvement  of  transport infrastructure so as to diminish
       possible  accident  risks,  and  to evaluate the compatibility of new
       industrial  developments  with  existing land use. Risk contours have
       been  derived for each hazard source category and used to analyse the
       overall risk situation.
Facet codes           :007 Safety
       314 Transportation
       538 Safety and health at work
