<TITLE>
A METHODOLOGICAL FRAMEWORK FOR ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS OF
HUMAN ERRORS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410779
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :A METHODOLOGICAL FRAMEWORK FOR ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS OF
       HUMAN ERRORS
Author                :PEDRALI M
       COJAZZI G
Affiliation           :CENTRE NATIONAL DE LA RECHERCHE SCIENTIFIQUE,
       ARAMIIHS, TOULOUSE (FR)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: 21ST CONFERENCE ON AVIATION
       PSYCHOLOGY  :  DEVELOPING THEORY AND EXTENDING PRACTICE, DUBLIN (IE),
       MARCH  28-31,  1994  AVAILABLE  FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2,
       L-2920      LUXEMBOURG      AS      PAPER      EN      38355      ORA
Abstract              :The methodology proposed for the root cause analysis
       (RCA) of human errors enables the incorrect behaviour of operators to
       be  detected and the possible causes to be identified. It is based on
       a  paradigm  of  human behaviour and a taxonomy for human errors. The
       use  of  the  paradigm is important to detect the causes of cognitive
       errors,  whereas  the  use  of a taxonomy is essential to distinguish
       between internal and external causes affecting human performances.
       The   theoretical   formalisation   of   the   methodology   for  the
       retrospective analysis of incidents/accidents is presented.
