<HEAD>
<TITLE>
A DYNAMIC RELIABILITY TECHNIQUE FOR ERROR ASSESSMENT
IN MAN-MACHINE SYSTEMS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199310921
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :A DYNAMIC RELIABILITY TECHNIQUE FOR ERROR ASSESSMENT
       IN MAN-MACHINE SYSTEMS
Author                :CACCIABUE P C
       CARPIGNANO A
       VIVALDA C
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       POLITECNICO DI TORINO, DIPARTIMENTO DI ENERGETICA (IT)
       POLITECNICO DI TORINO, DIPARTIMENTO DI ENERGETICA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF MAN-MACHINE STUDIES
       (1993) NO. 38, PP. 403-428
Abstract              :A methodology still under development, named DREAMS
       (Dynamic  Reliability  technique  for Error Assessment in Man-machine
       Systems),  is  dedicated to human reliability analysis and identifies
       the origin of human errors in the dynamic interaction of the operator
       and  the  plant  control  system.  In the proposed methodology, human
       behaviour  depends  on  the working environment in which the operator
       acts and on his psychological conditions, which are related to stress
        emotional  factors  and  fixation,  as  well as to lack of intrinsic
       knowledge. As a logical consequence of the dynamic interaction of the
       human  with the plant under control, either the error tendency or the
       ability  to  recover  from  a critical situation may be enhanced. The
       probability  of  erroneous actions and of recovery is thus a function
       of  a  generic  stress-in-action  correlation,  which  represents the
       effect of the internal-external worlds on the operator behaviour.
       This  leads  to  the evaluation of instantaneous human error/recovery
       probabilities  (IHEP and IHRP) which are dynamically evaluated during
       the  unfolding  of the sequence of the man-machine interaction. These
       can  then  be  used  for evaluating an overall probability measure of
       plant  safety  related  to  human  erroneous actions. A study case of
       applications of the methodology to a control system of a real nuclear
       power plant is given.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
       711 Knowledge engineering (including AI and
       818 Reactor safety
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1993
Publication type      :ART An article in a journal
Euroabstracts number  :EAB131144100
Programme acronym     :JRC-REACTSAFE 6C
Reference to project  :JRC-REACTSAFE 6C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
       IPS (INFORMATION PROCESSING, INFORMATION SYSTEMS)
       FIS (NUCLEAR FISSION)
 
