<TITLE>
ENVIRONMENTAL AND HUMAN EFFECTS OF ACCIDENTS WITH
HAZARDOUS MATERIALS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199211023
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :ENVIRONMENTAL AND HUMAN EFFECTS OF ACCIDENTS WITH
       HAZARDOUS MATERIALS
Original title        :MILJO - OG HUMANE EFFEKTER VED WHELD MED FARLIGE
       STOFFER
Note                  :PILOTUNDERSOGELSE AF UHELD I FRANKRIG 1987-1989
Author                :HAASTRUP P
       RASMUSSEN K
       BROCKHOFF L
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: DANSK KEMI (1991) NO. 11, PP. 396-400
Abstract              :The number of French accidents with hazardous
       materials  in  1987,  1988  and 1989 has been analysed with regard to
       evaluating the severity of the environmental and human effects of the
       accidents.  A  total  of 1538 descriptions of accidents are available
       and  626  of  these  are considered relevant. There are 456 accidents
       with   environmental   consequences  and  201  accidents  with  human
       consequences   (including   31   accidents   with   both   human  and
       environmental  consequences).  During  that period of time there were
       more than twice as many environmental accidents as human accidents.
       If  the  number  of  dead persons is used as the indicator for severe
       accidents with human consequences and the threshold value of severity
       is  fixed  at  a  death,  there  were  27 severe accidents with human
       consequences  in  the  said period of time or 12%. For the purpose of
       evaluating  the  severity  of  the  environmental accidents, a method
       based  on expert statements has been drawn up and the method has been
       tested  by  the  authors.  Using  this  method  for the evaluation of
       severity,  the severe environmental accidents amount to 46 out of 456
       or 10%.
