<TITLE>
COMMON CAUSE FAILURES AND HUMAN FACTORS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511311
Quality valid. date   :1995-11-23
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :COMMON CAUSE FAILURES AND HUMAN FACTORS
Author                :CACCIABUE P C
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: ESREDA GUIDEBOOK, CHAPTER 5 (1994) PP. 1-10
Abstract              :The main objective of the Human Reliability
       Assessment (HRA) is the identification and quantification of the most
       relevant  human-machine  interactions affecting the development of an
       incidental   sequence.   The  quantification  is  made  in  terms  of
       probabilities   and   frequencies  of  occurrence  of  unsuccessfully
       performed  tasks/missions,  due  to inappropriate or inadequate human
       behaviour.  In  the Probabilistic Safety Assessment (PSA) of a plant,
       the  probabilities of a mission failure are usually combined with the
       probabilities  of  a  system  failure in order to achieve the overall
       reliability  evaluation  of  the  man-machine system for well-defined
       initiating events and accident progression scenarios.
