<HEAD>
<TITLE>
A HUMAN FACTOR METHODOLOGY FOR SAFETY ASSESSMENT
BASED ON THE DYLAM APPROACH
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199311572
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :A HUMAN FACTOR METHODOLOGY FOR SAFETY ASSESSMENT
       BASED ON THE DYLAM APPROACH
Author                :CACCIABUE P C
       COJAZZI G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: SMIRT 12 POST-CONFERENCE SEMINAR NO.
       15  ON  CURRENT  ISSUES  IN  PSA, HEIDELBERG (DE), AUGUST 23-24, 1993
       AVAILABLE  FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS
       PAPER EN 37778 ORA
Abstract              :This paper discusses how human factors can be
       included  in  a  probabilistic  safety  study.  During incidents, the
       effect  of the plant dynamic evolution and component failure can lead
       to   non-intuitive   configuration   of  the  system  and,  when  the
       interaction  of the operator and the control and protection system is
       taken  into account, the overall scenario of the safety study becomes
       particularly  complex.  These  problems  demand  the use of a dynamic
       reliability   methodology   technique   and  the  development  of  an
       appropriate  model  of human behaviour to be coupled to a taxonomy of
       erroneous  actions.  These were carried out by the DYLAM approach and
       by  a number of modelling architectures of operator simulation, which
       were  coupled  for the development of a dynamic methodology for human
       factors analysis. A simple application is illustrated by the study of
       the  control  of  an  auxiliary  feedwater  system  during incidental
       conditions.
Facet codes           :818 Reactor safety
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1993
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13225700
Programme acronym     :JRC-REACTSAFE 6C
Reference to project  :JRC-REACTSAFE 6C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :FIS (NUCLEAR FISSION)
 
