<TITLE>
MODELLING MAN-MACHINE SYSTEMS FOR PLANTS SAFETY
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199010926
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :MODELLING MAN-MACHINE SYSTEMS FOR PLANTS SAFETY : THE
       ROLE OF COGNITIVE APPROACHES
Author                :CACCIABUE P C
       MANCINI G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: CONFERENCE ON HUMAN RELIABILITY IN
       NUCLEAR  POWER, LONDON (GB), OCT. 19-20, 1989 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 35178 ORA
Abstract              :Ongoing research at JRC-Ispra on the simulation of
       man-machine interaction is reviewed, with particular reference to the
       past  experience  of  system  modelling  and  to  the advances of the
       technological   world.   These   require  the  coalescence  of  mixed
       disciplines  covering  the  fields  of  engineering,  psychology  and
       sociology.  The  complexity  of  man-machine  systems with respect to
       safety  analysis  is  depicted.  The  role  and position of cognitive
       models  with  respect  to  more  "classical",  engineering orientated
       methodologies, like the human reliability techniques, are discussed.
       The  approach  proposed at JRC for studying in detail the interaction
       of complex man-machine systems is the System Response Analyser, which
       links   together   contributions   from  three  analytical  tools:  a
       quasi-classical  simulation of the actual plant, a cognitive model of
       the  operator  activities  and  a driver model. These three tools are
       briefly described.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1989
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB12891200
Programme acronym     :JRC-REACTSAFE 5C
Reference to project  :JRC-REACTSAFE 5C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :FIS (NUCLEAR FISSION)
