<HEAD>
<TITLE>
THE EURO-QUEBEC HYDRO-HYDROGEN PILOT PROJECT (EQHHPP)
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199110799
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE EURO-QUEBEC HYDRO-HYDROGEN PILOT PROJECT (EQHHPP)
       :  HYDROGEN,  AN  ENERGY  VECTOR  WITHIN A CLEAN AND RENEWABLE ENERGY
       SYSTEM
Author                :GIACOMAZZI G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: SECOND ANNUAL U.S. HYDROGEN MEETING
       -  HYDROGEN  APPLICATIONS  FOR  A SUSTAINABLE FUTURE, ARLINGTON (US),
       MARCH  13-15,  1991  AVAILABLE  FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2,
       L-2920      LUXEMBOURG      AS      PAPER      EN      36031      ORA
Abstract              :The concept of a hydrogen-based, clean, renewable
       energy  system  is  currently  investigated  by European and Canadian
       industries  and  the  JRC  Ispra.  The  100  MW  pilot  project is to
       demonstrate  the  provision  of clean and renewable primary energy in
       the  form  of  Canadian  hydropower  converted  via electrolysis into
       hydrogen  and  shipped  to  Europe,  where  it  is stored and used in
       different  ways:  electricity/heat cogeneration, vehicle and aviation
       propulsion and hydrogen enrichment of natural gas for use in industry
       and  households. Two transport/storage modes are investigated: liquid
       hydrogen  shipped  in  special  LH(2)  ships and methylcyclohexane as
       energy carrier shipped in normal product carriers. The costs of LH(2)
        produced  with  hydropower at 2 cents ECU/kWh, shipped to Europe and
       stored  in  the  port  of  Hamburg,  have  been evaluated at 15 cents
       ECU/kWh  (Reference case). Considerations are made of safety factors,
       the environment, costs, users and the European hydrogen market.
Facet codes           :408 Secondary energy vectors (gas- electricity etc)
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1991
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB129129500
Subject index codes   :EST (ENERGY STORAGE, ENERGY TRANSPORT)
 
