<TITLE>
DEVELOPMENT OF SEABORNE HYDROGEN TRANSPORTATION
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199011492
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :DEVELOPMENT OF SEABORNE HYDROGEN TRANSPORTATION
Author                :GIACOMAZZI G
       KRAPP R
       ROMAHN K
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       GERMANISCHER LLOYD, HAMBURG (DE)
       THYSSEN NORDSEEWERKE, EMDEN (DE)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: INTERNATIONALES SONNENFORUM,
       FRANKFURT (DE), OCTOBER 9-12, 1990 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION
        DGXIII/D-2,    L-2920    LUXEMBOURG    AS   PAPER   EN   35578   ORA
Abstract              :The problem of intercontinental seaborne hydrogen
       transportation  is  presented  in  the  framework  of the Euro-Quebec
       Hydro-Hydrogen   Pilot  Project.  The  characteristics  of  different
       hydrogen  vectors  are  studied  in connection with the relevant ship
       type  and  ship  design.  The  techno-economic aspects as well as the
       safety  and interfacial aspects are evaluated. Several ship types are
       examined:  liquid  hydrides  carriers  and  liquid  hydrogen carriers
       (ballasted  with  water,  fuel for propulsion or liquid hydride). The
       Liquid  Hydrogen  Barge  Carrier is discussed and the characteristics
       and advantages of this type of ship are described.
