       92-826-7009-0  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :This report describes work undertaken into the
       hazards  posed  by the release of pressurised liquefied gas. The four
       main  areas of the work are as follows: (i) conditions of a vessel up
       to  failure of containment; (ii) conditions within a vessel following
       partial failure; (iii) characteristics of discharge following partial
       failure; (iv) characteristics of discharge following complete failure
        Executive  summaries  for the individual projects are provided which
       give details of the work performed and conclusions drawn.
