<TITLE>
COMPARISON OF SELECTED LPG RELATED CODES AND
STANDARDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199310431
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :COMPARISON OF SELECTED LPG RELATED CODES AND
       STANDARDS
Author                :HARRIS S
       KEMP P
       TAIT D
       CERDA H W
Affiliation           :FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON
       (GB)
       FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON (GB)
       FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON (GB)
       FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON (GB)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 14636 EN (1992) 150 PP., FS, ECU 15 ISBN
       92-826-4737-4  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The current study compares in some depth certain key
       aspects  of  LPG  plant  design  (pressure  vessels, piping, pressure
       relief valves, hazardous area classification and water spray systems)
        LPG  regulations  and  codes themselves, as well as the more general
       codes and standards applicable also to LPG installations are examined
       in detail. Existing European codes and standards are compared to each
       other and to ones in the US. In view of the wish within the Community
       for  enhanced harmonisation, CEN has already initiated, among others,
       the   CEN/TC   286   programme   aiming   at   the  unified  European
       standardisation  of  all  pressure  equipment  and transport pressure
       equipment for LPG, including associated accessories. This comparative
       study  clearly  identifies priorities for action and it is hoped that
       it  will  be  a  useful  tool for authorities, industry and all other
       bodies  and  persons  working  towards  safety  in handling hazardous
       substances.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1992
