<TITLE>
COMMUNITY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE ON INDUSTRIAL RISK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210282
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :COMMUNITY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE ON INDUSTRIAL RISK :
       COMPARISON OF LPG-RELATED REGULATIONS
Author                :HARRIS S
       ARREGGER J E
       TRBOJERIC V M
       COX R A
Affiliation           :FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON
       (GB)
       FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON (GB)
       FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON (GB)
       FOUR ELEMENTS INDUSTRIAL SAFETY CONSULTANTS, LONDON (GB)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13699 EN (1991) 358 PP., FS, ECU 30 ISBN
       92-826-3246-6  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The Community Documentation Centre on Industrial Risk
       has  as its objectives the collection of safety related documentation
       and the production of review publications. Studies on lessons learned
       from  major  accidents  in  the  Community  member countries, lessons
       learned after emergencies and a comparison of the national approaches
       to  the safety report have already been published. This volume is the
       first  to compare regulations and guidelines for handling and storing
       a specific substance - LPG. LPG is a dangerous substance according to
       the definitions given in the SEVESO-Directive. Its selection does not
       imply  that  it  is  more  dangerous than any of the other substances
       either  listed  in  Annexes  II  and  III, or classified as dangerous
       according  to  the  criteria of Annex IV of this Directive. It mainly
       reflects  the  fact  that  it  is  widely used all over the Community
       (installations handling or storing LPG covered by the requirements of
       the  SEVESO-Directive  are  to be found in all member countries) and,
       consequently,  is  involved very frequently in accidents, as shown in
       the review of the accidents notified up to now in MARS.
Facet codes           :004 Law and regulations
       538 Safety and health at work
Availability in lang  :en English
