<TITLE>
THE EUROPEAN OIL AND GAS CONFERENCE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199111498
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE EUROPEAN OIL AND GAS CONFERENCE : A
       MULTIDISCIPLINARY   APPROACH   IN   EXPLORATION  AND  PRODUCTION  R&D
Note                  :PROCEEDINGS OF THE CONFERENCE HELD IN ALTAVILLA
       MILICIA    (PALERMO,    SICILY,    ITALY),    9-12    OCTOBER    1990
Author                :IMARISIO G
       FRIAS M
       BEMTGEN J M (EDITORS)
Affiliation           :CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
       CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
       CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13793 EN (1991) 602 PP. ISBN 1-85333-622-X GRAHAM
       AND  TROTMAN  LTD.,  STERLING  HOUSE, 66 WILTON ROAD, LONDON SW1V 1DE
       (GB)
Abstract              :The purpose of the European Oil and Gas Conference
       was  to cover multidisciplinary aspects of research and technological
       development  in  hydrocarbon  discovery  and  exploitation. The areas
       covered  by  the conference were information processing, geosciences,
       mechanics and new materials, gas conversion and operations.
       Information  processing  is fundamental to exploration technology and
       is featured as one of the larger sessions, with papers extending from
       the  use  of  seismic  velocity  anomalies  to  the  development of a
       hydrocarbon  potential  forecasting  system.  The geosciences session
       ranged   from  the  numerical  modelling  of  sedimentary  basins  to
       uncertainty  reduction in gas reservoir sizing. The mechanics and new
       materials  session  ranged  in  scope  from  drilling systems through
       hostile  well completions to unmanned platforms. The rise in resource
       importance  of  remote  gas  accumulations  was  acknowledged  with a
       session  on  the conversion of natural gas to liquids. The operations
       session primarily featured environmental and safety issues.
