<TITLE>
COMPRESSIBLE GAS-LIQUID FLOW THROUGH PIPELINE
RESTRICTIONS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199211324
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :COMPRESSIBLE GAS-LIQUID FLOW THROUGH PIPELINE
       RESTRICTIONS
Author                :MORRIS S D
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: CHEMICAL ENGINEERING AND PROCESSING, VOL. 30
       (1991) PP. 39-44
Abstract              :A method is presented for estimating the mass flow
       rate-pressure   drop   characteristics   of  compressible  gas-liquid
       mixtures  flowing  through  pipeline  restrictions. The method can be
       applied  for  all  two-phase  Mach numbers with values of Ma(tp) less
       than  or  equal to one. Predictions of the method are compared with a
       number  of experimental data sets for air-water flows through nozzles
       and air-water and air-oil flows through orifice plates. The agreement
       is  typically  within +/-8% for nozzles and within +/-12% for orifice
       plates.  The  application of the method to flow through rupture discs
       and pressure relief valves is discussed.
Facet codes           :306 Heat transfer and fluid flow (equipment -
       312 Safety engineering
