<HEAD>
<TITLE>
DESIGNING FOR TWO-PHASE RELIEF
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199510205
Quality valid. date   :1995-02-21
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :DESIGNING FOR TWO-PHASE RELIEF : IS THAT THE ANSWER?
Author                :ARNOLD S T
       DUFFIELD J S
Affiliation           :SHELL RESEARCH, EQUIPMENT ENGINEERING DEPARTMENT,
       AMSTERDAM (NL)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: ICHEME RESEARCH EVENT, EDINBURGH
       (GB),   JANUARY   5-6,   1995  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN  COMMISSION,
       DGXIII/D-2,    L-2920    LUXEMBOURG    AS    PAPER   EN   38819   ORA
Abstract              :Designing for homogeneous two-phase relief in
       chemical   reactors   requires   large  relief  areas  and  expensive
       downstream  separation equipment. This study aims to characterise the
       dynamic behaviour of a vessel undergoing depressurisation so that the
       effect of the slip and how this affects the design of a relief system
       can  be quantified. The code RELIEF has been identified as a tool for
       the  design  and  evaluation  of  emergency  relief systems. The code
       models  the  one-dimensional  behaviour within the reactor vessel and
       can be used to assess the conditions that promote two-phase venting.
Facet codes           :102 Chemical engineering
       530 Industrial health and safety in general
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1995
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13368700
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 3C
Reference to project  :JRC-INDHAZ 3C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
       TEC (OTHER TECHNOLOGY)
 
