<HEAD>
<TITLE>
METHOD OF SIZING OF THE PRESSURE RELIEF SYSTEM
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210959
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :METHOD OF SIZING OF THE PRESSURE RELIEF SYSTEM
Original title        :METODI PER IL DIMENSIONAMENTO DEL SISTEMI DI SFIATO
Author                :BENUZZI A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: CHIMICA E SICUREZZA: CONTRIBUTO DEI
       METODI  COMPUTERIZZATI,  MILANO  (IT),  JUNE  10, 1992 AVAILABLE FROM
       EUROPEAN  COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER IT 36934
       ORA
Abstract              :Adequate sizing of the pressure relief system of a
       batch  reactor  under runaway reaction requires knowledge of the heat
       of reaction and of the main features of the fluid flow in the venting
       duct (possibility of occurrence of two-phase flow and associated flow
       regimes).  In  this  report  the  following topics are addressed: the
       fundamental aspects of two-phase flows with distributed heat sources,
       the calorimetric techniques adopted to reproduce, at small scale, the
       behaviour  of  materials  in  the  real  reactor, and the methods and
       computer  codes  used  to  obtain safe but not over-conservative vent
       sizing.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :it Italian
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB130152000
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Reference to project  :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
       IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
 
