<HEAD>
<TITLE>
FLOW VISUALIZATIONS DURING TOP VENTING FROM A SMALL
VESSEL
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210868
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :FLOW VISUALIZATIONS DURING TOP VENTING FROM A SMALL
       VESSEL
Author                :BELL K
       MORRIS S D
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: J. LOSS PREV. PROCESS IND., VOL. 5 (1992) NO
        3, PP. 160-164
Abstract              :To study the venting characteristics of foams and
       high-viscosity  fluids,  a  13  litre  glass  facility was built. The
       fluids  used were pure water, foamy water and fluids with viscosities
       of 0.013 and 0.19 Pa s (giving values 73 and 1061 times that of water
       at  150  C). The resulting blowdowns show that differences in venting
       characteristics  (pressure  history  and  vented  mass)  are  due  to
       differences  in  the  flow  regimes.  The low viscosity fluids have a
       churn-turbulent  flow pattern, while the high viscosity fluid forms a
       two-phase  emulsion  through  which large bubbles rise. In this paper
       the  experimental  results  are  compared  with  existing  data. Good
       agreement between the two sets of water and foam data is demonstrated
       but  there  is  a  discrepancy between the two sets of high viscosity
       data.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :ART An article in a journal
Euroabstracts number  :EAB130141700
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Reference to project  :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Commission service    :JRC
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
 
