<HEAD>
<TITLE>
NEW CRITERIA FOR EMERGENCY RELIEF SYSTEMS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199110913
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :NEW CRITERIA FOR EMERGENCY RELIEF SYSTEMS
Original title        :NUOVI CRITERI DI PROGETTO PER I SISTEMI DI SFIATO
Author                :BENUZZI A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: PREVENZIONE, APRIL (1991) PP. 9-11
Abstract              :Research recently performed in the US and in Europe
       has  led  to the conclusion that design criteria for emergency relief
       systems to be installed in batch reactors and storage tanks should be
       revised.   The  occurrence  of  two-phase  flows  and  the  need  for
       experimental  characterisation of the energy sources are the relevant
       features  to  be  considered for an adequate vent sizing. The current
       norms  are  inadequate  because  they  are based on the assumption of
       single-phase vapour flow, which generally gives an underestimation of
       the vent area.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :it Italian
Publication year      :1991
Publication type      :ART An article in a journal
