<HEAD>
<TITLE>
HYDRODYNAMIC ASPECTS OF VENTING FOR VESSELS
CONTAINING VISCOUS FLUIDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199011522
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :HYDRODYNAMIC ASPECTS OF VENTING FOR VESSELS
       CONTAINING VISCOUS FLUIDS
Author                :SKOULOUDIS A N
       KOTTOWSKI H M
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       RWTH, AACHEN (DE)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: 24TH ANNUAL LOSS PREVENTION
       SYMPOSIUM,  SAN  DIEGO (US), AUG. 19-22, 1990 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 35621 ORA
Abstract              :Nine depressurisation experiments for vessels
       containing water, Freon-114 and high viscosity fluids are analysed.
       These   experiments,   carried   out  at  different  plants,  provide
       information  about  the dependence of the depressurisation process on
       the  size  of  the vessel, the type of vent installed and the initial
       conditions.  The  differences  between venting into the atmosphere or
       venting  into  a  catch  tank  are also examined. The accuracy of the
       two-phase  flow  model  used for the analysis of these experiments is
       demonstrated  by  comparisons  with  steady  state  data referring to
       co-current  liquid/vapour flow, as well as to batch type flows, where
       the liquid phase is stagnant.
Facet codes           :306 Heat transfer and fluid flow (equipment -
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1990
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB12916800
