<HEAD>
<TITLE>
VENTING OF VESSELS CONTAINING REACTING FLUIDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199011156
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :VENTING OF VESSELS CONTAINING REACTING FLUIDS : A
       PARAMETRIC STUDY WITH SAFIRE AND DEERS
Author                :SKOULOUDIS A N
       BELL K
       KOTTOWSKI H M
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: JOURNAL OF LOSS PREVENTION PROCESS
       INDUSTRIES, VOL. 3 (1990) PP. 13-16
Abstract              :The importance of in-vessel flow regimes, during the
       depressurisation of vessels containing viscous and non-viscous fluids
        is  examined by the codes SAFIRE and DEERS. Similarly, the influence
       of  chemical  reactions  on  the transient is investigated for simple
       reacting   mixtures.   The   differences  between  venting  into  the
       atmosphere  and venting into a catch tank are also examined. Whenever
       possible,  experimental  comparisons are made, with the main emphasis
       directed towards the hydrodynamic aspects of the phenomena involved.
Facet codes           :308 Industrial processes
       312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1990
