<HEAD>
<TITLE>
VENTING OF VESSELS CONTAINING REACTING FLUIDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199010040
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :VENTING OF VESSELS CONTAINING REACTING FLUIDS : A
       PARAMETRIC STUDY WITH SAFIRE AND DEERS
Author                :SKOULOUDIS A N
       BELL K
       KOTTOWSKI H M
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: FIRST INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON
       LOSS  OF  CONTAINMENT,  LONDON (GB), SEPT. 12-14, 1989 AVAILABLE FROM
       EUROPEAN  COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 35054
       ORA
Abstract              :The importance of the in-vessel flow regimes during
       the  depressurisation  of  vessels containing viscous and non-viscous
       fluids  is  examined  by  the  codes SAFIRE and DEERS. Similarly, the
       influence  of  the  chemical  reaction  on  the  transience  has been
       investigated for simple reacting mixtures. The differences of venting
       into  the  atmosphere  or  venting  into  a catch tank have been also
       examined.  Whenever possible, experimental comparisons are made, with
       the  main  emphasis  directed towards the hydrodynamic asepcts of the
       phenomena involved.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
       817 Reactor pressure vessels
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1989
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB1281800
Programme acronym     :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Reference to project  :JRC-INDHAZ 2C
Commission service    :JRC
