<TITLE>
AMES AND OTHER EUROPEAN NETWORKS IN INTEGRITY OF AGEING STRUCTURES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511103
Quality valid. date   :1995-08-22
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :AMES AND OTHER EUROPEAN NETWORKS IN INTEGRITY OF
       AGEING STRUCTURES
Author                :DAVIES L M
       VON ESTORFF U
       CRUTZEN S
Affiliation           :LMD CONSULTANCY, OXFORD (GB)
       JRC PETTEN (NL)
       JRC PETTEN (NL)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: INTERNATIONAL SYMPOSIUM ON MATERIALS
       AGEING AND COMPONENT LIFE EXTENSION, MILANO (IT), OCTOBER 10-13, 1995
       AVAILABLE  FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS
       PAPER EN 39114 ORA
Abstract              :The Institute for Advanced Materials at the JRC is
       responsible for the operation and management of three networks: AMES,
       NESC, ENIQ. Each of these deals with the fitness for their purpose of
       materials  used  in  particular  types of structural components. This
       paper describes the structure and objectives of these networks.
       Particular  emphasis  is  given  to AMES, which is concerned with the
       study  and  evaluation  of  ageing  materials,  i.e. reactor pressure
       vessel  steels  suffering  the  effects  of  irradiation  and thermal
       degradation over a period of years.
