<TITLE>
THE TREATMENT OF PHYSICAL DEPENDENCIES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199512080
Quality valid. date   :1996-01-15
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :THE TREATMENT OF PHYSICAL DEPENDENCIES AND CCFS
       WITHIN   THE   STARS   ENVIRONMENT:   METHODOLOGICAL   FRAMEWORK  AND
       APPLICATIONS
Author                :COJAZZI G
       MAURI G
       SARDELLA R
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: INTERACTIONAL CONFERENCE ON
       PROBABILISTIC  SAFETY  ASSESSMENT,  SEOUL  (KR), NOVEMBER 26-30, 1995
       AVAILABLE  FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS
       PAPER EN 39437 ORA
Abstract              :A proper treatment of dependencies is at the basis of
       a  correct  system  analysis  and,  if  not  correctly performed, can
       invalidate  a  whole  probabilistic safety analysis (PSA) study. Here
       the  problem  of  dependencies  is  addressed  with  reference to the
       Software  Tool for the Analysis of Reliability and Safety (STARS). To
       this  aim the information concerning the function of a component, its
       boundaries,  its states and its failure modes is synthesized in a set
       of tables from which the rules used in STARS can be simply derived.
       The  methodology  has then been applied to model components which are
       particularly  suitable  for taking into account physical dependencies
       and CCFs. Application and numerical results are also discussed.
Facet codes           :007 Safety
       711 Knowledge engineering (including AI and
       720 IT application technologies
