<TITLE>
DYLAM-3
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199511573
Quality valid. date   :1995-12-12
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :DYLAM-3 : A DYNAMIC METHODOLOGY FOR REALIABILITY
       ANALYSIS  AND  CONSEQUENCES  EVALUATION IN INDUSTRIAL PLANTS : THEORY
       AND HOW TO USE
Author                :COJAZZI G
       CACCIABUE P C
       PARISI P
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 15265 EN (L993) 120 PP., FREE OF CHARGE AVAILABLE
       FROM JOINT RESEARCH CENTRE, PUBLICATION DEPARTMENT, I-21020 ISPRA (VA
       ) (IT)
Abstract              :This report describes in detail the DYLAM-3 code. The
       first  part  of  the report describes the methodological aspects, and
       the  second part contains a quick reference to the use of the program
       and  also some examples in order to describe the main features of the
       code.  The DYLAM methodology does not represent an alternative to the
       fault-tree  and  event-trees  analysis,  but  it is rather a powerful
       complementary  approach  for  the  detailed study of those situations
       where  the interaction between the transient evolution and the system
       state plays a relevant role for the safety of the system.
Facet codes           :701 Computers and applications
