REFLECTIONS ON THE INDICATORS FOR VULNERABILITY AND THEIR APPLICATION TO CHEMICAL HAZARDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199510582
Quality valid. date   :1995-05-03
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :REFLECTIONS ON THE INDICATORS FOR VULNERABILITY AND
       THEIR APPLICATION TO CHEMICAL HAZARDS
Author                :HAASTRUP P
       RAVETZ J
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: RISK, RISK MANAGEMENT AND RISK
       COMMUNICATION  : AN INTEGRATED PERSPECTIVE, GORIZIA (IT), DECEMBER 2,
       1994   AVAILABLE   FROM   EUROPEAN   COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920
       LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 38894 ORA
Abstract              :The consequences of events considered by risk
       analysis may depend dramatically on the societal aspects of the total
       environment  in  which the events occur. The concept of vulnerability
       is   introduced  to  index  the  effects  of  different  milieu.  The
       construction  of  indicators  for  the  vulnerability  of society and
       target groups to chemical hazards is examined, together with criteria
       for evaluation of the quality of such indicators.
