<HEAD>
<TITLE>
RISK COMMUNICATION IN DIRECTIVE 82/501/CEE (SEVESO)
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210619
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :RISK COMMUNICATION IN DIRECTIVE 82/501/CEE (SEVESO)
Original title        :LA COMUNICAZIONE DEL RISCHIO NELLA DIRETTIVA
       82/501/CEE (SEVESO)
Author                :DE MARCHI B
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: PROGETTO FINALIZZATO FAT-MA, ROMA
       (IT),   MARCH   26-27,   1992  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN  COMMISSION,
       DGXIII/D-2,    L-2920    LUXEMBOURG    AS    PAPER   IT   36782   ORA
Abstract              :The promulgation of Community Directive 82/501/EEC in
       1982  made communication of the risk of accidents in industries which
       use  or  stock certain chemical substances a topical issue. Article 8
       requires  people  who are exposed to the risk of serious accidents to
       be informed of the risks they face and of the measures to take in the
       event of an accident. There must be a constant and unhindered flow of
       information  between various bodies: the Commission, the Council, the
       European  Parliament,  the relevant authorities in the member states,
       industry and the public. Communication must be an interactive process
        Surveys  of  recent  accidents  have  shown,  in fact, that negative
       consequences  can  be  significantly  worsened  by a lack of adequate
       knowledge  on  the  part of the public, the local authorities and the
       emergency  services, and therefore confirm the importance of adequate
       preventative knowledge.
Facet codes           :007 Safety
       538 Safety and health at work
Availability in lang  :it Italian
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB130119300
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
 
