<TITLE>
INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENTS-MANAGEMENT OF RISK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199512079
Quality valid. date   :1996-01-15
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENTS-MANAGEMENT OF RISK
Author                :AMENDOLA A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: HELECO'95, ATHENS (GR), NOVEMEBER
       9-12,  1995  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920
       LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 39431 ORA
Abstract              :The paper focuses on main issues being introduced in
       the  new  proposal  for  a Directive on the Control of Major Accident
       Hazards,  such as: land use planning with respect to accident hazards
       to  decrease  the  vulnerability  of  the  environment into which the
       undesired  event  may develop its consequences; and the adoption of a
       Major  Accident  Prevention  Policy  (MAPP)  to  reduce  hazards  and
       likelihood  of  related  accidents. It discusses how new requirements
       strengthen  the  socio-organizational  aspects in the risk management
       process,  and  result  in  an increased transparency in risk decision
       with respect to public information and participation.
