<TITLE>
RISK MANAGEMENT, UNCERTAINTY AND POST-NORMAL SCIENCE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199410643
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :RISK MANAGEMENT, UNCERTAINTY AND POST-NORMAL SCIENCE
Author                :FUNTOWICZ S O
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: FIRST INTERNATIONAL SYMPOSIUM ON
       SUSTAINABLE  FISH  FARMING,  OSLO  (NO), AUGUST 28-31, 1994 AVAILABLE
       FROM  EUROPEAN  COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN
       38326 ORA
Abstract              :This paper discusses post-normal science and its
       application  in  managing  problems  of  risk  and the environment. A
       method   for  assessing  and  expressing  the  quality  of  technical
       information  in  terms  of  its characteristic uncertainties has been
       developed.  This  system's  potential  use  in  the  work  of quality
       assurance   in   the  extended  peer  communities  is  outlined.  The
       epistemological   analysis  of  post-normal  science  shows  that  an
       extension  of  peer  communities  with the corresponding extension of
       facts  is  necessary  for the effectiveness of science in meeting new
       challenges.
