Record cntrl number   :199410623
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-28
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :INDUSTRIAL RISK MANAGEMENT : A EEC PERSPECTIVE
Author                :AMENDOLA A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: PSAM II, SAN DIEGO (US), MARCH 20-24
        1994   AVAILABLE   FROM   EUROPEAN  COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920
       LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 38054 ORA
Abstract              :New trends in European legislation aimed at
       controlling the risk of major accidents in industry are examined. The
       principles  relating  to  the control of accident hazards are set out
       and  the  implementation  of  Directives  by the member states of the
       European Union is discussed. The roles that the public, the competent
       authorities  and  industry have to play in risk management policy are
       outlined  and emphasis is placed on the adoption of safety management
       systems  (SMS).  The  major  challenges facing researchers as regards
       aspects  of risk assessment and decision making, and SMS-research are
       outlined.
