<TITLE>
EMPIRICAL EVALUATION OF PUBLIC INFORMATION ON MAJOR
INDUSTRIAL RISK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199211240
Quality valid. date   :1994-11-29
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :EMPIRICAL EVALUATION OF PUBLIC INFORMATION ON MAJOR
       INDUSTRIAL RISK
Author                :WYNNE B
Affiliation           :LANCASTER UNIVERSITY (GB)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 14443 EN (1992) 100 PP., FS, ECU 10.50 ISBN
       92-826-4402-2  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :Because public information on hazards and emergency
       advice  is  a  novel  element  of  industrial  regulation,  there  is
       considerable  uncertainty  about the best methods to adopt, and about
       the   effectiveness   of   current  information  campaigns.  Yet  the
       effectiveness  of  such  public information may be crucial for saving
       life  in  the  event  of  an  accident.  After  the successful Varese
       Conference  organised  by  the  Commission DG XI and JRC Ispra in May
       1989,  the  Council  requested  that the Commission draft a practical
       guide to aid proper and effective implementation of the active public
       information  obligations.  The  present study was designed to provide
       background  empirical  research  data which would help to inform this
       policy development.
