THE USE OF STARS AS AN OFF-LINE DECISION SUPPORT
SYSTEM FOR RISK MANAGEMENT
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210830
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE USE OF STARS AS AN OFF-LINE DECISION SUPPORT
       SYSTEM FOR RISK MANAGEMENT
Author                :POUCET A
       CHRISTENSEN P
       SMITH-HANSEN L
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       RIS NATIONAL LABORATORY, ROSKILDE (DK)
       RIS NATIONAL LABORATORY, ROSKILDE (DK)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: 1992 EUROPEAN SAFETY AND RELIABILITY
       CONFERENCE, COPENHAGEN (DK), JUNE 10-12, 1992 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 36877 ORA
Abstract              :After an introduction on the use of quantitative
       safety  assessment  methods  for  risk  management  purposes, a brief
       outline  is  given  of  the  STARS  project.  This project covers the
       development  of  an  integrated  informatic  system which consists of
       knowledge  based  tools (expert systems) and other modules to support
       industrial   plant   safety   assessment.   It  is  explained  how  a
       computer-based  safety  assessment could be used as a risk management
       related decision support system. Finally, the use of STARS modules in
       this  context  is  discussed,  and it is shown that those modules can
       support off-line monitoring of the risk over the plant life-cycle.
