<HEAD>
<TITLE>
RISK EVALUATION TECHNIQUES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199111090
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :RISK EVALUATION TECHNIQUES
Original title        :LE TECNICHE DI VALUTAZIONE DEL RISCHIO
Author                :VOLTA G
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :ARTICLE: TERMOTECNICA, SETTEMBRE 1990 (1990) PP.
       43-49
Abstract              :Technological risk, considered as a negative side
       effect  of  the use of equipment or plant, can be evaluated by taking
       into  consideration  different boundaries of the system affected. The
       paper  identifies  four  systemic  levels,  in  order  of  increasing
       complexity,  and  outlines  the  status  of the techniques adopted to
       evaluate  risk  at  each  level. It is shown how risk evaluation is a
       complex  knowledge process and not an algorithm. The consensus on the
       findings  is  assured more by the transparency of the techniques used
       than by the numerical precision of the results.
Facet codes           :300 Engineering and technology in general
Availability in lang  :it Italian
Publication year      :1990
