<HEAD>
<TITLE>
SEMINAR ON APPLICATIONS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199010243
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :SEMINAR ON APPLICATIONS, PERSPECTIVES AND LIMITATIONS
       OF COMPARATIVE RISK ASSESSMENT AND RISK MANAGEMENT : NICE, FRANCE, 26
       TO 30 SEPTEMBER 1988
Note                  :PROCEEDINGS OF THE WORKSHOP
Author                :OLAST M
       SINNAEVE J
       BRESSON G
Affiliation           :CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
       CEC BRUXELLES (BE)
       CENTRE  DE  D?VELOPPEMENT  DES  ?TUDES  ET APPLICATIONS EN HYGINE ET
       S?CURIT? (CEDHYS), PARIS (FR)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 11465 EN (1990) 363 PP., FS, ECU 32.50 OFFICE FOR
       OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :The experiences, knowledge and methodologies
       developed  for  assessing  radiation risks to man and his environment
       are  now  applied  in a broader context to prevent, reduce and manage
       risks  linked  to  numerous  human industrial activities. The obvious
       need  to  compare  such  risks  and  the  increasing  concern  of the
       responsible  authorities  for  the environment and for the safety and
       well-being  of  the  general  population  and industrial workers, has
       urged the scientific community to develop methods for risk management
       based  upon a comparative approach. The purpose of this seminar was a
       multi-disciplinary discussion of the progress made in this field with
       a  view to defining the applications, perspectives and limitations of
       risk assessment and risk management.
