       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: ISSA 93 CONFERENCE, SAFETY PAYS,
       LUGANO  (CH),  AUGUST  8  - SEPTEMBER 1, 1993 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 37328 ORA
Abstract              :This paper describes FORMENTOR, a real-time expert
       system  that  offers on-line decision support to operators of complex
       plant who are faced with unusual and potentially hazardous situations
        After  the  overall  project  background  and  philosophy  have been
       described,  the  essential  functionalities  of  such  a  system  are
       outlined.  The  paper  then  focuses on one of the pilot applications
       developed: a supervisory and decision support system for operators of
       an  extractive  distillation  unit of a petrochemical plant. The most
       important techniques and models used are briefly discussed. Knowledge
       bases  built  on functional, structural and behavioural models of the
       plant  and  incorporating  operator  heuristics provide the knowledge
       necessary for supporting many of the required functionalities.
       Finally,  the  distributed and object-oriented software architecture,
       which is a key technique for such systems, is illustrated.
Facet codes           :312 Safety engineering
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1993
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB13220000
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
