<TITLE>
SYSTEMS RELIABILITY ASSESSMENT
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199011539
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :SYSTEMS RELIABILITY ASSESSMENT
Note                  :PROCEEDINGS OF THE ISPRA COURSE HELD AT THE ESCUELA
       TECNICA  SUPERIOR DE INGENIEROS NOVALES, MADRID, SPAIN, SEPTEMBER 19-
Author                :COLOMBO A G
       SAIZ DE BUSTAMENTE A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       UNIVERSIDAD POLITECNICA DE MADRID (ES)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 12924 EN (1990) 310 PP. ISBN 0-7923-0837-9 KLUWER
       ACADEMIC  PUBLISHERS  GROUP,  P.O.  BOX  322,  3300 AH DORDRECHT (NL)
Abstract              :This book presents models and methods for systems
       reliability  assessment,  human  reliability analysis and uncertainty
       management.   Section  1  describes  basic  reliability  methods  and
       applications.   Section   2   deals  with  some  advances  in  system
       reliability  techniques.  It  includes  contributions  on the logical
       analysis  of  non-coherent  fault  trees,  stochastic  Petri nets and
       failure delay modelling. Dynamic systems are analysed using DYLAM and
       DYLAM-TRETA approaches. Section 3 is devoted to human reliability and
       uncertainty  analysis.  Cognitive  models,  fixation  errors  and the
       Bayesian  estimation  of  reliability  parameters  are discussed. One
       contribution  reviews  the  most  important  theories of quantitative
       reasoning under uncertainty currently implemented in expert systems.
Facet codes           :007 Safety
       706 Mathematical models
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1990
