<HEAD>
<TITLE>
BENCHMARK EXERCISE ON MAJOR HAZARD ANALYSIS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210445
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :BENCHMARK EXERCISE ON MAJOR HAZARD ANALYSIS
Note                  :VOL. 3 : SEISMIC ANALYSIS
Author                :DROGARIS G
       SOLOMOS G
       AMENDOLA A
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13898 EN (1992) 179 PP., MF, ECU 8, BLOW-UP COPY
       ECU  27 OFFICE FOR OFFICIAL PUBLICATIONS OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES,
       L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :A seismic analysis of the plant considered in the
       Benchmark  Exercise  on  the  Major  Hazard Analysis Project has been
       performed by four participating groups. Analysis of seismic source is
       often  hampered  by lack of availability of adequate data relating to
       specific  sites.  Where accelerograms are recorded on site, there are
       still  difficulties  regarding the proper application. Finite element
       discretisation  is  generally accepted as the most accurate method of
       seismic  analysis  for  complex structures. Considerations of seismic
       impact on the specific structure suggest that the inner metal tank is
       the  most  critical  component, but that more research is also needed
       concerning  the foundations, piles and outer concrete shell. Accurate
       seismic  risk  calculations  would  require  due consideration of the
       uncertainties in the failure criteria (incorporation of deterministic
       failure  modes  in  a  probabilistic  risk assessment, yield strength
       distribution,  stress  distribution,  etc.)  and  the  effect  of the
       variability of the filling height.
Facet codes           :204 Geophysics
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1992
Publication type      :EUR A report issued by the Commission as an EUR
       report      and      identified      by      its      EUR      number
Euroabstracts number  :EAB130105700
Subject index codes   :EAR (EARTH SCIENCES)
       SAF (SAFETY)
 
