<TITLE>
THE COMMUNITY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE ON INDUSTRIAL RISK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199510715
Quality valid. date   :1995-07-07
Update date           :1996-01-19
Title in english      :THE COMMUNITY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE ON INDUSTRIAL RISK
Author                :AMENDOLA A
       CARNEVALI C
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: 8TH INTERNATIONAL SYMPOSIUM ON LOSS
       PREVENTION  AND  SAFETY  PROMOTION IN THE PROCESS INDUSTRIES, ANTWERP
       (BE),  JUNE 6-9, 1995 AVAILABLE FROM EUROPEAN COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2,
       L-2920      LUXEMBOURG      AS      PAPER      EN      38982      ORA
Abstract              :The paper describes the operation of the Community
       Documentation Centre on Industrial Risk (CDCIR) and its relevance for
       loss  prevention  and safety promotion in the process industries. The
       CDCIR  (which  is  now part of the Major Accident Hazards Bureau) was
       created by the European Commission with the objective of contributing
       to  a harmonised implementation of the EU Directive on major accident
       hazards  by: (i) collecting and diffusing information on the national
       approaches  to  the  implementation  of  the  Directive; on technical
       guidance and codes of good practice concerning the activities covered
       by the Directive; on accident investigation and other related issues;
       (ii)  publishing  studies  and  other  work  promoted by the European
       Commission on issues related to the implementation of the Directive.
       The studies already published cover topics such as accident reporting
       and  analysis,  safety  reports  and  safety management systems, risk
       assessment  and land use planning, emergency planning and information
       to the public.
Facet codes           :538 Safety and health at work
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1995
Publication type      :ORA An oral conference paper
Euroabstracts number  :EAB133116300
Subject index codes   :SAF (SAFETY)
 
