<TITLE>
RISK COMMUNICATION AND ART. 8 OF THE SEVESO DIRECTIVE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210641
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :RISK COMMUNICATION AND ART. 8 OF THE SEVESO DIRECTIVE
Author                :DE MARCHI B
       PENNAVAJA S
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       CAMERA DI COMMERCIO, VARESE (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: HEALTH EMERGENCIES IN TECHNOLOGICAL
       DISASTERS,   ROMA   (IT),  MAY  5-7,  1992  AVAILABLE  FROM  EUROPEAN
       COMMISSION,  DGXIII/D-2,  L-2920  LUXEMBOURG  AS  PAPER  EN 36724 ORA
Abstract              :The experience gained from major accidents in several
       countries  has  resulted  in the European Community paying increasing
       attention  to  the  control  of  industrial hazards and environmental
       protection.  The  present  orientation  is towards the realisation of
       full   transparency   and  increasing  public  participation  in  the
       decisions regarding the siting and management of hazardous industrial
       installations   whose  production  or  storage  activities  may  have
       negative  effects  on  humans  and  the environment. Article 8 of the
       Seveso Directive is innovative in many respects and can be considered
       a  first  step  towards  the  establishment of a new approach to risk
       management,  which  involves local communities as well as experts and
       authorities.
Facet codes           :005 Science policy
       505 Environmental research and protection
