<TITLE>
THE TOXICOLOGY OF CHEMICALS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199111511
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :THE TOXICOLOGY OF CHEMICALS - 1. CARCINOGENICITY :
       SUMMARY   REVIEWS   OF   THE   SCIENTIFIC   EVIDENCE   -  VOLUME  III
Author                :BERLIN A
       VAN DER VENNE M T
       DRAPER M H
       DUFFUS J H (EDITORS)
Affiliation           :CEC LUXEMBOURG (LU)
       CEC LUXEMBOURG (LU)
       WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION, INTERNATIONAL PROGRAMME ON CHEMICAL SAFETY
        GENVE (CH)
       HERIOT-WATT UNIVERSITY, EDINBURGH CENTRE FOR TOXICOLOGY, EDINBURGH
       (GB)
Bibliogr reference    :EUR 13765 EN (1991) 184 PP., FS, ECU 17.55 ISBN
       92-826-2816-7  OFFICE  FOR  OFFICIAL  PUBLICATIONS  OF  THE  EUROPEAN
       COMMUNITIES, L-2985 LUXEMBOURG
Abstract              :This is the third volume in a series that is planned
       to  cover  the  carcinogenicity,  the  reproductive  toxicity and the
       immunotoxicity  of chemicals. It has been produced with the objective
       of  providing  readily  available  summary  reviews  of  the  salient
       scientific  evidence  that  underlies  the assessment of a particular
       chemical  in  terms  of  carcinogenicity.  This  volume deals with 24
       compounds  including  arsenic  compounds,  together  with  a  general
       introduction  to  the  chemistry  and  biology  of  arsenic  and  its
       industrial  and  health  aspects.  The  reviews  set  out  to provide
       concisely  and  systematically  the most relevant scientific findings
       from  studies  in  animals,  from the results of short-term tests for
       mutagens  and  carcinogens, and from epidemiological studies that all
       together are utilised in the risk assessment of a chemical.
Facet codes           :514 Toxicology
