<HEAD>
<TITLE>
TWO-PHASE DESCRIPTION OF HYDRODYNAMIC FRAGMENTATION PROCESSES WITHIN THERMAL DETONATION WAVES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :123049000
Quality valid. date   :1987-01-01
Update date           :1994-12-23
Title in english      :TWO-PHASE DESCRIPTION OF HYDRODYNAMIC FRAGMENTATION
       PROCESSES        WITHIN        THERMAL        DETONATION        WAVES
Author                :BUERGER M
       KIM D S
       SCHWALBE W
       UNGER H
       HOHMANN H
       SCHINS H
Affiliation           :INSTITUT FUER KERNENERGETIK UND ENERGIESYSTEME,
       UNIVESITAET STUTTGART (GERMANY)
       JRC ISPRA ESTAB. (ITALY)
Bibliogr reference    :JOURNAL OF HEAT TRANSFER, VOL. 106 (1984), PP.
       728-734.
Abstract              :Large scale vapour explosions are described by
       thermal detonation waves, proceeding through a fuel coolant mixture.
       A  two-phase  flow  model is used for modeling the processes inside a
       wave.  One  phase is formed by the drops of melt and the other by the
       coolant  and  the  fragments.  For the interfacial transfer relations
       between  the  phases  new  descriptions  are  presented, which extend
       earlier thermal detonation models. The fragmentation behaviour can be
       calculated  from  two  different  models,  one  based  on deformation
       break-up  and Taylor instability and another describing fragmentation
       by stripping of capillary waves induced by shear flow instabilities.
       In addition to the time development of the fragmented mass the models
       give  also  the  actual  sizes  of  the  fragments.  Results  of  the
       fragmentation   models   are   compared   with   the  experiments  on
       hydrodynamic fragmentation of single drops of gallium in water flows.
       For  vapour  explosion  experiments with tin - water and salt - water
       systems  the detonation cases are determined using the wave stripping
       model.
Facet codes           :907 Fluid mechanics
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1984
Publication type      :ART An article in a journal
Euroabstracts number  :EAB123049000
Subject index codes   :SCI (SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
</PRE>
</BODY>
