<HEAD>
<TITLE>
SOME COMPUTATIONS OF DETONATIONS USING THE CULDESAC CODE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :198910989
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :SOME COMPUTATIONS OF DETONATIONS USING THE CULDESAC
       CODE
Author                :FLETCHER D F
Affiliation           :CULHAM LABORATORY, ABINGDON, OXON. OX14 3DB (GB)
Bibliogr reference    :REPORT: CLM-R291 EN (1989) AVAILABLE FROM HER
       MAJESTY'S  STATIONERY  OFFICE,  P.O.  BOX  276,  LONDON, SE1 9NH (GB)
Abstract              :In this paper the results are presented of a series
       of  computations  performed  using  the  CULDESAC code. CULDESAC is a
       multiphase  detonation  model  which  is  being developed in order to
       understand  the  detonation  phase  of  a vapour explosion. The paper
       contains  the  results  of a limited parameter survey and simulations
       for  inhomogeneous  initial  coarse  mixtures.  The  relevance of the
       results  obtained  to  experimental  data  on  vapour  explosions  is
       discussed.   Also   considered   is   the   importance  of  modelling
       non-equilibrium  effects  in detonations. Finally, an overview of the
       status of detonation modelling is given.
Facet codes           :706 Mathematical models
Availability in lang  :en English
Publication year      :1989
Publication type      :REP Other scientific and technical reports published
       by     the     Commission     or     its     contractual     partners
Euroabstracts number  :EAB12799400
Subject index codes   :MST (MATHEMATICS, STATISTICS)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
 
 
