<HEAD>
<TITLE>
MULTIPHASE DETONATION MODELLING USING THE CULDESAC CODE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :198910591
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-01
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :MULTIPHASE DETONATION MODELLING USING THE CULDESAC
       CODE
Author                :FLETCHER D F
       THYAGARAJA A
Affiliation           :CULHAM LABORATORY, ABINGDON, OXON (GB)
       CULHAM LABORATORY, ABINGDON, OXON (GB)
Bibliogr reference    :REPORT: CLM-P855 EN (1988) AVAILABLE FROM THE
       LIBRARIAN,  UKAEA,  CULHAM  LABORATORY, ABINGDON, OXON. OX14 3DB (GB)
Abstract              :A mathematical model of melt/water detonations is
       developed  to study the escalation and propagation stages of a vapour
       explosion.  The  conservation  equations  and  constitutive relations
       which  form  the  model are given. Simulations are performed to study
       the effect of the presence of permanent gas in the coarse mixture.
       Predictions  using an approximate EOS are compared with those using a
       standard steam tube package.
Facet codes           :818 Reactor safety
