<TITLE>
MULTIPHASE FLOW MODELLING AND APPLICATIONS AT THE CEC
JOINT RESEARCH CENTRE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number   :199210826
Quality valid. date   :1994-12-02
Update date           :1996-01-20
Title in english      :MULTIPHASE FLOW MODELLING AND APPLICATIONS AT THE CEC
       JOINT RESEARCH CENTRE
Author                :JONES A V
       DUFFIELD S
       STDTKE H
       WIDER H W
Affiliation           :JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
       JRC ISPRA (IT)
Bibliogr reference    :PAPER PRESENTED: EUROPEAN COMPUTATIONAL FLUID
       DYNAMICS  CONFERENCE, BRUXELLES (BE), SEPT. 7-11, 1992 AVAILABLE FROM
       EUROPEAN  COMMISSION, DGXIII/D-2, L-2920 LUXEMBOURG AS PAPER EN 36888
       ORA
Abstract              :This paper is concerned with the work of the JRC
       laboratory  at  Ispra,  in  multiphase  flow  research. The JRC first
       became  interested  in  multiphase  flow  in  the  context of nuclear
       reactor  safety,  but  more recently, as industry in other fields has
       become  aware of the calculation capabilities built up in the nuclear
       area, it has begun to transfer its expertise into selected industrial
       sectors,  particularly  that  of  hazardous processes in the chemical
       industry. Topics covered include: (i) a summary of work done relating
       to  steam/water  flows;  (ii) two lines of model development for more
       complex    flows    (FARO    Experiment    Analysis   and   Transient
       Multiphase-Multicomponent  Flow  Treatments in EAC-2); (iii) the main
       issues   and   problems   associated  with  particulate  flows;  (iv)
       indications of future work.
