<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Modelisation incendie simulant les transferts et les risques a l'environnement
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23975
Quality valid. date    :1995-02-22
Key words              :Pool fire, accident, heat flux, modelling, 
                        dispersion
Update date            :1995-08-28
Project acronym        :MISTRAL 2
Title                  :Modelisation incendie simulant les transferts et
                        les risques a l'environnement
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)

General information    :Liquid or solid compound pool fire and its
consequences on  the  facility  or  building  as  well  as  on  the
environment is the typical accident studied in this project.
Development  and  qualification  of  technologies  (so  as to perform
industrial  plant safety studies and to improve prevention), carrying
out  studies  of  a  more  fundamental  nature  (in order to increase
knowledge of the physico-chemical phenomena involved during a fire so
as  to  better  determine  the thermal consequences on the building),
quantification  of the releases into the environment, optimization of
the  efficiency  of certain fire abatement means and extension of the
codes  qualification  field  so as to better manage the risk, are the
objectives  of  the  project. The inventory of the tasks performed is
the  study of fire propagation, soot aerosol nucleation, influence of
soot  aerosols  and  of  water  droplets on radiative heat transfers,
turbulence  induced  by  the  fire,  standardized tests (to determine
their  possible  use  in  defining  large-scale tests), combustion of
compounds  releasing  particularly toxic and/or corrosive products by
means  of  medium  and  large  scale  experiments,  realization  of a
three-dimensional  fire code and its qualification along with the one
of  zone  codes  by  means  of the above-mentioned experiments. Tests
(medium  and  large-scale)  using  standardized  device or apparatus,
basic  research  in  support  of  the  comprehension of the phenomena
generated by the fire (with or without a mitigating system) modelling
and  qualification of  the codes, theoretical  and experimental atmo-
spheric diffusion studies are  the  main  axes  of  the  project. The 
project will be accomplished in association of different laboratories
or organizations representing five community countries.
These  partners, represents a harmonious balance between : industrial
state   organizations  involved  in  environment  control  and  risks
incurred  by  man's  activities,  state organizations responsible for
fundamental   research  and  industrial  partners  concerned  by  the
protection   of  the  Environment  which  will  be  able  to  present
altogether their results obtained to the European community.

Start date             :1994-06-01
End date               :1996-05-31
Duration in months     :24
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0527
Prime contr org        :Commissariat a l'Energie Atomique
Prime contr dept       :Institut de Protection et de Surete Nucleaire -
                        Departement de Recherches en Securite Service  Experimentation des Accidents- Laboratoire                                   d'Experimentation et Modelisation des Feux - LEMF
Prime contr address    :Ctr Etudes de Cadarache - CE-Ca
