<TITLE>
Safety and Reliability Assessment Risk and
Environmental Impact Assessment Procedures
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19326
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-09
Key words              :Risk study, accident, seveso directive, hazard
                        analysis
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Safety and Reliability Assessment Risk and
                        Environmental Impact Assessment Procedures,
                        1988-1991
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Objectives             :Assessment of methods and  procedures for the
evaluation  of  risks  connected  with  major  accidents  hazards and
routine emissions.  The activity is relevant for Community Directives
on  Environmental  protection (Seveso Directive, Environmental Impact
Assessment, etc.).
General information    :Progress to end 1990
The  results  of the Benchmark Exercise on Major Hazards Analysis for
an  Ammonia  storage  plant  have been evaluated and published as EUR
report. Invited  publication  in  the  Journal of Hazardous Material.
Useful indications on the state  of the art in risk assessment and on
sources of  uncertainties have  been drawn, useful for  the STEP pro-
gramme, in which a second project has been launched on an LPG instal-
lation.
For  the  assessment  of cascade fire & explosion accident scenarios,
single  models have been tested and the architecture of an integrated
software package (DOMINO) on a P.C. has been designed. Collaborations
have  been established with the laboratories TNO (NL)and WQI (Dk) for
the study of  vulnerability of man  and environment to chemical acci-
dents. A  survey  of  indicators  and indices for enviromental impact
& risk assessment has been made through a Workshop organised at Ispra
on May 1990. (Proceedings edited as  EUR 13060 EN). Studies have been
started for the combination of  environmental  indicators  by  taking
into account  synergies  and  uncertainties,  and  for the definition
of syntetic  index for water  quality  assessment.  Data  analysis on
biotic indicators (lichens) for evaluation  of  cumulative  risk from
air pollution has  started.  These activities  e performed in collabo-
ration  with  the  Environment  Institute  and  the  Universities  of
Milano, Trieste  &  Parma,  and  are  strongly linked with T.P. works
for the Italian Ministry of the Environment and ISPESL.
Detailed description of  work foreseen in 1991 (expected results) The
second benchmark project (STEP) is expected to start on mid 1991,this
time  managed   by  HSE.   JRC  will  participate  in  it   with  the
objective  of  assessing  its  own  methodologies  (STARS, DOMINO). A
survey of  relevant models  for environmental impact  and of criteria 
for environmental  compatibility  of hazardous installations  will be
performed  (back-up for Support to Commission and T.P. works). The on
going studies on indicators and indices will be completed. Intermedi-
ate  results from the  collaborative efforts on  vulnerability models
and  environmental emergencies will  be obtained. A  Knowledge  Based
System  for impact assessment  on water  bodies will  be designed and
partially implemented.Short description of evolution of work in 1992.
Whereas  the  participation  in  the  benchmark  project  (STEP) will
continue  along  the established planning all other activities should
focus  on methods for  assessing the  integral risk  to  the  man and
environment:  routine  risk  to  people,  accident  risk  to  people,
accident and routine risk to the environment.     2

Start date             :1988-01-01
End date               :1992-01-01
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :INDHAZ 2C
Project reference      :0001
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute for Systems Engineering
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
Prime contr town       :ISPRA
Prime contr region     :R3201 Varese
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
Contact person         :Name:         COLOMBO, ALESSANDRO
       Tel:          +39-332-89119406 
