<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Simulation of Chemical Batch Processes, 1992-1994
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :17153
Quality valid. date    :1992-12-10
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Simulation of Chemical Batch Processes, 1992-1994
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Objectives             :Development and experimental validation of
comprehensive  models  for the numerical simulation of chemical batch
processes under normal and off-normal operating conditions.
Integration of these models into advanced methodologies for efficient
process   optimisation   and   prevention   of  uncontrolled  thermal
excursions.
The  work  is  presently  focused  on  the  mononitration of Toluene,
serving  as prototypical example for the class of aromatic nitrations
with  mixed  acid.  It  comprises  the  development  of the numerical
simulator FISIM, and a large experimental effort with different types
of  calorimeters  and  the main facility FIRES (a highly instrumented
100 litre tank reactor in a bunker).
General information    :Progress to end 1991
1.  Final  characterisation  tests of the FIRES facility (dynamics of
the  heating/cooling  loop, and overall heat transfer coefficient for
different liquids).
2.  Experimental  study  of  droplet  size  distribution  in agitated
liquid-liquid systems.
3. Preliminary studies on model-based techniques using Kalman filters
for the on-line prediction of the overall heat transfer coefficient.
4. Experiments on Toluene nitration in the calorimetric laboratory:
(a)  the  Differential  Scanning  Calorimeter  was  used  to test the
thermal stability of products and mixtures; 
(b) adiabatic experiments were carried out to measure the heat of reaction
and investigate accumulation problems; 
(c) the small scale (2 litre) reactor was used to characterise the influence
of  the  main  operating conditions (temperature, stirrer speed, sulphuric 
acid concentration and feeding rate).
5.  Set up of an analytical procedure based on gas chromatography and
titration  to  analyse,  during  the  reaction, the compounds present
respectively in the organic and in the acid phase.
6.  Validation  of  the  heterogeneous two-liquid-phase kinetic model
implemented  in  FISIM; it was shown that the formulated mathematical
model  adequately  describes the significant process behaviour, being
able  to  predict whenever the reaction is dominated by mass transfer
or by chemical kinetics.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1992
The  Toluene  nitration  experiments in FIRES under normal industrial
conditions  will  be  pursued  to  characterise  the influence of the
operating   conditions   (concentrations,   stirrer  speed,  starting
temperature, stream feed, etc.) and to optimise them from performance
and safety point of view.
The studies under induced failures (failure of the cooling system and
stirrer  stoppage) will start, as well as the assessment of different
methods  to  stop  the runaway reaction. After these experimental studies,
the possibilities  to  develop  a  common  strategy in order to implement
safety  measures  for  this  kind  of  family  of processes (aromatic
nitrations  with  mixed  acid)  will  be reviewed and the conclusions
published.
Following  the  advice  of  the  European  Contract  Group on Runaway
Reactions  the experimental programme will continue with the study of
the  methyl-methacrylate polymerisation reaction studies under normal
industrial conditions and under induced failures in the installation,
but  having in mind the possibility to carry out experimental studies
for different chemical industries on specific reactions under request
Short description of evolution of work in 1993
The  experimental  programme  set up by the European Contact Group on
Runaway  Reactions  will be finished and emphasis will be put on work
requested by specific chemical industries.
Start date             :1992-01-01
End date               :1994-12-31
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :INDHAZ 3C
Project reference      :0002
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute for Safety Technology
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
Prime contr town       :ISPRA
Prime contr region     :R3201 Varese
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
Contact person         :Name:         BASSANI C.
                    Tel:          +39-332-7889282
                    Fax:          +39-332-789001
                  Telex:        380042 EUR I
 
