<TITLE>
Development of design rules for unprotected steel structures
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23347
Quality valid. date    :1994-11-28
Key words              :Fire, car park, steel buidings
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Development of design rules for unprotected steel
                        structures  subjected  to  realistic  fires  in   enclosed  car  parks
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :This project is aimed at demonstrating that the
present  standards  of  fire resistance requirements for enclosed car
parks  are  too  conservative,  with  regard  to  the  actual thermal
conditions  produced  by  car  fire,  and  at  proposing  changes  of
regulations  to  relate  to fire curves such as R30 or R60 instead of
R90  or  even  R240.  Numerical  simulations  of spatial temperatures
distributions  shall  be  associated  with realistic thermomechanical
simulations  and  shall  lead  to  conclusions which will improve the
competitivity of steel in such structural applications.

Start date             :1993-07-01
End date               :1996-06-30
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :TESTEELCS 8C
Subprogramme area      :Steel Research Workprogramme - Steel structures
