<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Use of mass spectrometers in underground fire warning systems
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :21721
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Key words              :Mining, CO, gas detection, fire
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Use of mass spectrometers in underground fire
                        warning systems
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Objectives             :In the early stages of a fire the gases CO, NO and
hydrocarbons  are  given  off.  These  gases  are  also  produced  by
shotfiring  and from diesel engine exhausts. In low concentrations it
is  not  clear  what  activity has caused these gases to appear. Mass
spectrometers can identify simultaneously several such substances and
establish  their relative concentration. The aim of the project is to
establish,  in  the  laboratory  and  in  the  Tremonia fire gallery,
whether  mass spectrometers can identify several components and their
relative concentrations simultaneously.

Programme acronym      :MINSAFECS 2C
Subprogramme area      :FIRES; Gas and fire detection
Project reference      :7258-02/139/01
Prime contr org        :Deutsche Montan Technologie
Prime contr country    :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Contact person         :Name:         HEYN W.
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
