<TITLE>
Trials of fire protection devices - 2nd continuation
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :21716
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Key words              :Mining, CO, gas detection, fire
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Trials of fire protection devices - 2nd continuation
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Objectives             :The main objective of this project was to
investigate  the response of different types of sensor to the various
phases  of  combustion  involving fluids: smouldering, incandescence,
open flame.

General information    :One of the aims pursued was to determine the manner
in  which  these  sensors  were affected by exhaust gases from diesel
mine locomotives.
Other aspects concerned
- early detection of a fire in a large airflow;
- the feasibility of using the "LIST" system for monitoring conveyor
  belt temperature;                  
- analysis  of  gases  present at trace concentrations by means of a
  mass spectrometer.
Essentially,  it  was  hoped  to establish whether, in addition to CO
detection,  there  were  other  components of the fire gases or other
techniques which would allow early detection of a fire or heating.

