<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Fire and explosion safety studies 
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :29604
Quality valid. date    :1995-11-17
Update date            :1996-04-15
Title                  :Fire and explosion safety studies of colliery ground
       installations  and  of  the steel industry. Analysis of incidents and
       accidents.   Safety  characteristics  of  coal,  recommendations  for
       prevention    and   protection   applicable   to   industrial   units
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Objectives             :The aim of the project is to:
       - evaluate the safety characteristics of the different types of coal used,
       - analyse the main incidents and accidents,
       - define the risks posed by each type of installation,
       - analyse potential ignition sources,
       - advise on improvements in fire/explosion safety measures.
       The results of the study will be presented in the form of a guide.
       It  will be designed, firstly, to avoid the most frequent errors made
       in  coal  handling,  crushing,  drying  and storing and, secondly, to
       optimize  prevention  and  protection  measures both economically and
       technically.
General information    :Depending on the supply conditions, the coal used
       today  in colliery ground installations and in the steel industry may
       have  widely  differing  characteristics.  A  distinction can be made
       between bulk coal, granular coal and pulverized coal.
       While  the risk of fire, spontaneous heating and explosion is related
       to the nature and particle size of the coal, it is also influenced by
       other factors such as:
       - the choice of materials as regards reaction to fire and fire resistance,
       - the design of the installations,
       - the application of safety regulations, standards and recommendations,
       - the preventive measures and means of protection used.
       The following operations will be studied:
       - Transport of raw coal in confined spaces (tanks, wagons, barges, etc.)
       - Storage of raw coal in stockpiles, silos or bunkers
       - Coal handling (belt, screw, redler, etc. conveyors)
       - Crushing/drying
       - Injection of pulverized coal into blast furnaces
       - Storage and transport of pulverized coal.
       The study will concentrate on:
       - large stockpiles
       - coal handling installations in coking plants
       - crushing plant in thermal power stations
       - crushing and injection installations for blast furnaces.
Start date             :1993-07-01
End date               :1996-06-30
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ECSC-WORKSAFE C
Subprogramme area      :Specific safety requirements of mines
Project reference      :7262-03/307/08
Prime contr org        :INERIS
Prime contr address    :Parc Technologique ALATA  BP 2
Prime contr postcode   :60550
Prime contr town       :Verneuil-en-Halatte
Prime contr region     :R2222 Oise
Prime contr country    :FR (FRANCE)
Contact person         :Name:         LOEDEL, R. (Mr)
       Tel:          +33-44-556677
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
