<TITLE>
Uncontrolled Reactions : Large Scale Venting (LSV), 1988-1991
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19332
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-13
Update date            :1995-08-12
Project acronym        :LSV
Title                  :Uncontrolled Reactions : Large Scale Venting (LSV),
                        1988-1991
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Objectives             :Emergency venting of chemical reactors at industrial
                        scale. Construction and operation of an experimental
						facility.
General information    :Progress to end 1990
Inquire  about interest of European industry and national Governments
to participate in the project.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1991 (expected results)
Definition of main parameters of the experimental programme
The parameters of experimentation must be determined in close contact
with  sponsoring  organizations and future users.  Parameters include
physical  and  chemical  properties of the reaction fluids, operating
conditions, and the plant components to be tested in LSV.
The   following  activities  are  contingent  on  contributions  from
external sources :
Design of facility
The  facility  will  be  designed  with a specialized company up to a
stage  of "preliminary plant design".  This includes flow sheets, lay
out   of  components,  safety  techniques  and  regulations,  general
measurement  techniques,  requirements  of  plant  control  and  data
acquisition, preliminary estimates of construction time schedules and
cost.
Advanced measurement techniques
Devise  a  concept  on the use of advanced measurement techniques for
measurement  of multiphase flow in the vent line, void in reactor and
collection tank, and for chemical analysis techniques.
Short description of evolution of work in 1992
Detailed  engineering : Piping and Instrumentation diagrams, complete
specification  of  all  components,  complete facility documentation,
detailed  cost estimate and construction scheduling, specification of
commissioning procedure.  Call for tender for construction.
Experimental programme : Harmonizing with detailed plant desin;
definition of test matrix.
Advanced measurement techniques : Development of dedicated
instruments.
