<TITLE>
TWO-PHASE CLOUD GROWTH FOLLOWING A SUDDEN RELEASE OF LIQUEFIED GAS.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :11998
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-23
Key words              :Two-phase release, LPG, jet fire, dispersion
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :TWO-PHASE CLOUD GROWTH FOLLOWING A SUDDEN RELEASE
                        OF LIQUEFIED GAS.
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Other indexes          :FLAMMABLE GASES
                        LIQUEFIED GASES
                        SIMULATION TECHNIQUES
                        FLUID FLOW
                        ATMOSPHERES
                        EFFECTS OF TECHNOLOGY
                        RISK EVALUATION

Objectives             :TO PROVIDE A COMPREHENSIVE SET OF DATA TO ALLOW
VALIDATION OF EXISTING MODELS AND DEVELOPMENT OF NEW TECHNIQUES.

General information    :THIS CONTRACT FORMS PART OF A JOINT
PROJECT:"TWO-PHASE  RELEASES  OF  TOXIC  AND  FLAMMABLE  SUBSTANCES -
THERMAL  INITIATION, SOURCE TERM AND FIRE EFFECTS".TOXIC OR FLAMMABLE
FLUIDS  USED  IN  INDUSTRY  ARE  COMMONLY  STORED  UNDER  PRESSURE AS
LIQUEFIED  GASES.  ACCIDENTAL  LOSS  OF  CONTAINMENT  CAN BE TOTAL OR
PARTIAL  AS  IN TANK FAILURE OR SMALL BREAK FROM PIPEWORK.THE ENSUING
TWO  PHASE  PROCESSES  GOVERNING  VAPOUR  CLOUD  FORMATION ARE LITTLE
UNDERSTOOD.  THE  PROPOSED  PROGRAMME OF WORK WILL ATTEMPT TO RECTIFY
THIS  BY PROVIDING A COMPREHENSIVE SET OF DATA TO ALLOW VALIDATION OF
EXISTING  MODELS  AND  DEVELOPMENT  OF  NEW  TECHNIQUES.IT  WILL HELP
CHARACTERISE  BEHAVIOUR  IN  TERMS  OF  MATERIAL  PROPERTIES, STORAGE
CONDITIONS  AND  DISCHARGE  GEOMETRY.  THE  PROPOSED WORK FALLS INTRO
THREE MAIN AREAS :(1) CONTINUOUS TWO PHASE FLASHING RELEASES.
A)  A  LABORATORY STUDY OF THE STRUCTURE OF JETS OF FREON-1L USING AN
       EXISTING TEST RIG.
B) A LARGER SCALE STUDY ON AN EXISTING TEST RIG OUTDOORS.
2) INSTANTANEOUS FLASING RELEASES
   THE WORK IS TO BE CARRIED OUT ON THESE SEPARATE EXPERIMENTAL RIGS;
A) FREON-1L  INITIALLY  CONTAINED  IN  0.02M3 GLASS SPHERES OR METAL
   HEMISPHERES  WILL  BE  INSTANTANEOUSLY RELEASED FROM A WIDE  RANGE OF
   STORAGE CONDITIONS.
B) ALTERNATIVE  CONTAINMENT  SYSTEMS  WILL BE MANUFACTURED TO ENABLE
   SIMILAR  QUANTITIES  OF PROPANE, BUTANE OR FREON-1L TO BE RELEASED IN
   THE OPEN AIR OR IN S SAFE AREA.
C) IT  IS  PROPOSED TO UNDERTAKE A LIMITED NUMBER OF ONE-DIMENSIONAL
   SIMULATIONS OF THE FLASH EXPANSION PROCESS USING A SHOCK TUBE. 
   (3)OVERALL SUMMARY REPORT.

Start date             :1987-11-01
End date               :1990-10-31
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Completed
