<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Uncontrolled reactions : Release and dispersion of chemically reacting 
                         multiphase,1988-1991
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19336
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-13
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Uncontrolled reactions : Release and dispersion of
                        chemically reacting multiphase,1988-1991
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

To develop and assess computer models for:
1. Emergency  release of multicomponent fluid mixtures from chemical
   reactors (RELIEF code)
2. Dispersion of dense vapour clouds in terrain with obstacles.
   The  computation results of the vapour cloud dispersion model provide
   the   input   for   a   numerical  tool  describing  detonation  (see
   workschedule : numerical simulation of reacting gas flows).
General information    :Progress to end 1990

1.  Code  RELIEF  :  Further development of the code (a) inclusion of
capability  to  compute  axial  variation of component concentrations
inside  the  vessel,(b)formulation of a 1-D vent line model with
liquid  phase  chemical  reaction. Code  application  to  exothermic
chemical systems with gas generation (hydrogen peroxide
decomposition)(ref. 1). Completion of a basic study on
non-equilibrium effects in the vent line (ref. 2.Installation of a
physical property database, PPDS.
2. Vapour cloud dispersion : Continuing development of the 3-D finite
volume  code  ADREA-HF  aimed  at  speed  up  and improvement of code
structure.   Code  documentation.   Development  of an "intermediate"
computer  model  based  on  shallow  water  approach, providing a one
dimensional   simplified   treatment   of  isothermal  dispersion  in
irregular  terrain.  Start of code validation applying windtunnel-and
test   field-data.   All  the  above  work  is  in  the  frame  of  a
collaboration  agreement  between  JRC  and  the "Demokritos" Ctre of
Greece.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1991 (expected results)
1.  Code  RELIEF  :  Development and implementation of a userfriendly
input  and  output  processor  (window  techniques), extension of the
code's  capability to track void fraction discontinuities, completion
of code documentation, validation using experimental data provided by
the MPMC facility  at  JRC  (see  workschedule  MPMC)  and  other
laboratories,  application  to industrial installations, inclusion of
catch tank model.
2.  Vapour  cloud  dispersion  :  Extension  of the capability of the
"intermediate" model by including energy conservation and introducing
a  2-D  flow  capability.     Improvement  and  qualification  of the
2-phase flow capability of ADREA-HF. Continuing code validation.
Interaction with the Shared Cost Action Programme STEP.
Short description of evolution of work in 1992
1.   Code  RELIEF  :  Continuing  application  installations  in  the
chemical/process  industry,  and  use of the code as a predictive and
post-test  analysis  tool,  extension  of the code's capabilities for
design  purposes  and  to  describe  down  stream equipment in relief
systems  2. Vapour  cloude  dispersion  :  continuation  of  1991
activities.   Emphasis  on  validation  and code application for risk
analysis and mitigation  2
Start date             :1988-01-01
End date               :1992-01-01
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :INDHAZ 2C
Project reference      :0011
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute for Safety and Technology
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
