<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
RESEARCH ON CONTINUOUS AND INSTANTANEOUS HEAVY GAS CLOUDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :12006
Quality valid. date    :1993-04-19
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :RESEARCH ON CONTINUOUS AND INSTANTANEOUS HEAVY GAS
                        CLOUDS
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Other indexes          :ATMOSPHERES
                        CLOUDS
                        DATA ANALYSIS
                        EFFECTS OF TECHNOLOGY
                        FLUID FLOW
                        GASES
                        RISK EVALUATION
                        STATISTICAL ANALYSIS
Objectives             :TO ESTABLISH, FROM THE EXPERIMENTAL DATA, SIMPLE
PARAMETRIC  REPRESENTATIONS  OF  THE  EVOLUTION  OF  THE  PROBABILITY
DENSITY FUNCTION OF CONCENTRATION.
General information    :THE WORK TO BE UNDERTAKEN BY HSE IS IN THREE PARTS.
I)  THE  FIRST  PART IS TO ANALYSE WIND TUNNEL DATA OBTAINED PRIOR TO
THE  START OF THIS PROJECT BY WARREN SPRING LABORATORY UNDER CONTRACT
TO  HSE. THESE DATA SIGNIFICANTLY EXTEND THE DATABASE RELEVANT TO THE
VARIABILITY  OF  THE  DISPERSION PROCESS IN OPEN AND FLAT TERRAIN FOR
THORNEY  ISLAND  TYPE  RELEASES.  REPLICATED EXPERIMENTS WILL PROVIDE
DATA  ON THE VARIABLE IN CONCENTRATION LEVELS AT A NUMBER OF DOWNWIND
LOCATIONS.  THE  EXPERIMENTS COVER A RANGE OF INITIAL BULK RICHARDSON
NUMBERS.  THIS  EXTENSIVE  SET  OF  DATA REPRESENTS NEW AND IMPORTANT
KNOWLEDGE;  IN  PARTICULAR  THEY  PROVIDE  A  BASIS FOR ASSESSING THE
EFFECT OF OBSTACLES ON THE DEGREE OF VARIABILITY.
A STATISTICAL THEORY WILL BE DEVELOPED AND COMPUTERISED. THE SOFTWARE
WILL BE EXERCISED ON THE HSE MAINFRAME TO ANALYSE THE ABOVE DATA SET.
THE  PURPOSE  OF  THE ANALYSIS IS TO ESTABLISH, IF POSSIBLE, A SIMPLE
EXPRESSION  FOR  THE VARIABILITY IN CONCENTRATION LEVEL AS A FUNCTION
OF THE RELEVANT INDEPENDENT VARIABLES. ONE OF THE RESULTS WILL BE THE
EVOLUTION  OF THE PROBABILITY DENSITY FUNCTION (PDF) OF CONCENTRATION
AT  A  GIVEN LOCATION AS A FUNCTION OF TIME. THESE PDFS WILL FORM THE
BASIS   OF   THE   WORK  TO  ESTABLISH  SIMPLE  MODELS  SUITABLE  FOR
INCORPORATING  INTO BOX MODELS. PARTICULAR ATTENTION WILL BE GIVEN TO
THE RESPECTIVE NEEDS OF TOXIC AND FLAMMABLE HAZARD ASSESSMENTS.
II)  THE  SECOND  PART  OF  THE  HSE PROGRAMME WILL BE TO ESSENTIALLY
REPEAT  THE  ANALYTICAL  EXERCICE, SUITABLY MODIFIED IF NECESSARY, TO
DERIVE  SIMILAR  QUANTITIES  FOR  THE DATA SETS FOR DISPERSION IN THE
PRESENCE  OF  OBSTACLES  GATHERED BY WARREN SPRING LABORATORY AND THE
UNIVERSITY OF HAMBURG UNDER PHASE 2 OF THE JOINT PROJECT.
III)  FINALLY,  HSE,  IN  VIEW  OF  ITS EXPERTISE IN DISPERSION FIELD
TRIALS  WILL  PROVIDE  ADVICE  TO  RISO UNDER PHASE 1, 2 AND 5 OF THE
JOINT  PROJECT.  ASSISTANCE WILL ALSO BE GIVEN WITH THE EVALUATION OF
THE RESULTS DERIVED FROM THE CASE STUDY ON CONTINUOUS RELEASES.
Start date             :1987-11-01
End date               :1990-10-31
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :TECHHAZ C
Subprogramme area      :DISPERSION (86-90)
Project reference      :EV4T0005
Prime contr org        :Health and Safety Executive
Prime contr postcode   :W2 4TF
Prime contr town       :London
Prime contr region     :R755 GREATER LONDON
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
