<TITLE>
RESEARCH ON CONTINUOUS AND INSTANTANEOUS HEAVY GAS CLOUDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :12005
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-23
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :RESEARCH ON CONTINUOUS AND INSTANTANEOUS HEAVY GAS
                        CLOUDS
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Other indexes          :GASES
                        WIND TUNNELS
                        CLOUDS
                        FLUID FLOW
                        DIGITAL SIMULATION
                        EFFECTS OF TECHNOLOGY
                        RISK EVALUATION
Objectives             :TO PROVIDE IMPROVED METHODS WHETHER NUMERICAL OR
PHYSICAL   TO   PREDICT   THE   BEHAVIOUR   OF   HEAVY   GAS   CLOUDS
General information    :THE SPECIFIC ACTIVITIES OF TNO ARE DESCRIBED BELOW.
PHASE 2.2  THE  MAIN  ACTIVITY OF TNO WILL BE TO PERFORM WIND TUNNEL
EXPERIMENTS   ON   CONTINUOUS  RELEASES  OF  HEAVY  GASES.  TNO  WILL
PARTICIPATE  IN  THE  INTERCOMPARISON OF WIND TUNNELS WITH RESPECT TO
HEAVY  GAS  DISPERSION.  THIS  MEANS THAT ABOUT 2 SELECTED FULL SCALE
CONTINUOUS  RELEASES  (TO  BE CARRIED OUT BY RISO IN THE FRAMEWORK OF
THE TOTAL PROJECT) WILL BE SIMULATED.
PHASE  2.3  AFTERWARDS,  TNO  WILL  CONCENTRATE  ON  THE MODELLING OF
CONTINUOUS  RELEASES,  BASED  ON  THE  FULL  SCALE  EXPERIMENTS TO BE
CARRIED  OUT  BY  RISO.  THE  WIND TUNNEL STUDY WILL INCLUDE A LARGER
NUMBER   OF  OBSTACLE  AND  SOURCE  GEOMETRIES.  ABOUT  20  DIFFERENT
SOURCE/OBSTACLE  COMBINATIONS  (SELECTED  DURING  PHASE  0.3) WILL BE
STUDIED.
THE  TNO  WIND-TUNNEL  EXPERIMENTS  WILL  HEAVILY LAY EMPHASIS ON THE
MEASUREMENT  OF  FLUCTUATING   CONCENTRATIONS  WITHIN  THE STEADY GAS
CLOUD  AS  A  FUNCTION  OF  SOURCE AND OBSTACLE GEOMETRY AND POSITION
PHASE   3   THESE  MEASUREMENTS  WILL  BE  ANALYZED  USING  THE  SAME
STATISTICAL  TECHNIQUES  AS DEVELOPED BY HSE TO STUDY THE VARIABILITY
OF CONCENTRATION IN INSTANTANEOUS CLOUDS.
PHASE  4  CALCULATIONS WITH SIMPLE BOXMODELS AVAILABLE AT TNO WILL BE
PERFORMED.  THE  INFLUENCE  OF OBSTACLES WILL BE INCORPORATED BY SOME
SIMPLES RULES OF THUMB.
PHASE  5  TNO  WILL CARRY OUT THE WIND-TUNNEL SIMULATIONS OF THE FULL
SCALE  EXPERIMENTS  AT A REAL INDUSTRIAL SITE. THESE SIMULATIONS WILL
BE  USED TO VALIDATE THE USE OF WIND TUNNELS FOR PRACTICAL SITUATIONS
OF HEAVY GAS DISPERSION.
PHASE  6  PROGRESS  REPORTS AND FINAL REPORT ABOUT THE TNO ACTIVITIES
WILL  BE  PRODUCED.  AN  EXECUTIVE  SUMMARY  WILL  BE  PRODUCED AFTER
AGREEMENT WITH THE PARTNERS IN THE PROJECT.
PHASE 7 TNO WILL COORDINATE THE ACTIVITIES OF ALL PARTNERS WITHIN THE
PROJECT.  THERE  WILL  ABOUT  8  MEETINGS  OF THE PARTNERS DURING THE
PROJECT.  TNO  WILL  NOT  BE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE
OTHER PARTNERS.
Start date             :1987-11-01
End date               :1990-10-31
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :TECHHAZ C
Subprogramme area      :DISPERSION (86-90)
Project reference      :EV4T0004
