<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Dispersion of two-phase flashing release - fiel experiment
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :5171
Quality valid. date    :1995-03-06
Update date            :1995-08-11
Project acronym        :FLADIS
Title                  :Dispersion of two-phase flashing release - field
                        experiment
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)
General information    :The main objective of this project is to perform
dispersion experiments with a two-phase jet release of liquefied ammonia.
The initially  dense  jet will gradually change to a passively dispersing
plume  due  to  the  entrainment and heat transfer. Both the mean and
fluctuating part of the concentration and flow field Will be measured
in  all  the  dispersion  phases,  with Special attention to the heat
budget  including  air  moisture. The release rate, initial enthalpy,
initial momentum and ambient wind conditions and other meteorological
measurements  will be integrated in the data set. The experiment will
support  the  work  of  the FLADIS project previously financed by the
STEP programme, and close collaboration with this research group will
be  established.  Development  of a numerical model based on 2-D flow
equations is also proposed. This kind of model will have more details
than  the  traditional dense gas 'box'- models used in practical risk
analysis,  but  it  will  be  simpler  and  easier  to  run  than the
computationally expensive 3-D models.
Start date             :1993-01-01
End date               :1995-12-31
Duration in months     :36
