<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Partial inertisation with nitrogen
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Key words              :Explosion, dust explosion, inertisation, nitrogen
Record cntrl number    :21728
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Partial inertisation with nitrogen as a means of
                        preventing the initiation and propagation of a 
                        coal dust explosion
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Nitrogen purging is now widely practised in the European Community as a 
means of fighting open and deep-seated fires in mines. The atmosphere near 
the fire may be flammable as a result of the mixture of methane with the 
products of pyrolysis or combustion and there is a risk of a gas or coal-
dust explosion as long as the air reaching the seat of the fire is not 
sufficiently inerted.

