<TITLE>
Propagation of fire along electric cables and lines
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :21712
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Key words              :Mining, fire test method, electric cable
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Propagation of fire along electric cables and lines
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Objectives             :The main purpose of the project was to check, by
means  of  full-scale  fire gallery tests, whether the laboratory and
reduced-scale tests prescribed by the German standard (VDE 0472, Part
804)  were adequate to assess the fire risk resulting from the use of
cables below ground.

General information    :A further aim  was to compile  information on
the time for which electric cables and lines could maintain the power
supply in the event of a fire, with particular  reference to means of
communication: telephone and telemetry lines, etc.

Programme acronym      :MINSAFECS 2C
Subprogramme area      :FIRES; Material fire tests
Project reference      :7258-02/102/01
