<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Investigation into the safety of enclosures
FROM WHEAT 
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Key words              :Flame trap, electrical equipment, ignition source, 
                        explosion, mining
Record cntrl number    :21769
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Investigation into the safety of enclosures for
                        electrical apparatus for which wide-are flame traps 
                        provide pressure relief - experimental study
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

In mines where firedamp is an explosion hazard electrical equipment capable 
of causing ignition during normal operation must be provided with 
flameproof enclosures. Such enclosures are heavy, bulky and expensive to 
manufacture. The aim of this project was to test a pressure relief module 
from the USA to determine whether it conforms to European equipment 
standards.

Programme acronym      :MINSAFECS 2C 
Subprogramme area      :ELECTRICITY; Study of flameproof enclosures
Project reference      :7258-07/077/01
