<TITLE>
Effectiveness of triggered barriers against explosions in auxiliary-ventilated workings
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Key words           :Explosion, explosion suppression, mining, flame trap
Record cntrl number :21744
Quality valid. date :1994-05-08
Update date         :1995-08-12
Title               :Effectiveness of triggered barriers against
                     explosions in auxiliary-ventilated  workings
Subject index codes :SAF (SAFETY)
Objectives          :To investigate the performance of a category of triggered 
                     water barriers (the Belgian triggered system) in 
                     suppressing explosions in coal mines.

At present, it is envisage that the Belgian barrier will be used mainly in blind ends, eg in drivages.
It was proposed to study changes in its effectiveness as a function of 
increasing distance  between the head end and the barrier, since this distance 
is variable and may affect barrier performance.

