<HEAD>
<TITLE>
DISTRIBUTED TEMPERATURE SENSOR
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :30443
Quality valid. date    :1995-11-21
Update date            :1996-04-15
Title                  :DISTRIBUTED TEMPERATURE SENSOR
Other indexes          : 
        ACCIDENT PREVENTION
        SAFETY TECHNOLOGY
        WARNING SYSTEMS
        RELIABILITY
        OPTICAL FIBRES
        OPTICAL DETECTION
Objectives             :To demonstrate that a distributed fibre optic
       temperature  sensor (DTS) used as an early warning fire/heat detector
       can  give  an  improved system for fire detection on offshore oil/gas
       production  platforms.  Critical factors to be tested out will be the
       long  term  reliability  of the system in such environments including
       the  ability  of the fibre optic sensing cable to withstand the tough
       North Sea weather conditions and rough working environment.
General information    :The DTS based system is meant to replace the heat
       detectors  presently  in  use.  One  length  of  fibre  cable will be
       equivalent to a number of point detectors.
       This  technology is to be tested out on offshore oil/gas platforms in
       order  to  find out if it will give an improved heat detection system
       for  early  warning fire alarm systems. In this context the long term
       reliability  of  the  system  in  such  an  environment including the
       ability of the fibre optic sensing cable to withstand the tough North
       Sea  weather conditions, the corrosive sea air, and the rough working
       environment on a platform.
Programme acronym      :JOULE/THERMIE
Subprogramme area      :OIL AND GAS - MISCELLANEOUS
Project reference      :OG./00111/95/NO/UK
Prime contr org        :AUTRONICA AS
Prime contr postcode   :7005
Prime contr town       :TRONDHEIM
Prime contr region     :NO16 Soer-Troendelag
Prime contr country    :NO (NORWAY)
Contact person         :Name:         NOT AVAILABLE
       Tel:          +47-73581000
       Fax:          +47-73939120
 
