<HEAD>
<TITLE>
PHYSICAL MODELLING OF TORCH FIRES
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :12010
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-23
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :PHYSICAL MODELLING OF TORCH FIRES
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Other indexes          :EFFECTS OF TECHNOLOGY
                        RISK EVALUATION
                        FIRES
                        SIMULATION TECHNIQUES
                        WIND TUNNELS
Objectives             :DEVELOP PROCEDURES WHICH ENABLE RELIABLE AND
ACCURATE  SIMULATION  OF  FULL SCALE FIRES IN AN ATMOSPHERIC BOUNDARY
LAYER WIND.
General information    :TNO'S SPECIFIC TASK WITHIN THE PROJECT WILL BE TO
DEVELOP   PROCEDURES   ACCORDING   TO   WHICH   RELIABLE  WIND-TUNNEL
SIMULATIONS WITH REAL FLAMES OF FULL SCALE TORCH FIRE CAN BE CARRIED
OUT.DURING   THE  FIRST  STAGE  OF  THE  PROJECT  SCALING  RULES  FOR
WIND-TUNNEL  MODELLING  WILL  BE  DERIVED  FROM THEORETICAL ANALYSIS,
ASSISTANCE  WILL  BE  GIVEN  TO THE SELECTION OF THE SITUATIONS TO BE
STUDIED  WITHIN  THE PROJECT, MEASURING EQUIPMENT FOR THE WIND-TUNNEL
EXPERIMENTS  WILL  BE  SELECTED  AND  WIND-TUNNEL TESTS FOR IDEALIZED
SITUATIONS  WITHOUT  OBSTACLES  WILL  BE  PERFORMED.AT THE END OF THE
FIRST  STAGE  DATA  OBTAINED  FROM  THE  WIND-TUNNEL  TESTS  WILL  BE
EVALUATED AGAINST FIELD DATA AND DATA FROM NUMERICAL ANALYSIS.
DURING THE SECOND STAGE OF THE PROJECT, DEPENDING ON THE RESULTS FROM
THE  FIRST STAGE , THE MODELLING TECHNIQUE WILL BE ADJUSTED.AFTEWARDS
MORE  COMPLEX SITUATIONS WITH SIMPLE OBSTACLES WILL BE STUDIED IN THE
WIND TUNNEL.
A  FINAL  REPORT  ON THE TNO ACTIVITIES WILL BE PRODUCED.FURTHER, TNO
WILL  INITIATE  THE  TEXT  OF AN EXECUTIVE SUMMARY ON THE TOTAL JOINT
PROJECT,   BASED   ON   THE   REPORTS  OF  THE  OTHERS  PARTNERS.ALSO
RECOMMENDATIONS FOR THE "HOT" MODELLING OF FIRES IN WIND TUNNELS WILL
BE GENERATED.TNO WILL COORDINATE THE TOTAL JOINT PROJECT.
Start date             :1987-11-01
End date               :1991-06-30
Duration in months     :44
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :TECHHAZ C
Subprogramme area      :CATASTROPHIC FIRES (86-90)
Project reference      :EV4T0003
Prime contr org        :Nederlandse Organisatie voor Toegepast
                        Natuurwetenschappelijk Onderzoek
Prime contr postcode   :2595 CL
Prime contr town       :Den Haag
Prime contr country    :NL (NETHERLANDS)
Contact person         :Name:         BUILTJES P.J.H.
                    Tel:          +31-55-773344
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
