<TITLE>
Increase of the fire stability of steel structures with protective means
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :18232
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-24
Key words              :Steel buildings, fire protection measures
Update date            :1995-08-28
Title                  :Increase of the fire stability of steel structures
                        with protective means
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :This collaborative research project is intended to
derive  concepts  which  will  decrease  the  cost  of protection and
increase  the number of systems available by minimizing the number of
tests and increasing their accuracy. Tests will be carried out on the
four  most  commonly  employed methods of thermal protection: contour
and  box  protection,  intumescent  products,  partition  walls,  and
suspended ceilings.

