<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Processing of fire resistant composites by resin transfer moulding (RTM)
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Key words              :Fire resistance, fire
Record cntrl number    :23388
Quality valid. date    :1994-12-16
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Processing of fire resistant composites by resin
                        transfer moulding (RTM)
Subject index codes    :AER (AEROSPACE TECHNOLOGY)
                        IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)
Other indexes          :Automotive, Components & Parts
                        Processing (rubber & plastic)
                        Composites (polymer matrix)
                        Materials characterization/Testing
                        Railways/Locomotive
                        Engineering (mechanical)
                        Fibres/Reinforcing materials
                        Reliability

General information    :Fire resistance is a requirement that composites
materials  must  resolve,  mainly  in transport (bus, railway, naval,
aeronautic...) and building areas. Materials used at present for fire
resistant aplications are polyesther resin charged by flame retardant
agents. These materials carry out fire requirements but do not fulfil
standards concerning emisions of toxic gases and smoke density, which
are more important in a mass scale burning than fire itself. The only
resin  classified  in order to improve fire resistance with non toxic
gases and low smoke density requirements are phenolic resins.
Howether,  these  resins are not appropriated to be processed by hand
lay-up,  spray-up  or RTM technologies which are the wider in use for
transport and  building sectors. The aim of this project  is to adapt
and formulate  phenolic resin and modify  the  RTM process  to obtain
fire resistant composite materials with improved processing aspect.

Programme acronym      :CRAFT
Subprogramme area      :STRUCTURAL MATERIALS - Polymers and polymer matrix
                        composites; MASS COMMODITY MATERIALS - 
						New construction industry materials; MANUFACTURING
						-  Manufacturing  techniques  for  industrial  use
						of advanced materials 
project reference      :CR150291/BRE21435
Prime contr org        :Mariskone
Prime contr address    :Bo. Ugaldetxo, Centro Mayoristat no.22
Prime contr postcode   :20180
Prime contr town       :Oyarzun
Prime contr region     :RB212 Guipuzcoa
