<TITLE>
Buckling curves in case of fire
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :7347
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-24
Key words              :Steel buildings, fire resistance
Update date            :1995-08-28
Title                  :Buckling curves in case of fire, M-N interaction
                       (Part III)
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :This multinational research is aimed at providing a
simplified method of calculating the buckling behaviour of hot rolled
steel sections subject to fire to satisfy the requirements of Part 10
of  Eurocode  3 concerned with Structural Fire Design. The works will
involve  theoretical  simulations,  data  collection  and analysis; a
number  of  full  scale  fire tests shall be conducted to confirm the
theoretical  analysis and include an extension to previous results by
taking into account the effect of load eccentricity.

Start date             :1992-07-01
End date               :1995-06-30
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :TESTEELCS 8C
