<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Steel properties and structural behaviour in fire
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :6852
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-24
Key words              :Steel buildings, fire resistance
Update date            :1995-08-28
Title                  :Steel properties and structural behaviour in fire
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :These three proposals (inclusive P1861 and P1888)
have been coordinated in order to constitute a uniform programme. The
aim of this research project is to boost the economic return on steel
and  steel  composite structures by means of realistic assessments of
component  and  structural behaviour. These should form part of these
investigations  by  using  existing knowledge. Preparing new data and
identifying  the  hitherto unused reserves contained in the behaviour
of structures  in  fire,  and  thus  above  all  making the ultimate
transition from ISO pyrotechnic stressing to natural conflagrations.
Greater  use  will be made in the investigations of numerical methods
as  this  would  make the results more generally valid. These results
will   be   summarized  in  recommendations  intended  for  practical
application.

Start date             :1986-07-01
End date               :1989-06-30
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Actual end date        :1990-06-30
