<TITLE>
Practical tools for the design of unprotected steel beams
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :6849
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-24
Key words              :Steel buildings, fire resistance, guidelines
Update date            :1995-08-28
Title                  :Practical tools for the design of unprotected steel
                        beams for uprights exposed to fire
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :The project now centres on use of the theoretical
computer  model evolved during the earlier phases in order to develop
practical  tools  for  the  design  of  steel  columns  to  which all
potential  users would have access. The proposed programme is divided
into two parts covering: 
- fire tests on unprotected steel columns; 
- the  preparation  of  design  diagrams for those columns, due account
  being  taken  of  beam  type, column length, loading, fire-resistance
  class and the steel grades used.

