<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Combustion behaviour of upholstered furniture
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :27320
Quality valid. date    :1995-06-19
Key words              :Furniture, fire safety concept, fire test method
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Combustion behaviour of upholstered furniture
Subject index codes    :MEA (MEASUREMENT METHODS)
                        REF (REFERENCE MATERIALS)
                        STA (STANDARDS)

General information    :This project is being carried out in order to
provide  a  scientific  basis for the development of the test methods
that  would be needed for the implementation of a future directive on
the  fire safety of upholstered furniture. Both large scale and small
scale   test   methods  for  determining  the  burning  behaviour  of
upholstered furniture will be developed. The large scale test method,
for  testing  whole  items  of  furniture,  will  be  based  upon the
furniture calorimeter (NT FIRE 032). The small scale test method, for
testing  small  (0.01  m{2}) composite samples of the fabrics and the
paddings  used  in  the construction of furniture, will be based upon
the  cone  calorimeter  (ISO  5660).   In  each  case,  the main fire
parameters  considered  will  be  rate  of heat release and smoke and
toxic  gas production. Relationships between the results of the small
scale  and  the large scale tests and the conditions which occur in a
full  scale  room  due to the burning of an item of furniture will be
developed  and  validated  for  a  representative  range of furniture
designs  and  materials.  The  measured  conditions  in fire tests of
furniture  in  full  scale  rooms will be interpreted by carrying out
fire  hazard  analysis  and  identifying  the time for which a person
could  survive  in the room, and still be able to escape by the door,
despite  the  heat,  smoke  and  toxic  gases produced by the burning
furniture in the room. At the time of  writing,  the  project  is  on 
schedule to be completed at the end of 1994, as planned, and all  the 
testing has been completed. A detailed test protocol has  been  deve-
loped for the cone calorimeter which  enables accurate and repeatable
measurements to be made on composite  samples of furniture materials.
Initial results obtained with a model  that  has  been  developed  in 
order to be able to predict the results of cone calorimeter tests  on
composite samples from the results of cone calorimeter tests on indi-
vidual component materials appear to very  encouraging.  The  results
of the fire tests of furniture in full scale rooms are being compared
with predictions based on, firstly, furniture  calorimeter  data  and 
room fire modelsand, secondly, cone calorimeter furniture fire models
and correlations.  The  final  report on all the work carried out  in 
this project will be available in early 1995.

Start date             :1993-01-01
End date               :1994-12-31
Duration in months     :24
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :MAT
Project reference      :MAT1920005
Prime contr org        :Dansk Brandteknisk Institut
Prime contr address    :108 Amager Boulevard
Prime contr postcode   :2300
