<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Development of design rules for steel structures
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23346
Quality valid. date    :1994-11-28
Key words              :Steel buildings, fire, fire safety concept, 
                        standards, large compartments
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Development of design rules for steel structures
                        subjected to realistic fires in large compartments
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :The aim  of this  research is  to demonstrate 
that real fire conditions  for large  compartments (Atriums, Stations
halls, Industrial  buildings)  are such that the present fire regula-
tions of the  Standards are too  severe for steel  structures, and to
define new requirements which better correspond to real fire conditions.
Thermomechanical  simulations  using  sophisticated computer programs
shall  result  in more realistic ISO fire resistance requirements for
each type of building as a function of their specific parameters.

Start date             :1993-07-01
End date               :1996-06-30
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :TESTEELCS 8C
Subprogramme area      :Steel Research Workprogramme - Steel structures
Project reference      :7210-SA/932
Prime contr org        :CSI-PRODUCTOS LARGOS
Prime contr address    :Paseo de la Castellana 91- 1a Planta
Prime contr postcode   :28046
