<HEAD>
<TITLE>
FIRE TESTING
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :24403
Quality valid. date    :1995-03-15
Key words              :Fire test method, heat flux
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :FIRE TESTING
Subject index codes    :MEA (MEASUREMENT METHODS)
                        REF (REFERENCE MATERIALS)
                        STA (STANDARDS)

General information    :The first part of the project investigated
calibration  methods  for transducers measuring radiant heat flux. At
SP  calibrations  were  performed  using  a  black-body  cavity  as a
radiation  source.  At  FRS  calibrations  were  performed  against a
secondary  standard  radiant heat flux meter that was traceable to an
absolute   method  of  measuring  radiant  heat  flux  based  on  the
temperature rise of a copper block as a function of time. The  second
part  of  the  project  investigated  the  use  of plate thermometers
to  measure  the  temperature  to  which  construction  products  are
subjected during fire resistance tests in furnaces of various designs.
Plate thermometers have a  much larger  surface  area  than  ordinary
thermocouples and it had been suggested that they would  ensure  that
furnaces of different designs would  expose  specimens  to  identical
heating  conditions.  Two  tests  were carried out in four  laborato-
ries. In the first  test  the  furnaces  temperature  was  controlled 
using  ordinary  ISO  standard  thermocouples  and in the second with 
plate thermometers. 
RESULTS Calibrations of radiant heat flux meters  using  the  methods
used by SP and  FRS produced systematic differences of upto 8 %.  The
reasons for these differences are  not  clear  and  are  still  being
discussed. The differences in temperature between the different  fire 
resistance furnaces were considerably  less when  the  furnaces  were
controlled by plate  thermometers  instead  of  thermocouples.  After 
45 minutes, for example, the differences were less than 10 C  instead 
of more than 100 C.

Programme acronym      :BCR 4
Project reference      :MTR164
Prime contr org        :Statens Provensanstalt
Prime contr country    :SE (SWEDEN)
Organization           :Fire Research Station
Country                :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Organization           :Bundesanstalt fuer Materialforschung und Pruefung
Country                :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Organization           :Centre Scientifique et Technique du Batiment
Country                :FR (FRANCE)
Organization           :Centro Studi ed Esperienze
Country                :IT (ITALY)
Organization           :Loss Prevention Council
Country                :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
</BODY>
