<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Fire gallery tests for non-metallic materials intended for underground use
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :21711
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Key words              :Mining, fire test method
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Fire gallery tests for non-metallic materials
                        intended for underground use
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Objectives             :The aim of the project was to establish agreed
criteria  and  test procedures for the fire testing of large items of
non-metallic  materials  in  three  existing  fire galleries: that of
British  Coal,  at  their  Yorkshire Research Laboratories (YRL), the
Buxton  gallery  of  the  Health  and  Safety Executive (HSE) and the
German fire gallery at the Tremonia experimental mine.

General information    :The project set out to obtain three-dimensional
temperature data for the fire galleries in order to seek confirmation
of  the  temperature  stratification phenomenon and to provide a data
bank  which  would assist theoretical and practical studies. The work
described in ECSC Research Project No 7255-10/058/08, which sought to
establish  conditions  under which each of these three fire galleries
could produce similar fire regimes, was used as a starting point.

Programme acronym      :MINSAFECS 2C
Subprogramme area      :FIRES; Material fire tests
Project reference      :7258-02/098/08
Prime contr org        :British Coal
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Contact person         :Name:         SMITH P.G.
 
