<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Simultaneous development of chemical process, process engineering 
machinery and process-control-systems with special reference to 
low-temperature-desulphurisation
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23890
Quality valid. date    :1995-02-22
Update date            :1995-08-28
Title                  :Simultaneous development of chemical process,
process   engineering   machinery  and  process-control-systems  with
special       reference      to      low-temperature-desulphurisation
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF  (SAFETY)
General information    :As no experience exists concerning the applicability
of  neural  networks  and  Fuzzy  Logic  in  the field of controlling 
process  and  maschine,  the  present  project  will  investigate an 
installation  for  a new low temperature desulphurisation process the 
effects  of  these  technologies  on  the machines and on the process 
cycles  in  order  to  transfer  the  results  on a number of process 
engineering  installations.  The  main  aim  of  the  project  is  an 
absorption rate of 100 % which may result in sulphur free exhaust gas
The  development  and  design  of machines for process engineering is
marked  by  a  highly sequential procedure. Usually first of all, the
process  is  developed.  The corresponding installation are following
and  finally,  devices  for  open-loop control, automatic control and
monitoring  are  designed.  Due to the fact that demands of posterior
states  of  development are known quite late in the development cycle
and  might  cause important changes or, in wors case, cannot be taken
into  consideration at all, this procedure does not always assure the
optimum  result.  It would be better to recognize these demands at an
earlier stage and to take them into account in the process of design.
This  could  be  done  by  establishing  new rules for the design for
control.  A  combination  of the activities during the development of
machines and installations for process engineering is necessary under
the point of view of Simultaneous Engineering.
It  is  possible  to use neural networks combined with Fuzzy Logic in
the sector  of  process  engineering  machines  and  processes  for
monitoring and  as  closed loop and control. A large part of process
engineering processes is marked by a multitude of parameters changing
over  time  concerning  their influence on the process cycle. As this
happens  in  processes that ought to be steadystate processes, due to
the  complexity  of  the process and the multitude of parameters, the
remaining  in  the range of optimum efficiency cannot be reached with
common technologies.   This  would  be  possible  by  means  of  an
intelligent  open-loop  control that records all parameters and emits
an adequate signal corresponding to the process cycle.
Start date             :1994-09-01
End date               :1997-08-31
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0567
Prime contr org        :Technische Universitaet Clausthal
Prime contr dept       :Institut fuer Maschinenwesen
Prime contr address    :32 Robert-Koch-Strasse
Prime contr postcode   :38678
Prime contr town       :Clausthal-Zellerfeld
Prime contr region     :R13A6 Goslar
Prime contr country    :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Contact person         :Name:         DIETZ, PETER
