<HEAD>
<TITLE>
PILOT IMPLEMENTATION OF A FIBRE OPTICS METHANE DETECTION SYSTEM FOR
OFFSHORE PLATFORMS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23413
Quality valid. date    :1995-01-24
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :PILOT IMPLEMENTATION OF A FIBRE OPTICS METHANE
                        DETECTION SYSTEM FOR OFFSHORE PLATFORMS
Subject index codes    :ESV (ENERGY SAVING)
                        FFU (FOSSIL FUELS)
                        RSE (RENEWABLE SOURCES OF ENERGY)
Other indexes          :ENERGY (PHYSICS)
                        ENERGY RESOURCES
                        PETROLEUM TECHNOLOGY
                        PETROLEUM RESOURCES
                        HYDROCARBONS
                        ENVIRONMENTAL TECHNOLOGY
                        PHYSICAL ENVIRONMENT
                        OFFSHORE INSTALLATIONS
                        OPTICAL FIBRES
                        OPTICAL DETECTION
                        METHANE
Objectives             :The aim of the project is to demonstrate by a field
trial  that  the  new  technology which has been developed within the
promoters of laboratories achieves better performance levels than the
ones  presently  attainable.  The gas detection system, composed of a
central  instrument  installed  in  a control room and a series (3 in
this  demo)  of  detection  cells  will  be  left  functioning on the
selected  platform for 1 year. This is considered essential since our
final  goal  is  the  commercial  exploitation of this technology and
possible  customers  would  consider  a field test as essential. This
project  is  crucial to convince the potential future manufacturer to
invest  in  this  young technology. The preliminary work necessary to
perform  the  installation  on  a working platform will also allow to
reach  the  goal of producing engineering documentation to be used in
the industrial scale exploitation.
General information    :The project is carried out by Tecsa in association
with VUMAN Ltd. (venture company of the Manchester University) and by
the engineering firm Snamprogetti Ltd (Basingstoke, UK). The national
Italian  oil  company  Agip  spa  is also cooperating as an associate
partner.
As  stated  in the early papers of former CEC project TH/15099/87 (by
Tecsa,  Snamprogetti  and  TNO), the current state of the art for the
automatic  gas  detection  systems  to  be used in outdoor heavy-duty
environments  is  quite poor: a statistical study on a sample of over
150  significant  leakages  in  North Sea oil and gas fields resulted
(1987) in a success rate for automatic detection of less than 3%.
Only  very  recently a few new developments have resulted in possible
commercial systems characterized by a suitable performance.
The  technology  at  the  base  of the project comes from merging the
experimental  experience  and  the specific background that Vuman and
Tecsa have as a result of former developments in this area.
The  first phase of project includes the preparation of the executive
design  of  the  prototype to be demonstrated and the planning of the
test  installation.  The  issues related to installation engineering,
compliance  with  offshore  safety  codes  etc.  are  taken  care  by
Snamprogetti  Ltd.  Phase  two is devoted to construct the instrument
(Vuman  for  the  laser,  optical  and  detection parts and Tecsa for
electronics, field cells structures and software). In phase three the
system  will  be  installed  on one Agip platform and its performance
will  be  monitored  for  one year. Phase four will be devoted to the
evaluation  of  system  performance,  to reporting and to information
dissemination activities.
RESULTS:
The  system,  installed on an offshore platform, is currently working
satisfactorily.
Start date             :1991-12-01
End date               :1994-05-31
Duration in months     :30
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :THERMIE 1
Subprogramme area      :OIL AND GAS - ENVIRONMENTAL INFLUENCE
Project reference      :OG./00119/91/IT/UK
Prime contr org        :TECSA SPA
Prime contr address    :VIA CARAVAGGI 9
Prime contr postcode   :24040
Prime contr town       :LEVATE
Prime contr region     :R3205 Bergamo
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
Contact person         :Name:         LANCIA ANTONIO
                    Tel:          +39-35-657360
                    Fax:          +39-35-656598
                  Telex:        301384
 
