<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Inspection and control of pressure vessels
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23041
Quality valid. date    :1994-09-20
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Inspection and control of pressure vessels
Subject index codes    :AER (AEROSPACE TECHNOLOGY)
                        IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)
Other indexes          :Mechanical engineering/Machinery
                        Quality control/inspection
                        Metallic structural materials
                        Control systems
                        Chemical/Petrochemical
                        Instrumentation/Measuring systems
General information    :The advantage of the regulatory hydraulic proof
test used  as  a  qualification  test  i  s  that i t verifies whether the
pressure  vessel  is  capable  of  withstanding  the  maximum service
pressure.  However  i t is costly, and still gives little information
about  the quality of the structure. In particular, i t cannot detect
the  presence of evolving defects. In certain cases there is the risk
first  of  causing  the  defects  to  evolve  without  being detected
(notably  during  a  repeat  test)  ans,  secondly,  of affecting the
vessel's performance by the moisture that remains (as a result of ice
formation  or  corrosion).  Thus  constructors  and users both need a
method  for  evaluating  the  overall  quality of the structure in a
single operation during the proof test. particulary complete safety.
The  aim of the project is to develop a real-time surveillance method
for  ensuring  the safety of proof tests and repeat tests on pressure
vessels,  using acoustic emission measurements (A.E.). This method of
surveillance  should  enable  decisions  to be taken about whether to
continue   vessel   pressurisation  by  the  real-time  and  reliable
detection and location of any evolving defect of a dangerous nature.
The  method  will  cover  the  definition of a test procedure with an
associated  computer  program  for  automatically tripping the safety
alarms.  The  procedure  will  be  developed  and valided in-situ
conditions.
Programme acronym      :CRAFT
Subprogramme area      :STRUCTURAL MATERIALS - Metals and metal matrix
                        composites;
DESIGN  OF  PRODUCTS AND PROCESSES - Design methodologies for complex
components; DESIGN OF PRODUCTS AND PROCESSES - Maintainability and 
reliability
Project reference      :CR162291/BRE21220
Prime contr org        :B.S.L. Industries
Prime contr dept       :Usine de Soissons
Prime contr address    :108 Route de Reims - BP 84
Prime contr postcode   :02203
Prime contr town       :Soissons Cedex
Prime contr region     :R2221 Aisne
Prime contr country    :FR (FRANCE)
Contact person         :Name:         GERANDAL F.
                    Tel:          +33-23732098
                    Fax:          +33-23733862
Organization           :Vidropol Lda
Country                :PT (PORTUGAL)
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
