<HEAD>
<TITLE>
System for the Control of Dangerous Goods Transport in International Alpine
Corridors
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :16973
Quality valid. date    :1994-10-20
Update date            :1995-08-12
Project acronym        :CITRA
Title                  :System for the Control of Dangerous Goods Transport
                        in International Alpine Corridors
Subject index codes    :IPS (INFORMATION PROCESSING, INFORMATION SYSTEMS)
                        TEL (TELECOMMUNICATIONS)
                        TRA (TRANSPORT)
Objectives             :First objective of the project is to investigate
the feasibility  of  an  RTI  system  to  control  Hazardous  Goods  (HG)
transport  on  motorway  alpine  corridors.  The aim is at increasing
safety  by reducing accidents and their consequences through accident
preparedness.  Any  possible  connection  with traffic management and
environmental surveillance will also be examined.
As  second  objective a pilot system for carrying out field trials on
the chosen international alpine motorway section(Munich-Kufstein-Brenner
-Verona)   will  be  designed  and  installed according to the results 
deriving from the feasibility study. Third  objective  is  the  operation
of the experimental system with appropriate  field  trials in order to get 
elements for an evaluation of the benefits obtainable with the devised 
system.
General information    :Technical Approach
The  problem  of Hazardous Goods Control (HGC) will be examined along
the following guide-lines:
(a) Legal aspects
Common definitions and rules will be found both for classification of
hazard of transported goods and for the surveillance during transport
as well. Analysis of national laws, regulations and standards will be
accomplished  with  the  aim  at achieving a common basis of rules to
which reference should be made during the project;
(b) Methodological aspects
An  appropriate  methodology  for  the  supervision and management of
hazardous goods shall be described with sufficient detail such as to
permit  the  development  of  precise planning for HG-transport (from
origin  to destination) and of an emergency strategy to be applied in
case  of  accidents  (interaction  and  cooperative  intervention  of
national rescue centres);
(c) Technical aspects
All  technical  problems  concerning  the interconnection of existing
national   control   centres   for  coordinating  the  management  of
HG-transport  shall find an appropriate solution with the design of a
higher  communication  level  based  on  STRADA  nodes interconnected
through a X.25 network.
The  particular  technology  (-ies) for HG-transport location and the
relevant  physical  layer for vehicle-roadside communication shall be
decided  after  thorough  examination  of studies, experimentation on
parallel projects and results from existing experimental systems;
The main topics of the project will cover:
Definition,   design   and   installation  of  a  X.25  communication
infrastructure  based  on STRADA nodes for the interconnection of the
national TCCs and particularly aimed at HGC information exchange;
Definition of a common set of norms and regulations to be utilised as
a  basis for specifying a common methodology of HG-Control and Rescue
Centres Alerting (RCA);
Selecting of appropriate vehicle-infrastructure communication
technology (ies); Field  trials for testing the experimental HGC-system
on the selected motorway section;Traffic and environment implication with
HG-Control.
Expected results are:
The  installation of a high level international communication network
which,  besides  its  principal  purpose of HG-Control, could also be
utilised   for  other  interworking  necessities  (traffic,  weather,
environment, road conditions etc.);
The definition of a methodology for HG-control and RCA;
Choice   and  experimentation  of  the  physical  layers  usable  for
vehicle-infrastructure communication;
Design,   engineering,   installation,  activation  and  experimental
operation  of  a system for HG-control on the Munich-Verona motor-way
section for critical evaluation purposes of the proposed system.
Key Issues
Norms and standards for HG-Transport
Methodology for HG-Control
Technique for continuous location and management of HG-transport
Strategy  for  alerting  and  coordinating the intervention of Rescue
Centres in case of accidents
Experiment of communication technology for IRTE;
Operation and critical evaluation of the experimental system realised
Expected Achievements
Creation of an evaluation model and analysis of the data to be collected;
Definition of data to be collected in the experiment;
Detailed  definition  of the modifications and the upgrading parts to
be  introduced  into  the  national  TCCs  to  achieve HG-control and
international cooperation purposes (including parallel projects);
Development  of  Hardware  and  Software  necessary  to  operate  the
polycentric  (Munich,  Innsbruck,  Trent)  architecture realizing the
pilot system;
Installation,  activation,  operation of the national HGC-Centres and
subsequent integrated operation on an international level;
Pilot system operation and collection of significant data;
Results  of  the  experimental  system  operation  and  evaluation of
benefits  obtained  by HG-Control system proposed (risk reduction and
risk consequence decrease).
Expected Impact
To be decided in detail after the field trials with pilot system. The
system could form the basis for a general procedure to be widely used
all   over   European  motorways  for  HGC  purposes  independent  on
communication  technology. Impacts on traffic management, environment
and safety as well are to be expected.
Contribution to standardization
Important  contribution  to  standards on the following topics can be
expeceted:
Norms for procedures to be applied to RTI HG-Control
Physical level for vehicle-communication infrastructure communication
TCC interworking and relevant message interchange.
Start date             :1992-01-01
End date               :1994-12-31
Duration in months     :36
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :DRIVE 2
Subprogramme area      :Freight and Fleet Management
Project reference      :V2041
Prime contr org        :ITALTEL TELESIS
Prime contr dept       :STRATEGIC MARKETING DEPT
Prime contr address    :12 PIAZZALE ZAVATTARI
