<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Operation limits of intense light source in hazardous atmospheres
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :24449
Quality valid. date    :1995-03-15
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Operation limits of intense light sources in
                        hazardous atmospheres
Subject index codes    :MEA (MEASUREMENT METHODS)
                        REF (REFERENCE MATERIALS)
                        STA (STANDARDS)
General information    :The objective of the work is to investigate the
conditions  in  which optical instruments using intense light sources
(such   as  lasers)  can  operate  safely  in  hazardous  atmospheres
(containing  vapours of combustible products or suspended combustible
particles).
The   influence   of   the   following  parameters  is  going  to  be
experimentally addressed:
- the nature of the light (coherence, intensity, wavelength, spectral
  width and modulation;
- the  characteristics  of the illuminated particles (size, chemical
  and physical nature, means of presentation to the light beam;
- the nature of the gaseous environment, with the aim of classifying
  the  optical  hazard  of  the  atmosphere  in  terms analogous to the
  electrical case, and of investigating thoroughly the minimum ignition
  energy, the auto ignition temperature and the burning velocity.
A  small  fraction  of the work is devoted to theoretical mechanistic
investigations of the initiation phase of explosions.
Status                 :The work is in progress.
Programme acronym      :BCR 4
Project reference      :MTR165
Prime contr org        :SIRA Communications Ltd
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Organization           :Centre d'Etudes et Recherche de Charbonnage de France
Country                :FR (FRANCE)
Organization           :Imperial College
Country                :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Organization           :Physikalisch-Technische Bundesanstalt
Country                :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Organization           :Sira Safety Services
Country                :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Organization           :University of Leeds
Country                :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)

            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
