<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Land Use Planning and Chemical Sites
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :31838
Quality valid. date    :1996-06-24
Update date            :1996-07-13
Project acronym        :LUPACS
Title                  :Land Use Planning and Chemical Sites
General information    :The proposal applies to workprogramme issue no. 2.2. 
1.3 Industrial safety, Risk Assessment and Management - position no. 13.  
The  land use planning process will be investigated through four case  studies  
with chemical sites, after an initial state of the art study  on land use 
planning methods, and the core of the project will be development of a 
practical methodology for land use planning where CIC's are involved.
The  development  shall  lead to a demonstration of the method LUPACS 
through  some  essential support tools and an educational program for the 
end users of such tools in regional administrations.
An  integrated  view on safety management requires that one considers both  
safety  goals and indicators, different hazards, chemical sites as well as 
transport, and both accident prevention and mitigation.
Characteristic  to  land  use  planning  is  the  inclusion  of risky 
activities  and  vulnerable  objects in a common perspective, and the 
production  of  realistic planning criteria. Most risk regulation has been  
implemented  through  isolated  decisions  treating  the siting problem  one  
case  at  a  time with only loose couplings to regional planning. 
In  LUPACS  a  methodology  will  be  developed  to help politicians, 
administrators  and  engineers  -  the  decision  makers - in a local 
community, a county or a large city to identify, evaluate and monitor effective  
land  use  planning  processes  in  relation  to CIC's and connected activities.
Along  with  current  risk  management  methods,  LUPACS will draw on modern  
Total  Quality  Management  (TQM)  techniques  and  tools and involve  
functions  for  monitoring  of the activities and the safety status.  The  
idea is to create a climate for long term decisions and continuous  improvements 
of safety with community and CIC interacting efficiently in the process.
Education  and  training  of the end users is considered an essential condition  
for successful use, educational programs will therefore be developed as a part 
of the project.
Start date             :1996-05-01
End date               :1999-04-30
Duration in months     :36
Programme acronym      :ENV 2C
Project reference      :ENV4960241
Prime contr org        :Risoe National Laboratory
Prime Organization Type:NCL Non Commercial
Prime contr dept       :Systems Analysis Department
Prime contr address    :399 Frederiksborgvej,         PO Box 49
Prime contr postcode   :4000
Prime contr town       :Roskilde  Country    :DK (DENMARK)
Contact person         :Name:         GROENBERG, Carsten d.
       Tel:          +45-46775134,   Fax:          +45-46757101
          Contact name           :PAPAZOGLOU, Ioannis a.
           Department             :Institute of Nuclear Technology -  Radiation Protection
           Organization           :National Centre for Scientific Research   'Demokritos'
           Organization type      :NCL Non Commercial
           Address                :Aghia Paraskevi,    PO Box 60228
           City                   :Athens ,   Postcode    :15310  Country    :GR (GREECE)
