<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Inherently safer approaches to the design of chemical process plant
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :27088
Quality valid. date    :1995-07-25
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Inherently safer approaches to the design of
                        chemical process plant
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)
General information    :The concept of inherently safer chemical process
plant  has  been  around  for many years. It encompasses the ideas of
intensification,  substitution, attenuation and simplification. These
ideas  focus  on hazard elimination and prevention and offer benefits
in  terms of better operability and reduced lifetime costs as well as
enhanced   safety   and   environmental  performance.  In  short,  an
inherently  safer  approach  may  offer  a more effective, robust and
efficient   means   to   achieve   tolerable  levels  of  safety  and
environmental  performance  in today's business environment. However,
industry  on  the  whole  has  been reluctant to take up the ideas of
inherent  safety.  This  appears  to  be  due to a lack of awareness,
conservatism  in design and costing approaches and a lack of accepted
methods or tools to tackle inherent safety in plant design.
This  proposal  aims  to  address  these  aspects  by developing with
industry  the  tools and information that can persuade and facilitate
the integration of inherently safer approaches into plant design. The
project aims to achieve this by:
- reviewing the current state of design approaches
-  developing  the  means  to  address inherently safer issues in the
   design process
-  demonstrating  the  effectiveness of these means and the resulting
   benefits  in terms of safety, costs and operability by carrying out a
   series     of    trials    in    industry    on    actual    projects
-  producing  a series of reports and a symposium/workshop to pass on
   the  lessons  from  the  project  and  give  industry  the  tools and
   information it needs to start to adopt inherently safer approaches to
   design.   The   proposed   project   team   consists  of  3  research
   organisations  working  in  the  field  of inherent safety, safety in
   design  and hazard analysis methods and 4 industrial organizations in
   the   field   of   process  safety,  chemistry  route  and  synthesis
   development  and  plant  design and engineering - giving a balance of
   theoretical and practical skills and experience.
Start date             :1994-08-01
End date               :1997-01-31
Duration in months     :30
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0416
Prime contr org        :United Kingdom Atomic Energy Authority
Prime contr address    :154 B Harwell
Prime contr postcode   :OX11 0RA
Prime contr town       :Didcot
Prime contr region     :R7523 Oxfordshire
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Contact person         :Name:         MANSFIELD, DAVID
Contact name           :JONES, J.DAVID
Organization           :Inburex GmbH Consultinggesellschaft fuer
Explosionsschutz und Anlagensicherheit
Organization type      :IND Industry
Address                :5 Muensterstrasse
City                   :Hamm
Postcode               :59065
Region                 :R1554 Hamm, krfr.St.
Country                :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Contact name           :TURNEY, ROBIN
Organization           :Eutech Engineering Solutions Ltd.
Organization type      :IND Industry
Address                :Brunner House
City                   :Northwich
