<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ARGE SCALE CATASTROPHIC RELEASE OF FLAMMABLE LIQUIDS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :11997
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-23
Key words              :Two-phase release, jet fire
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :LARGE SCALE CATASTROPHIC RELEASE OF FLAMMABLE
                        LIQUIDS
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Other indexes          :EFFECTS OF TECHNOLOGY
                        RISK EVALUATION
                        FLAMMABLE GASES
                        SIMULATION TECHNIQUES
                        CIRCULATION OF POLLUTANTS
                        EXPLOSIONS

Objectives             :THE WORK WILL PROVIDE DATA AT A REALISTIC PRACTICAL
SCALE,  THAT  CAN  BE  USED  FOR  THE VALIDATION AND OR IMPROVMENT OF
EXISTING MODELS OF GAS DISPERSION, COMBUSTION AND RADIATION.

General information    :COMPREHENSIVE DATA WILL BE COLLECTED DURING
EXPERIMENTS  USING  INSTRUMENTATION WHICH IS ALREADY AVAILABLE AT THE
MIDLANDS RESEARCH STATION.
I) THE TEST VESSEL WILL BE INSTRUMENTED WITH PRESSURE AND TEMPERATURE
   SENSORS SO THAT THE CONDITIONS AT THE TIME OF RELEASE ARE KNOW.
II)SAMPLES  OF  THE  FUAL  CONTAINED WITHIN THE TEST VESSEL WILL BE
   ANALYSED SO THAT ITS COMPOSITION IS KNOWN.
III) DURING   EXPERIMENTS   MEASUREMENTS   WILL   BE  MADE  OF  THE
   METEOROLOGICAL  CONDITIONS.  THESE  WILL  CONSIST  OF  WIND SPEED AND
   DIRECTION,   AMBIENT  AIR  TEMPERATURE  AND  PRESSURE,  AND  RELATIVE
   HUMIDITY.
IV)OVERPRESSURES  GENERATED  BY  THE  VAPORISATION  OF THE RELEASED
   LIQUID  AND,  IN  IGNITED EXPERIMENTS, SUBSEQUENT COMBUSTION, WILL BE
   MEASURED BY AN ARRAY OF UP TO 10 PIEZO-ELECTRIC PRESSURE TRANSDUCERS.
   SIGNALS  WILL  BE RECORDED ON A MULTICHANNEL TRANSIENT RECORDER UNDER
   COMPUTER CONTROL, AND AS BACK-UP, ALSO ON  A  MULTI-TRACK INSTRUMEN-
   TATION TAPE RECORDER.
V) ARRAYS  OF  THERMOCOUPLES  WILL  BE SET OUT BOTH HORIZONTALLY AND
   VERTICALLY  TO  MEASURE  THE  GRAVITY SLUMPING OF THE (COLD) MATERIAL
   IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING THE RELEASE AND SUBSEQUENT COMBUSTION.
VI)DURING  IGNITED EXPERIMENTS, WIDE ANGLE RADIOMETERS WILL BE USED
   IN  CONJUNCTION  WITH  BOLEX 16MM CINE CAMERAS TO MEASURE THE OVERALL
   AVERAGE  SURFACE  EMISSIVE POWER OF THE FLAME AND TO DIRECTLY MEASURE
   INCIDENT  THERMAL  RADIATION. UP TO ABOUT 10 INSTRUMENTS WILL BE USED
   PER  TEST.  DATA  FROM THE INSTRUMENTS WILL BE RECORDED ON A COMPUTER
   CONTROLLED DATA LOGGER.
VII)IN  ADDITION TO THE 16MM CINE FILM RECORDS TAKEN IN CONJONCTION
    WITH  RADIATION  MEASUREMENTS,  AT  LEAST TWO LOCAM 16MM CINE CAMERAS
    WILL  RECORD  THE  EXPERIMENT  AT  FRAMING RATES UP TO 500 FRAMES PER
    SECOND.
VIII)FINALLY,IN THE UNIGNITED EXPERIMENT, AN ARRAY OF UP TO FORTY
    GAS  DETECTORS WILL BE DEPLOYED IN ORDER TO MEASURE THE DISPERSION OF
    THE  RELEASED  TWO PHASE MIXTURE.THE  RESEARCH  ON  LARGE  SCALE
	CATASTROPHIC  RELEASES  OF FLAMMABLE LIQUIDS  WHICH  IS  SET  OUT
	IN THIS PROPOSAL, IS ONE OF 12 SEPARATE PROPOSALS  FROM  VARIOUS
	EUROPEAN  ORGANISATIONS,  WHICH  ARE  BEING SUBMITTED  AS PART OF A
	JOINT PROJECT ENTITLED "TWO PHASE RELEASES OF TOXIC  AND  FLAMMABLE
	SUBSTANCES - SOURCE TERM AND FIRE EFFECTS", AS EXPLAINED IN THE ATTACHED
	ANNEX TO THIS PROPOSAL.

Start date             :1987-11-01
End date               :1989-12-31
Duration in months     :26
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :TECHHAZ C
Subprogramme area      :SOURCE TERM (86-90)
Project reference      :EV4T0014
Prime contr org        :British Gas PLC
Prime Organization Type:IND Industry
Prime contr dept       :Midlands Research Station
Prime contr address    :Wharf Lane
Prime contr postcode   :B91 2JW
Prime contr town       :Solihull - West Midlands
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Contact person         :Name:         HARRIS R.J.
       Tel:          +44-21-7057581
       Telex:        339128 MRSSOL G
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
