<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
TORCH FIRE IMPINGMENT RADIATIVE AND CONVECTIVE HEAT
TRANSFER TO ENGULFED OBJECTS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :11994
Quality valid. date    :1994-01-23
Key words              :Jet fire, LPG, two-phase release
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :TORCH FIRE IMPINGMENT RADIATIVE AND CONVECTIVE HEAT
                        TRANSFER TO ENGULFED OBJECTS
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Other indexes          :EFFECTS OF TECHNOLOGY
                        RISK EVALUATION
                        FIRES
                        HEAT TRANSFER
                        FLUID FLOW

Objectives             :TO OBTAIN DIRECT EXPERIMENTAL INFORMATION ON THE
INTERACTION  BETWEEN  LARGE JET FLAMES AND INDUSTRIAL STRUCTURES SUCH
AS LPG TANKS AND PIPEWORK.

General information    :AMONGST THE DETAILED AIMS OF THIS PROJECT ARE :
(1) TO ESTABLISH A FLEXIBLE ECONOMICAL FACILITY FOR STUDYING MOMEMTUM
DOMINATED  LARGE  JETS  OF  LPG AND NATURAL GAS AND THE CAPABILITY OF
EXTENSION TO OTHER FLAMMABLE SUBSTANCES.
(2)  TO CHARACTERISE THE DIMENSIONS AND RADIATION FIELD OF JET FLAMES
AND  THEIR  RELATION  TO FLOW RATE, APERTURE CONDITIONS, PHASE RATIO,
WIND, SOURCE ORIENTATION.
(3)  TO  DETERMINE  THE EXTENT TO WHICH FLAMES ENGULF REALISTIC SIZED
OBJECTS, E G  TANKS, PIPEWORK AND STRUCTURES.
(4)  TO  CHARACTERISE  HEAT  TRANSFER  DISTRIBUTION  TO  ENGULFED  OR
PARTIALLY  ENGULFED FULL  SIZE  STRUCTURES.  BENEFITS  AND INNOVATIVE
FEATURES OF THE PROJECT WILL INCLUDE :
(1)  IMMEDIATE  IMPROVEMENTS IN QUANTITATIVE ESTIMATION OF HAZARDS TO
VESSELS AND OTHER PLANT STRUCTURES FROM JET FIRES.
(2)  A  SOUND  AND  COMPREHENSIVE  BODY OF INFORMATION ON THE THERMAL
ENVIRONMENT NEAR OR WITHIN LARGE ENGULFING TORCH FIRES.
(3) FUNDAMENTAL AND ENGINEERING DATA FOR FIRE CONSEQUENCE MODELLING.
(4) SIGNIFICANT ADDITIONS TO THE SCIENCE OF HEAT TRANSFER.
(5) IMPROVEMENTS IN HAZARD ASSESSMENT PROCEDURES AND THE AMELIORATION
OF JET FIRE IMPACT.

Start date             :1987-11-01
End date               :1990-09-30
Duration in months     :35
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :TECHHAZ C
Subprogramme area      :SOURCE TERM (86-90)
Project reference      :EV4T0016
Prime contr org        :Shell Research Ltd
Prime Organization Type:IND Industry
Prime contr address    :3 Savoy Place
Prime contr postcode   :WC2R ODX
Prime contr town       :London
Prime contr region     :R755 GREATER LONDON
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Contact person         :Name:         STRACHAN D.C.
                    Tel:          +44-51-3735737
 
            --------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
