<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Accident prevention of metalorganic precursors
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :27086
Quality valid. date    :1995-06-14
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Accident prevention of metalorganic precursors
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)
General information    :The use of metalorganic vapour phase epitaxy 
(MOVPE)for  the  preparation of complex compound semiconductor materials 
for semiconductor and optoelectronic applications has expanded
considerably in recent years and has tremendous opportunities for the
future.  This  has  led to the widespread use of a range of specialty
metalorganic chemicals which are essential for MOVPE processing. They
are  supplied to approximately 250 research and production facilities
through  Europe,  the U.S.A. and Japan. Europe is at the forefront of
this   technology  and  the  leading  world-wide  supplier  of  these
chemicals  is Epichem, the coordinator of this proposal. A difficulty
has  arisen  which  may  delay  the  uptake  of  the  technology; the
properties  of  many  of  these  metalorganic chemicals have not been
fully investigated. This has led to a number of significant incidents
where   explosions   have  taken  place  during  the  manufacture  of
precursors, due to the poor definition of their properties.
The  objective  of  the  current  proposal  is  to completely prevent
accidents  during  production,  storage, handling and shipping of the
hazardous  chemicals. The project brings together the expertise of an
SME  covering  the production and handling of these chemicals (all of
which   are   pyrophoric   and   often   toxic)   with   those  of  a
distinguished research institute with the expertise and facilities to
fully  investigate  the thermal and thermodynamic properties of these
chemicals and all of the processes used to manufacture them.
The  expected  benefits  from  the European collaboration will be the
establishment  of a rigorous scientific understanding of the physical
and  chemical  properties  which  will  ensure  that  numerous  MOVPE
precursors  may  be  manufactured, transported and used in a safe and
environmentally  acceptable  manner, thus achieving complete accident
prevention.  Additional  benefits  will arise from the development of
handling  and  sampling  techniques  to  enable  other  air sensitive
materials to be easily tested in the future.
Start date             :1994-06-01
End date               :1996-05-31
Duration in months     :24
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0414
Prime contr org        :Epichem Ltd
Prime contr address    :Power Road
Prime contr postcode   :L62 3QF
Prime contr town       :Wirral
Prime contr region     :R784 MERSEYSIDE
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
