<TITLE>
The feasibility of using aerodynamic models
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Key words              :Explosion, methane, mining, modelling
Record cntrl number    :21734
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :The feasibility of using aerodynamic models to 
                        study the local build-up of methane gas and risk of 
                        frictional ignition in coal mines
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

The aim of the project was to examine the feasibility of using small-scale 
aerodynamic models to investigate the potential accumulation of methane in 
cavities where it might lead to frictional ignitions and relate the 
findings to actual underground situations.

