<TITLE>
Centralised monitoring applied to hazard control in a mine
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :21755
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Key words              :Mining, fire, fire hazard
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Centralised monitoring applied to hazard control in
                        a mine
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Objectives             :There were three objectives:
1) the  monitoring  of  high  voltage  (HV)  electrical  networks; a
   condition  of the project was that the data transmission should be by
   means  of  the  HV  cable  itself  and  that it should be possible to
   transmit data from parts of the system which had been switched off;
2) the  monitoring  of  the  ventilation  by the use of an increased
   capacity CGA system;
3) the checking of the location of personnel underground in order to
   know where they are and whether, in case of fire, they have assembled
   at muster stations.

