<TITLE>
Duration of rescue service operations in hot and humid underground workings
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :21747
Quality valid. date    :1994-05-08
Key words              :Mining, fire, rescue operation
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Duration of rescue service operations in hot and
                        humid underground workings
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)

Objectives             :There are different rules in the countries of the
EC regarding  working  times  for  mine  rescue  teams  in hot and humid
atmospheres. The aim of this  project  was to establish the climatic limits
for rescue  workers when  wearing  fire-retardant  garments  by means of
exercises  carried out in the Essen and Hasselt central rescue stations. 
The results will be presented in the form of tables showing the  permissible 
duration of deployment as a function of the climatic factors.

General information    :This is a Belgian/German joint project. The Belgian
                        contract number is 7258-04/117/02.

Programme acronym      :MINSAFECS 2C
Subprogramme area      :RESCUE; Working time in hot atmospheres
Project reference      :7258-04/116/01
Prime contr org        :Bergbau-Forschung
Prime contr country    :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Contact person         :Name:         FUNKEMEYER M.
 
