<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Chemical Waste, 1988-1991
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19341
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-21
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Chemical Waste, 1988-1991
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MEA (MEASUREMENT METHODS)
                        WAS (WASTE MANAGEMENT)
Objectives             :- Impact of hazardous wastes on environment: 
studies of migration, retention and  transformation of pollutants.
- Development of toxic waste management support decision systems (OPM and 
EM).
General information    :Progress to end 1990
The  possible migration of polychlorinated biphenyls (PCBs) congeners
to  ground  water  has  been  evaluated.   A preliminary quantitative
structure-activity  relationship  (QSAR)  has  been  derived  and the
soil-water PCB partition studied. One article is in print in the J.
Environ.  Toxicol.  Safety  and  two  others  have  been submitted to
Toxicol. Environ. Chem. and Chemosphere.
The  analysis  of PCB congeners in various environmental matrices has
been   developed   and   validated  through  several  interlaboratory
comparisons leading to one article in the Int. J. Environ. Anal.Chem.
and two others submitted to Sci.Tot. Envir. and to Int. J. Environ.
Anal. Chem.
The  Oil  PCB Manager system (OPM) has been developed in two versions
(DOS and MacOS).  The available versions include the basic module;
the  achieved  functionality  is  sufficient for experimentation with
industrial and public users.
The  development  of the stochastic finite element model (FENSUN) for
application  to  the diffusion of inorganic pollutants in soil porous
media and in water has been completed.
The  fate  of  coal  fly  ash  constituents  in sandy soils and their
effects on physical  and  agronomic  soil  properties  have  been
investigated  and the trace metal specification in soil and sediments
studied in the frame of a laboratory intercomparison exercise.
The  influence  of  the  physical  properties  of  a retention matrix
ordinary  Portland  cement)  like  porosity, density and compressive
strength  of  cylindrical  specimens  has  been  evaluated by dynamic
leaching   procedures   at  various  temperatures  and  at  different
preparative conditions on immobilized wastes.
An  international agreement for the proposal as an EUREKA project for
the  construction  of  an analytical mobile unit has been reached and
the technical project nearly completed.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1991 (expected results)
- Field lysimeter experiments to study migration of selected pollutants.
- Application of soil diffusion models to anthropogenic toxic organic
  compounds.
- Use   of   model   colloids   to   investigate   mechanical   and
  physico-chemical filtration processes.
- Completion and calibration of a gamma-ray attenuation device;
  development  of  analytical  techniques  based on supercritical fluid
  extraction and new hyphenate techniques.
- Evaluation  of  the effects of waste incineration temperatures and
  procedures  onthe  retainment of toxic inorganic elements by selected
  sorbing matrices.
- Experimentation  of  OPM  with  AEM  Turin  and  Lombardy  Region
  Authorities. Design and implementation of Risk Priority and Container
  Diagnosis modules.
- Construction of an analytical mobile unit.
  Short description of evolution of work in 1992
- Quantification of the geochemical barrier towards the transport of
  colloidal and complex species.
- Field  validation  of laboratory experiments and their application
  for prevision al purposes.
- Studies on the leaching properties of matrices containing real
   wastes.
- Local Emergencies Management Module for expert systems.
- Tests on the mobile analytical unit.
Start date             :1988-01-01
End date               :1992-01-01
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :ENVPROTJ 5C
Project reference      :0007
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute of the Environment
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
Prime contr town       :ISPRA
Prime contr region     :R3201 Varese
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
Contact person         :Name:         FACCHETTI, SERGIO
                    Tel:          +39-332-89119969
                    Fax:          +39-332-789001
                  Telex:        380042
 
