<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Uncontrolled Reactions : MPMC, 1988-1991
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19335
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-21
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Uncontrolled Reactions : MPMC, 1988-1991
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
To  study,  both  experimentally  and  analytically, the discharge of
flashing fluids from a pressure vessel to a catch tank; to assess the
implications  of  these results for the improved design of industrial
relief systems; to transfer these findings to industry.
General information    :Progress to end 1990
1. The MPMC test facility has been constructed, commissioned and over
250  experiments  successfully  completed  with water, high viscosity
fluids and foamy fluids.
2. In  addition,  a  test  series has been performed with venting of
H202  (hydrogen  peroxide)  during  decomposition (a "gassy" chemical
reaction).  These test data are currently being analysed.
3.  Two  additional  test  facilities  have been constructed for flow
visualisation  studies  of  bubble  size, motion and coalescence when
rising  in  high  viscosity  liquids.   This  test  work has now been
completed   and   the  observations  offer  insight  into  the  fluid
mechanisms occurring in the (larger) MPMC facility.
4.Currently,  the MPMC facility is being modified for a test series
involving the discharge of fluids containing small solid particles.
It is planned to complete these tests by the end of 1990.
5. A further analytical activity has commenced in the last quarter of
1990  concerned with improving the sizing criteria for catch tanks to
contain  discharged  material  from  chemical reactors as a result of
runaway reactions.
Publications:
Oster,  R.,  Bell, K. and Kottowski, H.M. Hydrodynamic considerations
of venting with high-viscosity non-reacting fluids. J. Loss Prev.
Process Ind., 1990, vol. 3 (January), pp 50-52.
Skouloudis,  A.N.,  Bell,  K.  and Kottowski, H.M. Venting of vessels
containing  reacting  fluids  :  a  parameteric study with SAFIRE and
DEERS. J.Loss Prev. Process Ind., 1990, vol. 3 (January), pp.13-16.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1991 (expected results)
1.  A further test series with H202 decomposition but now with higher
concentration of H202.
2.  Modification  of  the  MPMC  facility  in preparation for the new
programme  of  work  on  safety  device and catch tank performance to
begin in Summer 1991.
3. Theoretical analyses and development of simple models for vent and
catch tank sizing under runaway reaction conditions.
Short description of evolution of work in 1992
Continuation  of  planned  work  programme  on  discharge  tests with
rupture  discs,  pressure  relief  valves  and  combinations of these
safety  devices.   Monitoring of catch tank conditions.  Both top and
bottom venting will be studied with a range of different fluids.
Further  analytical  work  to model experimental observations with an
emphasis on containment (catch tank conditions).
Start date             :1988-01-01
End date               :1992-01-01
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :INDHAZ 2C
Project reference      :0010
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute for Safety Technology
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
Prime contr town       :ISPRA
Prime contr region     :R3201 Varese
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
Contact person         :Name:         MORRIS, STANLEY
                    Tel:          +39-332-89119754
                    Fax:          +39-332-789001
