<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Towards a better design of pressure relief systems in chemical and
petroleum industries
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :17634
Quality valid. date    :1995-03-06
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Towards a better design of pressure relief systems
                        in chemical and petroleum industries
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)
General information    :The basic two coupled elements of a multiple
reactor relief  system  design after the postulation of a worst credible
case scenario,  e.g. a thermal runaway reaction, are (1) the prediction of
the characteristics   of   the   transient   mass   flux   (single
phase/multiphase  flow) to be discharged from the reactor and (2) the
provision  of  a  discharge piping system capable of transporting off
this mass flux at any time during relief.
In the  proposed  project,  the  first  part will be dealt with by the
Technische  Universitaet Hamburg-Harburg (prof. L. Friedel). By using
the predictions of a physically more consistent code to be developed,
more realistic input data will be provided for an extended version of
the  FLIERS  code,  This  extended  version  will  be proposed by the
Universite  Catholique  de  Louvain  (prof.  L.  Bolle)  following an
experimental  campaign  in  the  same  university. In addition to the
implementation   of   special   items  into  FLIERS  such  as  sudden
enlargements,  orifices,  tees,  etc.  there is a strong necessity to
investigate the flow mechanisms encountered in safety relief valves.
This will   be   done   experimentally  and  theoretically  in  the
commissariat  a  l'Energie  Atomique,  Centre  d'Etudes Nucleaires de
Grenoble  (Dr H.Lemonnier) Moreover, particular but important effects
such  as  nonequilibrium  and  shock  waves  will be addressed at the
Institute for Fluid Flow Machinery in Gdansk (prof. Z. Bilicki).
Finally  A.S.  Veritas  Research in Hoevik (Dr. S. Selmer-Olsen) will
perform  venting  experiments  in a simplified multiple vessel relief
system  and  the  results  will be compared to the predictions of the
coupled vessel/relief line design code.
This  three-year  project  will focus on the following objectives and
achievements :
1.  improvement  of  the  accuracy  and  reliability  of  the  design
procedures for relief systems composed of multiple storage or reactor
vessels  connected  to  a downstream process unit through collectors,
safety   valves,   ventinlines   and   other   components  (orifices,
T-junctions,  silencers,  etc.)  
2. determination of the range of applicability and tentative recommendations
on the degree of extrapolation of existing design methods outside of their
assessed validity
3. development of user-friendly tools for engineering calculations
Start date             :1994-01-01
End date               :1995-12-31
Duration in months     :24
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0289
Prime contr org        :Commissariat a l'Energie Atomique
Prime contr dept       :Direction des Reacteurs Nucleaires - Departement de
                        Thermohydraulique et dePhysique
Service de Thermohydraulique pour lesApplications Industrielles - GRETh
Prime contr address    :Ctr Etudes de Grenoble - CE-G
Prime contr postcode   :38041
Prime contr town       :Grenoble
Prime contr region     :R2714 Isere
Prime contr country    :FR (FRANCE)
Contact person         :Name:         DELHAYE, Jean-Marc
Contact name           :SELMER-OLSEN, STAALE
Organization           :Det Norske Veritas Research A/S
Organization type      :IND Industry
Address                :1 Veritasveien
PO Box 300
City                   :Hoevik
Postcode               :1322
Region                 :NO03 Oslo
Country                :NO (NORWAY)
Contact name           :FRIEDEL, LUTZ
Department             :Arbeitsbereich Stroemungsmechanik
Organization           :Technische Universitaet Hamburg-Harburg
Organization type      :EDU Education
Address                :38 Eissendorfer Strasse
City                   :Hamburg
Postcode               :21073
Region                 :R12 HAMBURG
Country                :DE (GERMANY FEDERAL REP.)
Contact name           :BOLLE, LEON
