<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Risk Management, 1988-1991
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19328
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-13
Update date            :1995-08-12
Title                  :Risk Management, 1988-1991
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Studies   on  decision  processes  and  communication  pertaining  to
industrial  and environmental risk management; development of related
decision  support  system This activity is relevant for any community
directive  implementing  an  interface  between  social  systems  and
technological systems.
General information    :Progress to end 1990
New  kinds of relevant mathematical models of decision processes were
investigated  :  These  models  are related to preference elicitation
including both interactive methods (which require a close cooperation
between  the  user  and  the  system)  and  outranking methods (which
include other available informations to enhanced dominance relation).
The  existence  of a mathematical analogy between the problem of the
aggregation   of   quality   parameters   and   the   application  of
multicriteria decision analysis was investigat, indicating that a new
formal  approach  could  be  usefull  to expert in the relevant field
("Assessment  of the aggregation of environmental parameters by means
of  multicriteria  methods"  Proceedings  to  the  2nd  International
Conference on Statistical Methods for the Environmental Sciences).
Studies on territorial risk management dealing with industrial impact
were  initiated.  The aim is to compare heterogeneous effects such as
major  hazards, pollution of air, water and soil, negative effects on
the  landscape,  public opposition, etc.("A modelling approach to the
urban   waste   disposal  system"  European  Journal  of  Operational
Research).    In  the  framework  of  the  decision  support  systems
development  of  the  activity  on a stereo reconstruction system for
industrial  site  models  has  continued.  The orinal system has been
enhanced  to improve accurracy and to include color attributes and is
now  giving  good  results on laboratory images.  Regarding wireframe
completion,  a  preliminary  study  has  been  done,  and  a  set  of
experiments  on  domain  independent  and  knowledge  based  (frames)
representation and completion has been started.
Methodological  work  has started for the improvement of sociological
studies  in  the area of risk management. Protocols will be developed
and empirically tested cross-culturally in order to provide effective
research  tools.  These  will enable the availability of reliable and
comparable  sociological  data  from  different countries and various
socio-cultural  settings.  The  results  of this work are a necessary
step to enhance effective risk management.
The  collaboration  contract  with  the  Dutch  Ministry for Housing,
Physical Planning and the Environment, which aimed at customising the
Ispra Risk  Management  Support  System  was  terminated,  and  the
developed software is now available at the JRC.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1991 (expected results)
Multiusers  decisions  processes will be explored and modelled mainly
in  relation  to the design of DSS relevant for water bodies recovery
and industrial hazardous waste disposal.
New algorithms for the aggregation of risk parameters on the bases of
multicriteria  decision  analysis  will be implemented in relation to
territorial planning case studies.
Risk  communication studies will be focused on fundamental aspects of
problems.  They  will  continue, and expand to include the subject of
conflict resolution (or management) related to risk debate and safety
issues. The work on wireframe completion of industrial sites will be
continued.
Short description of evolution of work in 1992
Start date             :1988-01-01
End date               :1992-01-01
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :INDHAZ 2C
Project reference      :0003
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute for Systems Engineering
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
Prime contr town       :ISPRA
Prime contr region     :R3201 Varese
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
Contact person         :Name:         PARUCCINI, MASSIMO
                    Tel:          +39-332-89119302
                    Fax:          +39-332-789001
