<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
ADVANCED RISK MANAGEMENT SYSTEM
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :15979
Quality valid. date    :1992-12-31
Update date            :1995-08-12
Project acronym        :ARMS
Title                  :ADVANCED RISK MANAGEMENT SYSTEM
Subject index codes    :FFU (FOSSIL FUELS)
Other indexes          :ENERGY (PHYSICS)
                        ENERGY RESOURCES
                        HYDROCARBONS
                        MAINTENANCE
                        MANAGEMENT METHODS
                        MATHEMATICAL MODELS
                        OFFSHORE INSTALLATIONS
                        PETROLEUM RESOURCES
                        PETROLEUM TECHNOLOGY
                        PROBABILITY THEORY
                        CONNECTION
                        RISK
                        RISK EVALUATION
                        RISK LEVEL
Objectives             :The purpose of this project is to ASSIST the
Operator  of  an  in-service  offshore platform to keep an acceptable
level  of  SAFETY  thanks  to  an  on-line  RISK  ASSESSMENT  and the
MANAGEMENT of abnormal situations and unplanned modifications.
This  project  will  take  benefit  of transfer of techniques used in
nuclear  industry.  An  expert system approach will allow to consider
the  human factor as part of the risk assessment, risk management and
decision process.
General information    :ARMS is an Advanced Risk Management System, the
mission  of  which  is  to  give information on risk level and causes
analysis.
ARMS will fulfill two main functions:
- on-line assessment of the installation
- management of abnormal situations and unplanned modifications.
With  this  aim  in  view,  the  System  is  connected on-line to the
existing  safety  and  control  systems  of the platform and possible
additional instrumentation.
Risk assessment and management is based on an integrated modelization of:
- P & ID's - Safety Systems
- Risk analyses Studies
- Regulations
- Expertise
- Maintenance procedures
- Etc...
In  case of planned event within the modelization, ARMS will react by
running an algorithmic risk assessment software.
In  case  of  situations unplanned within the modelization, ARMS will
activate  a risk management expert system module. Operators will have
the  possibility to run simulations off-line of incident, maintenance
and modification scenario.
Results  of  above  analyses  are  displayed  to  the  operator using
synthetic  views  designed  for  decisional  purpose.  Logging of all
detected anomalies, assessment and actions will be possible through a
black box.
ARMS   will  allow  and  centralize  the  management  of  maintenance
operations from the safety point of view.
Following features of ARMS will be focused on:
- Updating : ARMS will have capacity to be quickly updated in case of
approved modifications of the installation.
- Transportability : ARMS will adapt to different platform
configurations.
- RAMS : 
Reliability
Availability
Maintenability
Security.

RESULTS:
We  elaborated  the specification of experimental system. We took two
examples : the Fire Safety System Integrity and the structural repair
after  storm-induced damage. The techniques used are a combination of
probabilistic  belief  networks,  expert system and decision analysis
technologies.
Start date             :1990-01-01
End date               :1992-06-30
Duration in months     :30
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :HYDROCARB 2C
Subprogramme area      :HYDROCARBONS - MISCELLANEOUS
Project reference      :TH./15127/89/FR/..
Prime contr org        :BUREAU VERITAS
Prime contr address    :PLACE DES REFLETS 17BIS,
Prime contr postcode   :92077
Prime contr town       :PARIS LA DEFENSE CEDEX 44
Prime contr region     :R2105 Hauts-de-Seine
Prime contr country    :FR (FRANCE)
Contact person         :Name:         BESSE PIERRE
                    Tel:          +33-1-42915291
                    Fax:          +33-1-42915345
Organization           :TNO
 
