<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Local Area Emergency Support System
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :4969
Quality valid. date    :1995-03-06
Update date            :1995-08-11
Project acronym        :LAESS
Title                  :Local Area Emergency Support System
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)
                        information system, warning system
General information    :The main objective of this research proposal is to
research the feasibility of developing a comprehensive support system
to  aid  the  management  of  emergency situations, in particular the
management  of  off-site  emergency  evacuation.  The  support system
envisaged  would  be  used  primarily  by the operators of a chemical
facility and by emergency services personnel.
In  the  first instance the support system would need to be used in a
"planning  mode"  so  that those devising evacuation strategies could
test  a  number  of  options  by  varying parameters such as weather,
population  densities,  response  times etc. The knowledge from these
trial  examinations  could  possibly be stored in a knowledge base so
that  some  primary conditions related to evacuation could be readily
available.
To be of maximum benefit the system must be able to predict the areas
around the facility which will be subjected to greatest threat at the
time  of  the incident and to advise emergency personnel of groups of
persons most at risk. Such a ''real time/predictive advisory system''
would  need to incorporate models relevant to people movement, chains
of   communications  dispersion  of  hazard,  knowledge  of  released
substance chemical characteristics etc.
The goal of the study would be the production of a prototype software
system  that  would  evaluate  the  spread  and  extent  of hazardous
phenomena  generated  by  possible accidents and map these parameters
onto  the  surrounding  geographical  and social features. The system
would  then  evaluate numbers of persons at risk and the demands what
would be placed on the risk aversion measures that are available such
as  evacuation  facilities.  Finally  the  system  would evaluate the
effectiveness  of  the  risk  aversion  facilities  and  policies  in
minimising harm to persons.
Start date             :1992-11-15
End date               :1994-09-14
Duration in months     :22
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0111
Prime contr org        :Electrowatt Engineering Services Ltd
Prime contr postcode   :BD1
Prime contr town       :Bradford
Prime contr region     :R724 WEST YORKSHIRE
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Contact person         :Name:         DUMOLO, RICHARD
Contact name           :GATTI, STEFANO
Organization           :Applied Information Technologies
Organization type      :IND Industry
Address                :26 Via Taramelli
