<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Uncotrolled Reactions : FIRES Project, 1988-1991
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :19331
Quality valid. date    :1992-04-13
Update date            :1995-08-12
Project acronym        :FIRES
Title                  :Uncotrolled Reactions : FIRES Project, 1988-1991
Subject index codes    :SAF (SAFETY)
Study  of  abnormal  behaviour of chemical reactors (numerical models
for   simulation,   experimental   modelling,   techniques  for  safe
operation).
General information    :Progress to end 1990
Assembly  and characterisation of key elements of the FIRES (Facility
for   Investigating   Runaway   Events  Safely)  facility,  including
commissioning  of  control  and data acquisition systems; preliminary
experiments to calculate heat capacities, heat transfer coefficients,
heat losses, and stirring effects in the reactor vessel.
Neutralisation  experiments  between  hydrogen  chloride  and  sodium
hydroxide  to  study the dynamic behaviour of FIRES and adjustment of
FISIM (FIres SIMulator) for FIRES reactor have been carried out.
Esterification  reaction  experiments between 2-butanol and propionic
anhydride  started  at the end of February 1990 in collaboration with
the   UK   Health  and  Safety  Executive,  Buxton  Laboratory.   The
experiments  carried  out in the small scale reactor aimed at testing
different  early  warning  detection techniques in runaway conditions
and  at  obtaining kinetic data.  These experiments have been pursued
in  the  FIRES  reactor  for  validation of scaling criteria for heat
transfer  and  runaway  reaction  prediction,  fornvestigation on the
reliability  of  data  obtained  from  different  sources : DSC, ARC,
PHITEC,  RC1  and  FIRES,  for  validation  of  kinetic  schemes from
small-scale experiments, and for adjustment of FISIM.
The  experiments on toluene nitration in the small scale reactor were
pursued to prepare those in the FIRES reactor.
Equilibrium   reactions   were   introduced  in  FISIM.  Model  based
applications  for  the  on-line  estimation  of  the  state variables
(temperature,  pressure,  and  concentration), the early detection of
runaway  initiation,  and  the  adaptive  control of the reactor were
started.
Detailed description of work foreseen in 1991 (expected results)
Toluene   nitration   experiments   in  FIRES  facility  with  normal
industrial  conditions to characterize the influence of the operating
conditions  (concentrations,  stirrer  speed,  starting  temperature,
stream  feed,  etc.),  and to optimize it from performance and safety
point  of  view.  Study  of  methods  of  early  detection of runaway
initiation.
Experimental simulation of failures : influence of the cooling system
failure,  of  the  stirrer  stopping, of the speed of stream feed, of
incorrect initial concentrations, of incorrect starting temperature.
Study  of  different  methods  to  stop  the runaway : fast injection
system experiments and emergency emptying system experiments.
Adjustment  of  the  heterogenous  two  liquid  phases  kinetic model
developed in FISIM by experimental results.  Conversion of FISIM in a
general  simulation  code  to  deal  with  any  type of batch reactor
installation.
Short description of evolution of work in 1992
Methyl-methacrylate  polymerization  reaction  studies  under  normal
industrial conditions and under induced failures in the installation.
Possibility to carry out experimental studies  for different industries.2
Start date             :1988-01-01
End date               :1992-01-01
Duration in months     :48
Project status         :Completed
Programme acronym      :INDHAZ 2C
Project reference      :0006
Prime contr org        :Joint Research Centre Ispra
Prime contr dept       :Institute for Safety Technology
Prime contr address    :Sito di Ispra
Prime contr postcode   :21020
Prime contr town       :ISPRA
Prime contr region     :R3201 Varese
Prime contr country    :IT (ITALY)
 
