<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Ship-assessment of the safety of hazardous
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :26230
Quality valid. date    :1995-06-27
Update date            :1995-09-25
Title                  :Ship-assessment of the safety of hazardous
industrial processes in the presence of design faults
Subject index codes    :COO (COORDINATION, COOPERATION)
                        SCI (SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH)
General information    :Title: Quantitative Analysis - 2
This project will make a step towards developing more precise methods
for  analysis  and  assessment  of  safety  of  hazardous plants. The
project will aim maximise transfer of technology between participants
It will be structured around two tasks.
Task  1: Hierarchical, heterogeneous approach to safety analysis. The
basic  assumption  of this research is that while analysing safety we
will   face   the   problem  of  heterogeneous  hierarchy  of  models
representing  the system. The basic distinction is between the models
suitable  to  represent  the whole application, the system design and
the  software  design. A result of this task will be development of a
formal  approach  to  specification  and  analysis  of safety related
computer  applications  which  supports  a  heterogeneous hierarhical
modelling.
Task  2:  Application of Formal Methods to the assessment of critical
software.
The  aim  of  this  task  is  to  investigate the potential of Formal
Methods  for  being  used  to  strenghten  the  assessment process by
introducing more preciseness and analytical power into it.
The  results  of  the  research  will  include evaluation of a chosen
formal  method  as  a  tool  supporting formal assessment of critical
software.
Start date             :1994-04-01
End date               :1995-12-31
Duration in months     :21
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ICPECO C
Project reference      :CIPD930043
Prime contr org        :Adelard
Prime contr address    :3 Coborn Road, Coborn House
Prime contr postcode   :E2 2DA
Prime contr town       :London
Prime contr region     :R755 GREATER LONDON
Prime contr country    :GB (UNITED KINGDOM)
Contact person         :Name:         BLOOMFIELD, Robin
                    Tel:          +44-81-9830217
                    Fax:          +44-81-9831845
                  Email:        RCB@ED.LFCS.AC.UK
