<TITLE>
Buckling curves in case of fire
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :23341
Quality valid. date    :1994-11-28
Key words              :Fire, steel buildings
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Buckling curves in case of fire, M-N interaction
                       (Part III)
Subject index codes    :IND (INDUSTRIAL MANUFACTURE)
                        MAT (MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY)

Objectives             :This multi-national research project is aimed at
producing  a  simplified method of calculating the buckling behaviour
of  hot-rolled  sections  which are subjected to fire. This behaviour
must satisfy Section 10 of Eurocode 3 concerning Building Design with
regard to Fire Hazards. The work will include theoretical simulations
searching   and  analyzing  the  numerous  existing  databases,  and
carrying  out many tests of the behaviour of full scale structures to
exposure  to  fire.  Such  tests  will  provide a means of confirming
theoretical  values,  and  of  correlating  with  previous  series of
research work,

