<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Mitigation of Hazardous Fire Radiation by Water Spray Curtains
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :24009
Quality valid. date    :1995-02-22
Key words              :Water spray, hazard mitigation, fire, toxic gas
Update date            :1995-08-28
Title                  :Mitigation of Hazardous Fire Radiation by Water
                        Spray Curtain
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)

General information    :The severe consequences  of recent  accidents 
(Mexico,1984  or of Port E. Herri in Lyon, 1987)  and the  subsequent
economical  penalties  emphasize  the  need  to   propose  systematic
engineering methods  for  designing  efficient,  simple and  low cost
mitigating devices against fire. Among other solutions,  according to
encouraging preliminary  tests (1),  the  water  spray  curtain is an
attractive technique.The  final goal of the present  research will be
to optimize the fluid curtain techniques in termsof water consumption
and  spray characteristics.  The present proposal  is an extension of
the research by  the  proposers  during  the last seven years in  the
field of industrial hazard mitigation by water spray curtains. So far
this  work has been focused on accidental release of gas and led to a
numerical  model  describing  the hydrodynamic, thermal convetion and
physico-chemical effects of a single spray on toxic gascloud. Suppor-
ted by an experimental investigation, this study has led to produce a
significant data bank of hydrodynamic and physico-chemical properties
of  industrial water  sprays. This model  is being extended  to water
spray curtains  including  wind  effects, in  the frame of a research
program  partially  sup  supported  by  the  ECC  Environment Program
(EV5VCT 92 00 72, 1993-1995).This  proposal deals with the mitigation
of accidental  thermal  radiations  due to large scale fires. The ob-
jective is to propose a global model for the design  of  water  spray
protection systems suited to different types of accidents.  For  this
new purpose, the water spray will  be modelled as a  particulate bar-
rier absorbing and scattering thermal radiations. Thus the main steps
of the proposed research are : 
1) Development of a  radiative  model,  
2) Coupling  of  radiative  heat transfer with hydrodynamic and
   convective  heat  and mass transfer, 
3) Laboratory experimental  investigation,  
4) Engineering  code  and  field tests validation. The final product
   of the present research will be an engineering  code, a methodology
   and a set of guidelines to design efficient spray curtains to 
   protect environment by mitigating the detrimental effect of 
   accidental fires.  The project involves the co-operation of three
   Europeanscientific teams : 
1) the "Institut des Technologies Chimiques"   ITC-Lyon,  France,  
2) The  "Von  Karman Institute for fluid dynamics" -VKI, Khode St Genese,
   Belgique, 
3) The "Centre de Thermique de l'INSA DE Lyon" CETHIL-Lyon, France.

Start date             :1994-09-01
End date               :1997-02-28
Duration in months     :30
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0565
Prime contr org        :Institut des Technologies Chimiques de Lyon
Prime contr address    :6 Rue Jean Mace
Prime contr postcode   :69190
Prime contr town       :Saint-Fons
Prime contr region     :R2716 Rhone
Prime contr country    :FR (FRANCE)
Contact person         :Name:         JOSEPH, LIETO
                    Tel:          +33-78700040
                    Fax:          +33-0078703719
Contact name           :BUCHLIN, JEAN-MARIE
Organization           :Institut von Karman de Dynamique des Fluides
Organization type      :ROR Research
Address                :72 Chaussee de Waterloo
City                   :Rhode Saint Genese
Postcode               :1640
Region                 :R5122 Halle-Vilvoorde
Country                :BE (BELGIUM)
Telephone              :+32-2-3581901
Fax                    :+32-2-3582885
Contact name           :SACADURA, JEAN-FRANCOIS
Organization           :Institut National des Sciences Appliquees de Lyon
Organization type      :EDU Education
Address                :20 Avenue Albert Einstein
City                   :Villeurbanne
Postcode               :69621
Region                 :R2716 Rhone
Country                :FR (FRANCE)
Telephone              :+33-72438153
