<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Transport and risk communication
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
Record cntrl number    :27057
Quality valid. date    :1995-06-21
Update date            :1995-10-09
Title                  :Transport and risk communication
Subject index codes    :ENV (ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION)
                        MET (METEOROLOGY)
                        SAF (SAFETY)
Objectives             : The aims of the project are to identify the
environmental risks involved in transport systems and describe how in
three  countries environmental risks are treated in the evaluation of
transport  policies  and  projects,  identifying  and  comparing  the
importance  of  social debate in this evaluation. The intention is to
draw  up  recommendations  which allow a better communication between
the experts and the public, on the risks of transport.
General information    : The project consists of the following:
1. The gathering of data and studies concerning the transport network
in  Europe  and  the  specific position of each considered country in
this network. The economic and technical aspects are examined so that
the  behaviours  of  the  economic  and  political  actors  are  both
described  and  understood.  This  stage  is also intended to build a
common(empirical and theoretical)background concerning transportation 
systems  and a common framework in risk evaluation by scientific experts;
2.  Selected  national case-studies. They are intended to analyse the
social  process by which evaluation of risks is used by social actors
to  elaborate  alternative  projects  in  transport  systems  in each
country.  A  special  attention is given to the role of international
and European constraints and institutional settings in these projects
The  economic  constraints  and  the  social  and  political  debate
emerging  is  analysed.  The  involvement  of experts and the balance
between  local,  regional,  national and international actors and the
nature  of  the  procedural  and  institutional arrangements used are
given special consideration;
3. A comparison of the national case-studies is made and provides the
basis   for  common  conclusions  about  the  ways  to  improve  risk
communication.
Start date             :1994-04-01
End date               :1996-03-31
Duration in months     :24
Project status         :Execution
Programme acronym      :ENV 1C
Project reference      :EV5V0384
Prime contr org        :Fondation Universitaire Luxembourgeoise - ASBL
Prime contr dept       :Unite de Sociologie de l'Environnement
Prime contr address    :185 Avenue de Longwy
Prime contr postcode   :6700
Prime contr town       :Arlon
Prime contr region     :R5261 Arlon
Prime contr country    :BE (BELGIUM)
Contact person         :Name:         MORMONT, MARC
Contact name           :BARROS, AFONSO
