<HEAD>
<TITLE>Transportation Partnerships Program Grant Announcement</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/rsc/027.jpg">
<A HREF="/index.html">
<IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/photow8.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A>
<P></P>
<H2>Transportation Partnerships Program Grant Announcement</H2><P></P>
<CENTER><IMG ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER>
<!-- ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->

<P>The Governor&#146;s Office of Energy Conservation (OEC) is announcing $125,000 is available for the next funding cycle of the <I>Transportation Partnerships</I> program, depending on the volume and quality of applications received.  The application deadline for the next funding cycle is January 31, 1997.  Applications must be received no later than 5 p.m. January 31, at OEC, 1675 Broadway, Suite 1300, Denver, Colorado, 80202.
<P><I>Transportation Partnerships</I> began in 1995, as a way to encourage and assist Colorado communities trying to manage transportation demand and address the associated concerns of air quality and energy efficiency.  Since October 1995, the program has received requests for more than $900,000, and has granted nearly $400,000 to fund 19 projects around the state.  The program will continue to be funded on a quarterly basis, with upcoming deadlines of January 31 and April 30, 1997.  The amount of funding for the April deadline will be announced in mid-January.  Future funding amounts may vary depending on statewide interest and program resources.
<P><I>Transportation Partnerships </I>staff held a regional workshop December 3,1996, in Fort Collins for parties interested in developing applications for the <I>Transportation Partnerships</I> program.  If you are interested in hosting a regional workshop in your area, please contact OEC.  We also are available one-on-one to discuss project ideas with applicants.
<P>For more information on <I>Transportation Partnerships</I> or to obtain an application packet, contact Kate Fay or Jodi Asarch at (303) 620-4292 or 1-800-OEC-6662.
<!-- ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<P></P>
