<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Pew Charitable Trusts Announces Grant Program - Civic Leadership </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!-- CT - 10/28/96-->

<BODY BACKGROUND="/rsc/027.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<P><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="/rsc/photow8.gif" ALT="Center of Excellence for Sustainable Development, a Project of the US DOE's Office of  Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy"></A></P>
<P></P>




<P>
<CENTER><H2><B>Pew Announces Grant Program<BR>
For Civic Leadership</B></H2></CENTER>
<P>

<CENTER><IMG ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER>
<P></P>

According to an article in the <B>Chronicle of Philanthropy</B>
(10/3/96), the Pew Charitable Trusts in Philadelphia has announced
a $3.7 million, two-year grant program to fund &quot;civic entrepreneurs&quot;
in as many as 10 cities nationwide with populations between 150,000
and 400,000.  The program will bring together a team of 20 leaders
each year in the selected cities to solve a serious problem threatening
their communities.  One organization in each city should take
the lead in coordinating a single application on behalf of a coalition
of groups.  Grant recipients will receive $80,000 in cash to cover
both years.  Deadline for preliminary proposals is December 3,
1996.
<P>
For more information or a copy of the grant guidelines, contact
the Pew Civic Entrepreneur Initiative, 145-C Ednam Drive, Charlottesville,
VA 22903;  phone: 804/971-2073.<BR>

