<H3>About the Author</H3>
<P>Hardin B. C. Tibbs, the author of this article, is the Asia Pacific Representative of Global Business Network (GBN), the international research and consulting firm specializing in scenario planning and long-range strategy development, headed by Peter Schwartz and described in <I>The Art of the Long View</I> (the leading business book on scenario planning). GBN is based in Emeryville, California. 

<P>Hardin is resident in Sydney, where he runs his own think-tank/strategic consulting firm, Rolan Innovation &amp; Development. He is also a director of Australian Business Network (ABN), the Australian counterpart of GBN. Before moving to Australia, he was a senior consultant with GBN in California.

<P>Hardin has a particular interest in future patterns of social response to technology deployment, and in environmentally responsible applications of technology. Before joining GBN, he was a consultant with Arthur D. Little, Inc., the international management and technology consulting firm based in Cambridge, Massachusetts. 

<P>Before moving to the United States, Hardin was an independent consultant and entrepreneur in England and Europe. He has a BA degree in Industrial Design Engineering, and a Master of Science in Management (MSM). 

