<center><font size=+3>NATIONAL INDICATORS PROGRAMS</font></center>


<B>12. <a name="s">U.S. Council on Environmental Quality, SDI Group</b>
<P>
In February 1996, the Presidents Council on Sustainable Development (PCSD) published "Sustainable 
America: A New Consensus for Prosperity, Opportunity, and a Health Environment for the Future," 
the result of a three-year process among a diverse group of government, business, environmental, 
civil rights, labor, and Native American leaders.  The report to the President concluded that 
the U.S. must change by moving from conflict to collaboration and adopting stewardship and individual 
responsibility as tenets by which to live.
<P>

PCSD established goals in the following 10 areas to ensure economic prosperity, environmental protection, 
and social equity:
<P>

<table cellspacing=20>
<tr><td width=50></td><td valign=top>
<B>1.  Health and Environment<P>
2.  Economic Prosperity<P>	
3.  Equity<P>		
4.  Conservation of Nature<P>
5.  Stewardship</b>		
</td><td valign=top>
<B>6.    Sustainable Communities<P>
7.    Civic Engagement<P>
8.    Population<P>
9.    International Responsibility<P>
10.  Education</b>
</td></tr>
</table>

<BR><BR>

For more information on the goals and the Council, see the <B>PCSD Web site:</b><BR>
<a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/EOP/pcsd/index-plain.html">http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/EOP/pcsd/index-plain.html</a>
<P>

In May 1996, PCSD formed an interagency working group in to select indicators to monitor progress 
towards the goals in these 10 areas.  The working group has four principal tasks:
<P>

1. Development of a framework to identify, organize, and integrate national sustainable development indicators.  This framework will cover all aspects of global systems: society, economy, and environment.  The framework will support efforts to develop reg




ional and local indicators.
<P>

2. Development of an information system providing easy, low-cost, electronic access to federal data and information about sustainable development indicators.
<P>

3. Release of regular reports on progress toward national sustainable development indicators.
<P>

4.  Recommendation for an organizational strategy in which all levels of government, non-government organizations, and industry can collaborate on the long term evolution of sustainable development indicators.
<P>

For more information on the progress of the PCSD indicators working group, see the <B>Interagency Work 
Group on Sustainable Development Indicators Web site:</b><BR>
<a href="http://venus.hq.nasa.gov/iwgsdi">http://venus.hq.nasa.gov/iwgsdi</a>

<BR><BR><BR><BR>
